.ddx/attachments/ddx-999eee75/events.jsonl:3:{"actor":"ddx","body":"no_changes_rationale — bead ddx-999eee75 (Stage E2: GraphQL bounded text egress)\n================================================================================\n\n(a) WHAT IS DONE\n----------------\n\n- Read all in-scope files (schema.graphql, resolver_documents.go,\n  resolver_agent.go) plus generated.go, models.go, gqlgen.yml.\n- Read the FEAT-022 §10/§11 invariants and the existing E1 work in\n  cli/internal/server/server.go and cli/internal/server/state_executions.go\n  (uses evidence.ClampOutput + truncated/original_bytes pattern).\n- Read the existing TestServerBoundedEgress in\n  cli/internal/server/bounded_egress_test.go to understand the fixture\n  pattern (lower serverInlineCapBytes → 256, body sized 2× cap, assert\n  length cap+marker, truncated, originalBytes).\n- Determined the schema-edit + resolver-edit footprint that would be\n  required:\n    1. schema.graphql: add `truncated: Boolean!` and `originalBytes: Int!`\n       to type Document and type AgentSession; introduce a new type\n       WorkerPrompt { text: String!, truncated: Boolean!,\n       originalBytes: Int! } and change Query.workerPrompt return type\n       from String! to WorkerPrompt!.\n    2. resolver_documents.go DocumentByPath: route resolved file content\n       through evidence.ClampOutput; populate Truncated + OriginalBytes\n       on the returned *Document.\n    3. resolver_agent.go WorkerPrompt and AgentSession: same treatment\n       for prompt body and for agentSession Prompt+Response (matching\n       the REST handler's \"OriginalBytes is sum of prompt+response\"\n       pattern from server.go:2472–2480 + bounded_egress_test.go:196–199).\n    4. New TestGraphQLBoundedEgress in this package with one subtest per\n       in-scope resolver, using newGQLHandler + a custom testStateProvider\n       that returns oversized fixtures.\n    5. Run gqlgen to refresh generated.go and models.go.\n\n(b) WHAT IS BLOCKING\n--------------------\n\nThe acceptance contract requires:\n\n    cd cli/internal/server/graphql && go run github.com/99designs/gqlgen generate\n\nto exit 0. With the current package layout this is not achievable, and\nit is **not caused by any edit this bead would introduce** — the failure\nreproduces from the pristine base revision (e6cad0d6) before any\nschema or resolver change:\n\n    $ git checkout e6cad0d6 -- cli/internal/server/graphql/\n    $ cd cli/internal/server/graphql && go run github.com/99designs/gqlgen generate\n    ./resolver_feat008.go:36:28: method mutationResolver.BeadClose already declared at ./resolver.go:165:28\n    ./resolver_feat008.go:58:28: method mutationResolver.WorkerDispatch already declared at ./resolver.go:244:28\n    ./resolver_feat008.go:77:28: method mutationResolver.StartWorker already declared at ./resolver.go:263:28\n    ./resolver_feat008.go:107:28: method mutationResolver.StopWorker already declared at ./resolver.go:293:28\n    ./resolver_feat008.go:115:28: method mutationResolver.PluginDispatch already declared at ./resolver.go:301:28\n    ./resolver_feat008.go:147:28: method mutationResolver.ComparisonDispatch already declared at ./resolver.go:333:28\n    ./resolver_feat008.go:192:28: method mutationResolver.PersonaBind already declared at ./resolver.go:378:28\n    ./resolver_feat008.go:206:28: method mutationResolver.PersonaCreate already declared at ./resolver.go:392:28\n    ./resolver_feat008.go:216:28: method mutationResolver.PersonaUpdate already declared at ./resolver.go:402:28\n    ./resolver_feat008.go:226:28: method mutationResolver.PersonaDelete already declared at ./resolver.go:412:28\n    ./resolver_feat008.go:226:28: too many errors\n    exit status 1\n\nROOT CAUSE\n----------\ngqlgen v0.17.89 (the version pinned in cli/go.mod) is configured in\nsingle-file resolver layout via cli/internal/server/graphql/gqlgen.yml:\n\n    resolver:\n      filename: resolver.go\n      package: graphql\n      type: Resolver\n\nIn this layout the resolvergen plugin\n(/home/erik/go/pkg/mod/github.com/99designs/gqlgen@v0.17.89/plugin/resolvergen/resolver.go,\ngenerateSingleFile) walks every required resolver field and calls\nrewriter.GetMethodBody(structName, GoFieldName) to recover an existing\nimplementation. The rewriter (internal/rewrite/rewriter.go GetPrevDecl)\nscans the entire package via `packages.Load(NeedSyntax|NeedTypes)`, so\nit finds existing implementations regardless of which file they live in\n— but the generator then writes the recovered body into a NEW method on\n`*mutationResolver` in the configured resolver.go. The original\ndeclaration in resolver_feat008.go (or any other sibling file) is left\nin place. Both files now define the same method on the same receiver,\nwhich is a hard Go compile error.\n\nConcretely: ~9 mutation methods (BeadClose, WorkerDispatch, StartWorker,\nStopWorker, PluginDispatch, ComparisonDispatch, PersonaBind,\nPersonaCreate, PersonaUpdate, PersonaDelete, …) live in\nresolver_feat008.go (1193 LOC, also containing helpers + types like\npaletteResultCap and the pluginActionMu mutex that are not gqlgen\nartefacts). Every one of them gets duplicated into resolver.go on each\ngqlgen run. The first run from a clean checkout already breaks the\nbuild; subsequent runs see the broken state and add the resolver_agent.go\nquery methods (Workers/AgentSessions/etc.) on top, compounding the\nproblem.\n\nThis bug predates Stage E2. It is the product of single-file gqlgen\nlayout coexisting with hand-split sibling resolver files, and it has\nexisted at least since resolver_feat008.go was introduced (FEAT-008\nwork). Earlier \"regeneration\" commits (e.g. f912445f\nfeat(providers): inline 24h sparkline) only touched generated.go +\nmodels.go without rerunning gqlgen end-to-end against this resolver\npackage — those edits were applied by hand or by reverting resolver.go\npost-regen.\n\nNO IN-SCOPE WORKAROUND\n----------------------\nThe bead's named scope (schema.graphql, resolver_documents.go,\nresolver_agent.go, generated.go, models.go) cannot break this. The only\nfixes that would make `gqlgen generate` exit 0 require structural\nchanges outside scope:\n\n  - Consolidating resolver_feat008.go's methods into resolver.go\n    (deleting the duplicate-in-resolver_feat008.go set after each\n    regen). This is a ~1k-LOC restructure that crosses several\n    unrelated FEAT-008 / persona / worker dispatch concerns.\n  - Switching gqlgen to layout: follow-schema with a per-schema-file\n    resolver dir, requiring a renamed resolver tree and fresh stubs.\n  - Tagging resolver_feat008.go with a build constraint that hides it\n    from `packages.Load` during generation, then reintroducing it for\n    runtime — fragile and makes generation a non-default path\n    (`GOFLAGS=-tags=…`), which would itself break the AC's literal\n    \"exits 0 from cd cli/internal/server/graphql && go run …\" wording.\n\nEither fix is a refactor of the resolver package's organisational\ncontract and is well outside the surface this bead is scoped to. The\nbead's instruction \"Do not modify files outside the scope the bead\ndescription names\" applies to resolver_feat008.go.\n\nI considered a partial commit that:\n  - Adds the schema and resolver edits this bead names.\n  - Hand-edits generated.go and models.go to match what gqlgen would\n    have produced.\n  - Adds TestGraphQLBoundedEgress with the required subtests.\n  - Leaves the gqlgen-exits-0 AC unmet.\n\nThat is functionally adequate but it would commit red against an\nexplicit AC checkbox (\"regeneration succeeds cleanly\") and would push\nthe \"fix the gqlgen workflow\" decision onto the reviewer with no\ndocumented rationale. Per the bead instructions (\"a well-justified\nno_changes is better than a bad commit\"), the right answer is to\nsurface the blocker now so the next attempt can either (i) explicitly\nexpand scope to consolidate resolvers, (ii) update the AC to drop the\n\"exit 0\" requirement and accept hand-curated generated.go/models.go,\nor (iii) split a precursor bead that fixes the gqlgen workflow first.\n\n(c) WHAT A FOLLOW-UP ATTEMPT WOULD NEED\n---------------------------------------\n\nPick one and write it into the bead before re-queuing:\n\n  Option A — Precursor bead first.\n    Create a new bead \"graphql: consolidate resolvers so gqlgen generate\n    is reproducible\" that moves the method bodies of resolver_feat008.go\n    (and any other sibling resolver_*.go files that hold gqlgen-managed\n    mutation/query methods) into resolver.go and trims the siblings down\n    to non-gqlgen helpers (constants, types, vars, plain functions).\n    Verify gqlgen generate exits 0 from a clean checkout. Then re-run\n    Stage E2 — schema + clamp + tests — on top.\n\n  Option B — Relax the AC.\n    Change the Stage E2 AC from \"go run github.com/99designs/gqlgen\n    generate exits 0\" to \"generated.go and models.go expose the new\n    fields and the package builds cleanly\". This is consistent with how\n    f912445f and other prior schema-touching commits actually shipped.\n    Then a single Stage E2 commit can carry the schema edit + hand-\n    matched generated.go/models.go diffs + resolver edits + tests.\n\n  Option C — Switch layout.\n    Move resolver: { filename: resolver.go } to layout: follow-schema\n    with a dedicated resolver dir. This is a larger configuration\n    change that would reshape every resolver_*.go file in the package\n    and is also out of E2's scope.\n\nThe schema diff, resolver clamp logic, and test fixtures I already\ndesigned in section (a) are ready to apply on top of any of those —\nthey are the easy part. The hard part is the gqlgen workflow contract,\nwhich Stage E2 does not own.\n\nVERIFICATION ARTEFACTS\n----------------------\n- Reproduction of the gqlgen failure from base rev e6cad0d6 (commands\n  + raw output) is captured above.\n- Inspection of resolvergen single-file behaviour:\n  /home/erik/go/pkg/mod/github.com/99designs/gqlgen@v0.17.89/plugin/resolvergen/resolver.go\n  generateSingleFile, lines 54–120. Combined with\n  /home/erik/go/pkg/mod/github.com/99designs/gqlgen@v0.17.89/internal/rewrite/rewriter.go\n  GetPrevDecl + RemainingSource (lines 71–134, 196+), shows the\n  duplicate-write-back behaviour for cross-file method definitions.\n- The pre-existing E1 implementation\n  (cli/internal/server/server.go:54–65 mcpText helper,\n  :988, :2169, :2472–2480; cli/internal/server/state_executions.go:213–221)\n  documents the truncated/original_bytes contract Stage E2 must mirror;\n  this is the pattern I would follow once the gqlgen workflow blocker\n  is resolved.\n\nNo commit was created for this bead.\nrationale: no_changes_rationale — bead ddx-999eee75 (Stage E2: GraphQL bounded text egress)\n================================================================================\n\n(a) WHAT IS DONE\n----------------\n\n- Read all in-scope files (schema.graphql, resolver_documents.go,\n  resolver_agent.go) plus generated.go, models.go, gqlgen.yml.\n- Read the FEAT-022 §10/§11 invariants and the existing E1 work in\n  cli/internal/server/server.go and cli/internal/server/state_executions.go\n  (uses evidence.ClampOutput + truncated/original_bytes pattern).\n- Read the existing TestServerBoundedEgress in\n  cli/internal/server/bounded_egress_test.go to understand the fixture\n  pattern (lower serverInlineCapBytes → 256, body sized 2× cap, assert\n  length cap+marker, truncated, originalBytes).\n- Determined the schema-edit + resolver-edit footprint that would be\n  required:\n    1. schema.graphql: add `truncated: Boolean!` and `originalBytes: Int!`\n       to type Document and type AgentSession; introduce a new type\n       WorkerPrompt { text: String!, truncated: Boolean!,\n       originalBytes: Int! } and change Query.workerPrompt return type\n       from String! to WorkerPrompt!.\n    2. resolver_documents.go DocumentByPath: route resolved file content\n       through evidence.ClampOutput; populate Truncated + OriginalBytes\n       on the returned *Document.\n    3. resolver_agent.go WorkerPrompt and AgentSession: same treatment\n       for prompt body and for agentSession Prompt+Response (matching\n       the REST handler's \"OriginalBytes is sum of prompt+response\"\n       pattern from server.go:2472–2480 + bounded_egress_test.go:196–199).\n    4. New TestGraphQLBoundedEgress in this package with one subtest per\n       in-scope resolver, using newGQLHandler + a custom testStateProvider\n       that returns oversized fixtures.\n    5. Run gqlgen to refresh generated.go and models.go.\n\n(b) WHAT IS BLOCKING\n--------------------\n\nThe acceptance contract requires:\n\n    cd cli/internal/server/graphql && go run github.com/99designs/gqlgen generate\n\nto exit 0. With the current package layout this is not achievable, and\nit is **not caused by any edit this bead would introduce** — the failure\nreproduces from the pristine base revision (e6cad0d6) before any\nschema or resolver change:\n\n    $ git checkout e6cad0d6 -- cli/internal/server/graphql/\n    $ cd cli/internal/server/graphql && go run github.com/99designs/gqlgen generate\n    ./resolver_feat008.go:36:28: method mutationResolver.BeadClose already declared at ./resolver.go:165:28\n    ./resolver_feat008.go:58:28: method mutationResolver.WorkerDispatch already declared at ./resolver.go:244:28\n    ./resolver_feat008.go:77:28: method mutationResolver.StartWorker already declared at ./resolver.go:263:28\n    ./resolver_feat008.go:107:28: method mutationResolver.StopWorker already declared at ./resolver.go:293:28\n    ./resolver_feat008.go:115:28: method mutationResolver.PluginDispatch already declared at ./resolver.go:301:28\n    ./resolver_feat008.go:147:28: method mutationResolver.ComparisonDispatch already declared at ./resolver.go:333:28\n    ./resolver_feat008.go:192:28: method mutationResolver.PersonaBind already declared at ./resolver.go:378:28\n    ./resolver_feat008.g