.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:42:{"acceptance":"1. TestAttempt_NoChanges_StaysCanonical_NotNeedsInvestigation verifies the attempt layer does not persist needs_investigation as a status and still emits triage:no-changes-* labels.\\n2. TestAttempt_NoChanges_WiresAdjudicateNoChangesContract proves try.Attempt calls adjudicateNoChangesContract rather than leaving it only in execute_bead_loop.go.\\n3. TestExecuteBeadWorkerNoChangesVerifiedClosesImmediately, TestExecuteBeadWorkerNoChangesVerificationFailsKeepsBeadOpen, TestExecuteBeadWorkerNoChangesNeedsInvestigationKeepsBeadOpen, and TestExecuteBeadWorkerNoChangesUnjustifiedStaysOpenWithLabel remain green after the move.\\n4. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... green.\\n5. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","created_at":"2026-05-05T10:43:27.591625526Z","description":"PROBLEM\\nThe no_changes contract is still adjudicated in execute_bead_loop.go after Attempt returns, so the loop owns triage labels, no_changes_count bookkeeping, and already_satisfied closure policy instead of try.Attempt. That makes the attempt contract leaky and keeps no_changes policy split across packages.\\n\\nROOT CAUSE\\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:975-1059 calls w.adjudicateNoChangesContract, increments the no_changes counter, applies triage labels, emits no_changes_* events, and closes the bead when the contract is satisfied.\\n- cli/internal/agent/try/attempt.go:99-137 only returns OutcomeReported / OutcomeSuccess / OutcomePark for conflict recovery; it does not own the no_changes policy.\\n\\nPROPOSED FIX\\n- Move ParseNoChangesRationale, verification_command execution, and triage label/event selection into cli/internal/agent/try/attempt.go near Attempt().\\n- Extend the try outcome contract so the loop only consumes structured disposition data plus cooldown/park reason/event instructions.\\n- Keep the persisted status canonical: needs_investigation is represented with triage labels/events, not a new status value.\\n- Reduce execute_bead_loop.go to generic structured-outcome handling for the no_changes path.\\n\\nNON-SCOPE\\n- Rate-limit retry handling.\\n- Decomposition, push_failed, or push_conflict routing.\\n- Any change to the canonical status vocabulary beyond the existing triage-label contract.\\n\\nINTERSECTIONS\\n- Absorbs ddx-b24e9630 behavior.\\n","events_attachment":".execute-bead-wt-ddx-c8f79963-20260505T104148-6e54f8ef-8083652e/events.jsonl","id":".execute-bead-wt-ddx-c8f79963-20260505T104148-6e54f8ef-8083652e","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2","area:agent","kind:refactor","story:10","observed-failure"],"notes":"Superseded by ddx-71a48703. This generated worktree-prefixed bead ID failed execute-bead ref preservation because it is not a valid git ref path component.","parent":"ddx-c8f79963","priority":0,"schema_version":1,"status":"closed","title":"try.Attempt: relocate no_changes adjudication and labels","updated_at":"2026-05-05T16:16:59.135252516Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:91:{"acceptance":"1. TestExecuteLoopLanding_StagesAttachmentDir asserts that after a `ddx try \u003cid\u003e` returns success, the .ddx/attachments/\u003cid\u003e/ dir for that bead is committed (`git ls-files .ddx/attachments/\u003cid\u003e/` returns the events.jsonl, and `git status --short` shows no untracked entries under that path).\n2. TestExecuteLoopLanding_AttachmentsCommittedUnderIndexLockContention asserts the auto-commit succeeds even when a stale .git/index.lock is present at commit time (regression guard for the gitlock recovery integration).\n3. TestBeadMigrate_AutoCommits asserts that `ddx bead migrate` against a repo with closed beads carrying inline events writes the attachments AND creates a single commit with message matching `^chore\\(beads\\): externalize and archive`. The commit's path list includes all modified attachment files and any new attachment dirs.\n4. TestBeadMigrate_NoChangesNoCommit asserts `ddx bead migrate` against an already-migrated repo (no inline events to externalize, no beads to archive) does NOT create an empty commit.\n5. TestBeadReconcileAttachments asserts the new `ddx bead reconcile-attachments` operator command stages and commits any untracked .ddx/attachments/ dirs and modified attachment files, and prints a summary line `chore(beads): reconcile missing attachment commits (\u003cN\u003e dirs, \u003cM\u003e modified)`.\n6. TestBeadReconcileAttachments_NoChanges asserts the same command in a clean repo prints \"no attachment changes to reconcile\" and exits 0 without committing.\n7. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./cmd/... ./internal/bead/... ./internal/agent/... green.\n8. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-07-02T22:52:12Z","closing_commit_sha":"cb8f3f6b7f9cf55b192215f2a6a6523ed4f4a479","created_at":"2026-05-15T00:09:45.350063448Z","description":"PROBLEM\nTwo code paths write to .ddx/attachments/\u003cbead-id\u003e/events.jsonl as part of normal operation, and neither auto-commits the result. Operators end up with persistent untracked-and-modified worktree state that contradicts the project's intent (1083 attachment files ARE tracked across 11.6 MB of committed history — this is first-class audit-trail data, not detritus).\n\nConcrete demonstration today:\n\n1. Run `ddx try \u003cid\u003e` on 9 beads → 9 new untracked .ddx/attachments/\u003cbead-id\u003e/ dirs appear in main repo. Each contains routing decisions, cost-per-attempt, execution-routing-intent, prose-check.findings, execute-bead outcome — exactly the audit data the convention says we keep.\n2. Run `ddx bead migrate` → 142 events externalized into existing tracked attachment files (showing as M), 1 new untracked attachment dir, 292 beads archived (modifying .ddx/beads.jsonl and .ddx/beads-archive.jsonl), and a fresh worktree of 151 dirty files. None committed.\n3. The audit log clearly shows the historical pattern: commits like `878931ce3 chore(beads): commit missing event attachments` and `5d54258fd Merge bead ... attempt ... into main` periodically sweep up the accumulation — but it's recurring manual cleanup, not the steady-state design.\n\nROOT CAUSE\nTwo distinct writers, neither stages or commits its output:\n\nA. The execute-loop emits per-attempt routing/cost/intent events. cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go emitRouteFailureEvent (line 3872) and the routing/cost emitters all call store.AppendEvent → the bead store writes to .ddx/attachments/\u003cbead-id\u003e/events.jsonl when the bead's events are externalized (or to the inline events array when not). The Store.AppendEvent path has no follow-up `git add`. The execute-loop's chore(\"add execution evidence\") commit (visible in git log as `chore: add execution evidence [\u003crun-id\u003e]`) stages `.ddx/executions/\u003crun-id\u003e/` per AGENTS.md convention — but NOT `.ddx/attachments/\u003cbead-id\u003e/`.\n\nB. cli/internal/bead/migrate.go ArchiveWithEvents (line 561) externalizes inline events from closed/archived beads to attachments. After externalizing 142 events today across many files, the migrate command exits without staging or committing the resulting changes. The operator command surface (cli/cmd/bead.go migrate handler) has no auto-commit step analogous to the bead store's other auto-commit paths.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n1. Execute-loop landing path: extend the existing post-merge \"chore(beads): commit missing event attachments\"-style commit (or the bead's own evidence commit) to ALSO stage .ddx/attachments/\u003cbead-id\u003e/ for the bead just landed. Use the same git-index-lock recovery (cli/internal/gitlock per ddx-6a518fd9) so concurrent workers and the statusline poller do not race.\n2. `ddx bead migrate` auto-commit: after a successful migrate that wrote any attachment changes (newly externalized + newly archived rows), call a single auto-commit at end-of-run with message `chore(beads): externalize and archive (\u003cN\u003e events to \u003cM\u003e attachments, \u003cK\u003e beads archived)`. Skip the commit entirely when no changes were written (idempotent re-run is a no-op).\n3. Regression invariant: after `ddx try \u003cid\u003e` completes with `success`/`already_satisfied`, `git status --short` in the main repo MUST show zero untracked files under `.ddx/attachments/\u003cbead-id\u003e/` for that bead.\n4. Operator escape hatch: `ddx bead reconcile-attachments` — single command that stages every untracked .ddx/attachments/ dir and any modified attachment files, commits as `chore(beads): reconcile missing attachment commits (\u003cN\u003e dirs, \u003cM\u003e modified)`. Useful for one-shot cleanup of pre-existing accumulation when this fix lands (today's 10 untracked + 141 modified dirs are an immediate use case).\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Do not change WHAT gets externalized (the migrate event-externalization logic is fine).\n- Do not change ATTACHMENT FORMAT or location.\n- Do not add attachments to .gitignore (they ARE valuable cross-machine audit data per characterization).\n- Do not auto-commit .ddx/executions/\u003crun-id\u003e/ — that's per-machine and stays untracked under existing convention.\n\nDEPS\nddx-6a518fd9 (landed) — required so the auto-commits route through index-lock recovery and don't bounce on operator/statusline git contention.","events_attachment":"ddx-051500ff/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-051500ff","issue_type":"task","labels":["area:bead","area:execution","area:devx","kind:bug","phase:2"],"priority":2,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-a6b20b71","status":"closed","title":"bead: auto-commit attachment writes from execute-loop and migrate","triage.power_hint":6,"updated_at":"2026-05-15T18:51:55.615439056Z","work-failed-routes":[{"actual_power":5,"at":"2026-05-15T00:39:54Z","count":1,"model":"qwen3.6-27b-autoround","provider":"bragi-club-3090","reason":"provider_connectivity"}]}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:121:{"acceptance":"1. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... -run TestWorkHaltsOnParentBackEdge` passes.\n2. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/...` passes.\n3. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 lefthook run pre-commit` passes.","archived_at":"2026-07-02T22:52:12Z","closing_commit_sha":"880cfacf58d5c1c5135ed58327dad027280bc761","created_at":"2026-06-06T03:14:51.058731186Z","description":"PROBLEM\nThe worker still treats `mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale` as a recoverable no-progress outcome even when the just-created children still point back to the attempted bead. That leaves the same bead getting reclaimed forever while the children are structurally blocked.\n\nROOT CAUSE\n`cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go` already has no-progress and candidate-skip machinery, but it does not check for the specific back-edge case where a fresh child carries the attempted bead in its deps. Without that guard, the worker continues to re-claim the parent instead of escalating.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nWhen a run ends with `mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale` and any freshly-created child still depends on the attempted bead, emit a durable `operator_attention` event with reason `parent_back_edge`, park the bead, and stop re-claiming it. Add a regression named `TestWorkHaltsOnParentBackEdge` that proves the worker exits the loop rather than retrying the parent.\n\nNON-SCOPE\nDo not change the dependency validation commands, doctor repair logic, prompt templates, or lifecycle docs in this bead.\n\nIn-scope files:\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop_test.go\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_intake_decompose_test.go (if the test fixture needs child deps)\n\nOut-of-scope:\n- cli/internal/bead/store.go\n- cli/internal/bead/doctor.go\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go\n- cli/internal/agent/lifecycle_dispatch.go","events_attachment":"ddx-0836dde5/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-0836dde5","issue_type":"task","labels":["ac-quality:needs-refinement","area:decomposition","area:lifecycle","area:tracker","kind:correctness","kind:safety"],"parent":"ddx-e19185aa","priority":0,"queue-rank":1770,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-1089ef73","status":"closed","title":"Halt work on parent_back_edge no-progress loops","updated_at":"2026-06-13T13:58:34.771417389Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:155:{"acceptance":"1. ADR-023 lists bead-readiness reasons: `too_large`, `ambiguous_scope`, `missing_root_cause_or_current_state`, `missing_verification`, `missing_code_path_assertion`, `missing_dependency_or_parent`, `hidden_external_blocker`, `already_satisfied_candidate`.\n2. ADR-023 lists system-readiness reasons: provider/quota, transport, missing harness, ENOSPC, git lock, worktree/evidence write failure.\n3. ADR-023 lists post-attempt reasons: tests red, merge conflict, review block, no changes unverified, no changes unjustified, already satisfied.\n4. FEAT-010 maps each reason to owner surface: readiness skill, provider preflight, resource cleanup, repo lock handling, retry policy, close policy, or human triage.\n5. TD-031 is updated or explicitly annotated to preserve queue action ownership for the new taxonomy.\n6. Specs state infra/system failures must not be classified as bead defects.\n7. Documentation-only waiver is stated in closing notes; no new Go test is required unless generated references are edited.\n8. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-15T00:08:56Z","claimed-at":"2026-05-07T22:54:00Z","claimed-machine":"eitri","claimed-pid":"4097607","closing_commit_sha":"af9142fdafd6aed79e8dbcbeeceeaad6c3415de6","created_at":"2026-05-06T16:08:33.605573835Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-0c872266","depends_on_id":"ddx-8977b68b","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-06T16:09:05Z"}],"description":"PROBLEM\nFailure reasons such as too-large beads, missing tests, provider quota, ENOSPC, git locks, review transport, and no-op attempts are not consistently owned by a readiness, preflight, cleanup, retry, close-policy, or triage surface.\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\n- `docs/helix/02-design/adr/ADR-023-bead-lifecycle-quality-policy.md:50-112` defines lifecycle checkpoints and fail-open behavior but does not provide a shared failure taxonomy.\n- `docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-010-task-execution.md:535-575` describes quality hooks but does not map reason classes to owner surfaces.\n- `docs/helix/02-design/technical-designs/TD-031-bead-state-machine.md` owns queue actions but does not yet distinguish bead readiness failures from system readiness failures using the new vocabulary.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nAdd a reason taxonomy to ADR-023 and reference it from FEAT-010 and TD-031. The taxonomy must separate bead-readiness reasons, system-readiness reasons, and post-attempt reasons, and must map each reason to the subsystem that should detect/respond.\n\nNON-SCOPE\nDo not implement classifiers, cleanup, provider pause, or CLI output changes.","events_attachment":"ddx-0c872266/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-0c872266","issue_type":"task","labels":["adr:023","area:docs","area:specs","bead-quality","kind:doc","phase:2","reliability","spec:FEAT-010","spec:TD-031"],"owner":"erik","parent":"ddx-a9d130d0","priority":0,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-831899a4","spec-id":"ADR-023","status":"closed","title":"docs: define readiness failure taxonomy and owner surfaces","updated_at":"2026-05-07T22:57:54.68284288Z","work-heartbeat-at":"2026-05-07T22:54:00.020260638Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:156:{"acceptance":"1. Single doc under docs/ describing bd-as-bead-backend wiring. 2. Covers interface adapter, JSONL interchange, claim/lock translation, tradeoffs. 3. Cross-references the axon TD for comparison.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"ed95e12e752fdd85dbd75fb167a2bc65467ca98f","created_at":"2026-05-02T14:48:31.432225578Z","description":"Single-artifact documentation under docs/ that explains how to wire bd (with its doltdb backend) as the bead backend if axon adoption stalls. Cover: required interface adapter, JSONL interchange (already supported via ddx bead import/export), claim/lock translation, and tradeoffs (external dependency on bd codebase, git-for-data semantics). This is the documented fallback path; no code required.","events_attachment":"ddx-0c8c9670/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-0c8c9670","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2"," area:beads"," area:storage"," kind:docs"," backend-migration","triage:no-changes-unjustified"],"parent":"ddx-5d49b14e","priority":3,"schema_version":1,"status":"closed","title":"Document bd/doltdb fallback wiring for bead backend","updated_at":"2026-05-05T15:46:21.775806814Z","work-last-detail":"agent exited without a commit or no_changes_rationale.txt","work-last-status":"no_changes","work-no-changes-count":1,"work-retry-after":"2026-05-05T21:46:21Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:157:{"acceptance":"1. The orchestrator's 'project root mutation rejected (continuing)' warning, when emitted alongside the parent-back-edge state, is upgraded from WARN to ERROR with the offending bead ID logged. Test: dispatch_logs_error_on_root_mutation_with_back_edge.\n2. Lifecycle schema documents that 'parent' and 'deps' MUST be disjoint and that 'deps' MUST be acyclic with the parent-tree. docs/ddx/lifecycle-rules.md (or equivalent) updated; ADR file if no governing artifact already exists.\n3. Existing valid graphs continue to pass 'ddx bead doctor' without --fix and without regression — regression test against a pre-existing tracker snapshot.\n4. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./... passes.\n5. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-07-02T22:52:12Z","closing_commit_sha":"cbf7935979e8bbebfc9bba2cc891d3bbd0008d95","created_at":"2026-06-06T03:22:30.655513392Z","description":"PROBLEM\nParent bead ddx-e19185aa is too broad for one execution pass. This child owns part 3 of 3 of that parent scope.\n\nROOT CAUSE\nThe decomposition action (currently invoked when a bead is too large for one execution and the agent splits it into child beads) is writing the parent's ID as a dep edge on every child. This produces an unbreakable deadlock:\n\n  e29892a4 (parent, open) -- parent --\u003e child_A\n  e29892a4 -- parent --\u003e child_B\n  child_A.deps = [e29892a4]           \u003c- BAD: parent is also a dep\n  child_B.deps = [child_A, e29892a4]  \u003c- BAD\n\nThe parent stays open until its children close. Every child is blocked on the parent. Nothing can be claimed. ddx work loops on the parent, the orchestrator emits 'mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale', the worker retries, and burns claim budget without progress.\n\nObserved scenario (niflheim, 2026-06-04 04:30-05:13 UTC):\n- Parent: niflheim-e29892a4 ('feat(delta): async write-behind ...')\n- 10 children created during planning loops (23223661, a44a8ceb, 054c89b7, 0470ba0d, f10e9e35, f076b08c, 6c041162, 94e1df73, 9da62c2d, 5e4f9fb2)\n- Every child carried deps=[..siblings.., niflheim-e29892a4]\n- ~50 minutes of agent time + 4 strong-policy claude/opus attempts with zero feature commits; only tracker chores\n- Unwedged manually by closing the parent via 'ddx bead close', after which siblings drained correctly in foundational order\n\nRoot cause is structural, not model-capability — auto-upgrading to a stronger model does NOT fix this. The orchestrator already detects the no-progress state but its only remediation is 'retry parent', which re-enters the same loop.\n\nThere is also a 'project root mutation rejected (continuing)' warning emitted by the readiness check during this state; that's a downstream symptom of the same problem, not the cause.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nImplement only this child acceptance slice:\n- The orchestrator's 'project root mutation rejected (continuing)' warning, when emitted alongside the parent-back-edge state, is upgraded from WARN to ERROR with the offending bead ID logged. Test: dispatch_logs_error_on_root_mutation_with_back_edge.\n- Lifecycle schema documents that 'parent' and 'deps' MUST be disjoint and that 'deps' MUST be acyclic with the parent-tree. docs/ddx/lifecycle-rules.md (or equivalent) updated; ADR file if no governing artifact already exists.\n- Existing valid graphs continue to pass 'ddx bead doctor' without --fix and without regression — regression test against a pre-existing tracker snapshot.\n\nNON-SCOPE\nDo not implement parent acceptance criteria assigned to sibling child beads. Preserve every parent non-scope constraint unless this child explicitly narrows it.","events_attachment":"ddx-0c96c8b1/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-0c96c8b1","issue_type":"task","labels":["ac-quality:needs-refinement","area:decomposition","area:lifecycle","area:tracker","decomposed","kind:correctness","kind:safety"],"parent":"ddx-e19185aa","priority":0,"queue-rank":1810,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-80d6ce75","status":"closed","title":"Reject bead dep edges that re-introduce the parent or any ancestor: part 3","updated_at":"2026-06-13T13:58:34.923249996Z","work-no-changes-count":2}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:163:{"acceptance":"1. `TestExecuteBeadRejectsCommitPlusNoChangesRationale` or equivalent proves an attempt with a synthesized implementation commit and `.ddx/executions/\u003cattempt\u003e/no_changes_rationale.txt` does not return `status=success`, `outcome=merged`, or close the bead.\n2. `TestExecuteBeadMixedCommitAndBlockedNoChangesRationalePreservesEvidence` or equivalent proves a mixed result containing `status: blocked` preserves the rationale text in result/evidence and exposes a clear `mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale`-style detail.\n3. Existing legitimate zero-diff no_changes coverage still passes, including `TestNoChangesRationaleWithVerificationCommandClosesAlreadySatisfied` or the local equivalent for verification_command behavior.\n4. Existing normal commit success coverage still passes when no `no_changes_rationale.txt` is present.\n5. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... -run \"TestExecuteBead.*NoChanges|TestNoChanges.*|Test.*Mixed.*NoChanges\" -count=1` passes.\n6. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./internal/bead/...` passes or any pre-existing unrelated failure is recorded in the bead evidence without being converted to success.\n7. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-15T00:08:56Z","closing_commit_sha":"694426cc7e302ed91531fbf6a082c6b7c5a0d21c","created_at":"2026-05-12T05:23:44.206444045Z","description":"PROBLEM\nA DDx execute-bead attempt can produce both a substantive implementation commit and `.ddx/executions/\u003cattempt\u003e/no_changes_rationale.txt`, and DDx still records the attempt as `success`/`merged`. Live evidence: attempt `20260512T050728-bb18a61f` for `ddx-ef9e8aec` landed commit `15772fc85`, merged evidence commit `9e1ab8506`, and closed the bead, while `.ddx/executions/20260512T050728-bb18a61f/no_changes_rationale.txt` says `status: blocked` because the required `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./internal/bead/...` gate timed out/failed. That turns a self-reported blocked verification into a successful close.\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:1413-1428` classifies `task_succeeded` solely from `resultRev != baseRev`; it only reads `no_changes_rationale.txt` when `resultRev == baseRev`.\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:615-616` deliberately excludes `.ddx/executions/*/no_changes_rationale.txt` from synthesized code commits, so the file can coexist with a synthesized implementation commit without affecting `resultRev`.\n- `cli/internal/agent/try/no_changes.go:56-90` already parses structured `status: blocked|open|proposed` no_changes rationales, but that parser is bypassed when any implementation commit exists.\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:1360-1407` treats the returned report as authoritative; by the time the loop sees the result, the contradictory no_changes signal has been lost behind a success/merged outcome.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- Make execute-bead treat an implementation diff plus `no_changes_rationale.txt` as a non-successful mixed-signal result before close/merge success is reported. A worker must choose one lane: commit green implementation, or no_changes/status rationale.\n- Preserve the rationale text in evidence and surface a clear failure/detail such as `mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale` so the worker can retry or a follow-up bead can handle the stated blocker.\n- Ensure `status: blocked` in the rationale cannot close a bead as success when a commit also exists.\n- Keep legitimate `no_changes` behavior unchanged for zero-diff attempts and keep ordinary green implementation commits unchanged when no rationale file exists.\n\nIN-SCOPE FILES\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go`\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_*test.go` or `cli/internal/agent/try/*test.go` as needed for focused coverage\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Do not rewrite the already-landed `ddx-ef9e8aec` history.\n- Do not change Fizeau routing/model/provider selection.\n- Do not weaken legitimate already-satisfied no_changes verification.\n\nPARENT/DEPS\nParent: ddx-cc0641a7. No deps.","events_attachment":"ddx-0e46a2f5/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-0e46a2f5","issue_type":"bug","labels":["area:agent","area:bead-lifecycle","kind:bug","phase:2","prevention","spec:FEAT-010","td:031"],"parent":"ddx-cc0641a7","priority":1,"schema_version":1,"spec-id":"FEAT-010","status":"closed","title":"agent: reject commit plus no_changes rationale mixed results","updated_at":"2026-05-12T13:19:57.035027062Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:199:{"acceptance":"1. Programmatic decomposition path (the action that fans a too-large bead into children) MUST NOT add the parent as a dep. Existing action templates / system prompts are audited and amended; one golden e2e test (decompose_does_not_self_dep) creates a bead with N children and asserts every child's deps set excludes the parent.\n2. 'ddx bead doctor' (existing subcommand) gains a check 'parent_ancestor_in_deps' that scans the tracker, lists violating beads, and (with --fix) removes the offending edges. Output is stable / scriptable. Test: ddx_doctor_detects_and_repairs_back_edge.\n3. ddx work no-progress remediation: when an attempted bead's outcome is 'mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale' AND any freshly-created child carries the attempted bead in its deps, ddx auto-emits an 'operator_attention' event with reason 'parent_back_edge' and stops re-claiming that bead. (Today it loops indefinitely.) Test: ddx_work_halts_on_parent_back_edge.\n4. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./... passes.\n5. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-07-02T22:52:12Z","created_at":"2026-06-06T03:22:30.563043932Z","description":"PROBLEM\nParent bead ddx-e19185aa is too broad for one execution pass. This child owns part 2 of 3 of that parent scope.\n\nROOT CAUSE\nThe decomposition action (currently invoked when a bead is too large for one execution and the agent splits it into child beads) is writing the parent's ID as a dep edge on every child. This produces an unbreakable deadlock:\n\n  e29892a4 (parent, open) -- parent --\u003e child_A\n  e29892a4 -- parent --\u003e child_B\n  child_A.deps = [e29892a4]           \u003c- BAD: parent is also a dep\n  child_B.deps = [child_A, e29892a4]  \u003c- BAD\n\nThe parent stays open until its children close. Every child is blocked on the parent. Nothing can be claimed. ddx work loops on the parent, the orchestrator emits 'mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale', the worker retries, and burns claim budget without progress.\n\nObserved scenario (niflheim, 2026-06-04 04:30-05:13 UTC):\n- Parent: niflheim-e29892a4 ('feat(delta): async write-behind ...')\n- 10 children created during planning loops (23223661, a44a8ceb, 054c89b7, 0470ba0d, f10e9e35, f076b08c, 6c041162, 94e1df73, 9da62c2d, 5e4f9fb2)\n- Every child carried deps=[..siblings.., niflheim-e29892a4]\n- ~50 minutes of agent time + 4 strong-policy claude/opus attempts with zero feature commits; only tracker chores\n- Unwedged manually by closing the parent via 'ddx bead close', after which siblings drained correctly in foundational order\n\nRoot cause is structural, not model-capability — auto-upgrading to a stronger model does NOT fix this. The orchestrator already detects the no-progress state but its only remediation is 'retry parent', which re-enters the same loop.\n\nThere is also a 'project root mutation rejected (continuing)' warning emitted by the readiness check during this state; that's a downstream symptom of the same problem, not the cause.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nImplement only this child acceptance slice:\n- Programmatic decomposition path (the action that fans a too-large bead into children) MUST NOT add the parent as a dep. Existing action templates / system prompts are audited and amended; one golden e2e test (decompose_does_not_self_dep) creates a bead with N children and asserts every child's deps set excludes the parent.\n- 'ddx bead doctor' (existing subcommand) gains a check 'parent_ancestor_in_deps' that scans the tracker, lists violating beads, and (with --fix) removes the offending edges. Output is stable / scriptable. Test: ddx_doctor_detects_and_repairs_back_edge.\n- ddx work no-progress remediation: when an attempted bead's outcome is 'mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale' AND any freshly-created child carries the attempted bead in its deps, ddx auto-emits an 'operator_attention' event with reason 'parent_back_edge' and stops re-claiming that bead. (Today it loops indefinitely.) Test: ddx_work_halts_on_parent_back_edge.\n\nNON-SCOPE\nDo not implement parent acceptance criteria assigned to sibling child beads. Preserve every parent non-scope constraint unless this child explicitly narrows it.","events_attachment":"ddx-130cf9ab/events.jsonl","execution-eligible":false,"id":"ddx-130cf9ab","issue_type":"task","labels":["ac-quality:needs-refinement","area:decomposition","area:lifecycle","area:tracker","decomposed","kind:correctness","kind:safety"],"parent":"ddx-e19185aa","priority":0,"queue-rank":1800,"schema_version":1,"status":"closed","title":"Reject bead dep edges that re-introduce the parent or any ancestor: part 2","updated_at":"2026-06-17T20:06:21.005257886Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:296:{"acceptance":"1. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... -run 'TestIsTransientGitContention|TestFinalizeDurableAudit.*TrackerLock' -count=1` passes.\n2. A unit test asserts `isTransientGitContention` returns true for an error wrapping `TrackerLockTimeoutError`.\n3. A unit test asserts `isTransientGitContention` returns true for the literal substring \"tracker lock timeout\" as a defense-in-depth fallback.\n4. A unit test of `finalizeDurableAuditOrStop` injects a tracker-lock-timeout error and asserts: (a) `result.OperatorAttention` is NOT set, (b) the durable_audit_transient event is emitted, (c) the function returns false (don't stop).\n5. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./... -count=1` passes.\n6. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.","archived_at":"2026-07-02T22:52:12Z","closing_commit_sha":"f5ad95d750e192a6579517c58ab83d69c1216ec0","created_at":"2026-05-29T02:21:39.52547268Z","description":"PROBLEM: When two or more `ddx work` workers run concurrently against the\nsame project and worker B reaches `FinalizeDurableAudit` at the same moment\nthat worker A holds the tracker lock, worker B times out, and the loop\nclassifies the timeout as `operator_attention` and exits — even though\nnothing requires operator action. The other worker just needs to finish.\n\nOBSERVED 2026-05-28 in niflheim drain with two concurrent workers:\n- Worker1 (pid 424293) was committing tracker state for niflheim-996afcc8.\n- Worker2 (pid 681801), simultaneously finalizing niflheim-e43f04bb (an\n  ADR-051 cold-tier PUT concurrency implementation that had already run to\n  completion — 66091 tokens, 32m8.5s), hit `tracker lock timeout (max\n  elapsed, lock: /home/erik/Projects/niflheim/.ddx/.git-tracker.lock,\n  owner pid: 424293)` while trying to commit durable audit outputs.\n- Worker2 exited with `operator attention required`, releasing\n  niflheim-e43f04bb back to `open` without committing the audit trail,\n  and leaving these paths dirty: `.ddx/beads.jsonl`,\n  `.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl`, `.ddx/metrics/attempts.jsonl`,\n  `.ddx/attachments`.\n\nThe work was successful — 32 minutes of agent time produced a clean\nimplementation and commit. The lock race nuked the audit attribution and\nforced the worker to stop. Re-running it would either repeat the agent run\n(burning more tokens) or hit `already_satisfied` (with the worktree-leak\ndocumented in `ddx-274943fc`).\n\nROOT CAUSE: `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:1262-1309`\n(`finalizeDurableAuditOrStop`) calls `runtime.FinalizeDurableAudit` and\nbranches on `isTransientGitContention(err.Error())` to decide retry vs\noperator-attention. The matcher at\n`cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:1019-1034` covers `.git/index.lock`\n(via `gitlock.IsIndexLockError`) and the strings \"unable to write new index\nfile\", \"cannot lock ref\", \"unable to update the ref\" — but **does not cover\nthe DDx-specific tracker-lock error format** emitted by\n`cli/internal/agent/tracker_lock.go:243`:\n\n  \"tracker lock timeout (%s, lock: %s, owner pid: %s)\"\n\nThe tracker lock is a DDx-internal ordering lock around tracker writes\n(`.ddx/.git-tracker.lock`), held briefly during tracker-state mutations.\nConcurrent worker contention on this lock is structurally identical to\nthe `.git/index.lock` case the existing matcher handles, and the comment\non `isTransientGitContention` explicitly states the design intent:\n\n  \"A persistent cause (e.g. ENOSPC) simply keeps releasing+retrying the\n   bead, which is still preferable to halting the whole unattended drain.\"\n\nPROPOSED FIX: Extend `isTransientGitContention` to recognise the DDx\ntracker-lock-timeout string class. Recommended implementation:\n\n  1. Export a stable marker constant (or recogniser) from\n     `cli/internal/agent/tracker_lock.go` rather than string-matching\n     across packages. Suggested: a sentinel error type\n     `TrackerLockTimeoutError` wrapping the existing fields (lockDir,\n     ownerPID), with an `Is(err)` helper.\n  2. Update `FinalizeDurableAudit` and its callers to wrap the timeout\n     error with this sentinel, so callers can use `errors.Is` instead of\n     substring matching.\n  3. In `isTransientGitContention` at `execute_bead_loop.go:1019`, add a\n     branch that returns true for `errors.Is(err, TrackerLockTimeoutErr)`.\n     Keep the existing substring fallbacks for defense in depth.\n  4. Confirm via test that worker2 in the observed scenario survives the\n     lock timeout, re-enters the loop, and successfully commits on a\n     subsequent iteration when the lock releases.\n\nNON-SCOPE:\n- Changing the tracker-lock retry policy itself (timeout duration, backoff\n  curve) — only changing how the loop classifies the lock-timeout outcome.\n- Changing concurrent-worker safety guarantees on tracker writes.\n- Adding queue-level fairness or worker coordination (out of scope for\n  this bead).\n- Fixing the orphan-worktree leak that compounds this issue — tracked\n  separately in `ddx-274943fc`.\n\nIN-SCOPE FILES:\n- cli/internal/agent/tracker_lock.go (export sentinel error type)\n- cli/internal/agent/durable_audit.go (wrap timeout with sentinel where\n  it bubbles up — verify by reading line 41 and 127)\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go (extend `isTransientGitContention`)\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop_test.go (new test for tracker-lock\n  classification)\n\nOUT-OF-SCOPE FILES:\n- gitlock package (already correct for .git/index.lock; do not modify)\n- cli/cmd/work.go (exit-reason rendering unchanged)\n- Any other isTransientGitContention call sites — only the durable-audit\n  branch matters for this bug.","events_attachment":"ddx-2189a07f/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-2189a07f","issue_type":"bug","labels":["area:agent","area:bead","area:execution","kind:bug","kind:reliability","phase:iterate","spec:FEAT-010"],"needs-human-reason":"consecutive_wedge","needs-human-since":"2026-05-31T06:52:49Z","needs-human-source":"ddx work","needs-human-suggested-action":"investigate the repeated wedge (resolver hang / phase-empty heartbeats) and clear the operator-attention state once resolved","needs-human-summary":"bead wedged on 2 consecutive claims (\u003e= threshold 2; last wedge \"progress_watchdog\"); stopped re-claiming and flagged for operator attention","priority":0,"queue-rank":1250,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-eb508f6b","spec-id":"FEAT-010","status":"closed","title":"execute-bead: treat 'tracker lock timeout' as transient git contention (currently misclassifies concurrent-worker lock race as operator_attention and exits)","updated_at":"2026-06-13T13:58:32.571303648Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:339:{"acceptance":"1. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... -run 'TestExecuteBead.*Cleanup|TestCleanupAttemptWorktree' -count=1` passes.\n2. A unit test exists for each of these non-success outcomes asserting WorktreeRemove was called: provider_connectivity, no_evidence_produced, execution_failed, structural_validation_failed, land_conflict, post_run_check_failed.\n3. A unit test asserts the success-path classifier does NOT call WorktreeRemove from the new hook (landing path retains ownership).\n4. A unit test asserts `ddx try --no-merge` preserves the worktree regardless of outcome.\n5. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./... -count=1` passes.\n6. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.","archived_at":"2026-07-02T22:52:12Z","closing_commit_sha":"e979bcd786ff98bd4767596dd1ed2dbe76cddb0c","created_at":"2026-05-29T02:02:14.061932044Z","description":"PROBLEM: When a `ddx try`/`ddx work` attempt fails with any non-success\noutcome (`provider_connectivity`, `no_evidence_produced`, `execution_failed`,\n`structural_validation_failed`, `land_conflict`, `post_run_check_failed`),\nits execute-bead worktree under `~/.cache/ddx/exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-\u003cbead\u003e-\u003cattemptID\u003e/`\nis not removed. Cleanup happens only when a *subsequent attempt of the same bead*\nis launched and `RecoverOrphans` runs as pre-spawn sweep.\n\nOBSERVED 2026-05-28 in niflheim drain: a 6.6 GB worktree\n`.execute-bead-wt-niflheim-07f6f8ff-20260528T164209-f179349f` remained 9+\nhours after its attempt failed with `provider_connectivity` (bragi 502).\nThe bead's retry resolved as `already_satisfied` without spawning a new\nexecute-bead worktree (the AC was already met by partially-landed commits\nfrom the failed attempt), so `RecoverOrphans` was never called for that\nbead — the leak is permanent until another attempt at the same bead runs.\n\nThe user reports seeing this pattern consistently across drains, not just\non the one observed bead.\n\nROOT CAUSE: `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_orchestrator.go:393-411`\ndefines `RecoverOrphans` with the docstring \"the parent's responsibility —\ncall it before spawning new workers so stale worktrees from crashed previous\nattempts do not accumulate.\" The function matches strictly by\n`basenamePrefix := ExecuteBeadWtPrefix + beadID + \"-\"` and is only invoked\non a new-attempt pre-spawn path. Two leak conditions follow:\n\n  (a) Bead's retry succeeds via `already_satisfied` (no new worktree\n      spawned because the AC check resolves before agent invocation).\n      The orphan from the prior failed attempt is never matched.\n  (b) Bead is closed for any reason after a failed attempt and is never\n      re-attempted (most common in real flows — failures often resolve\n      via decomposition into different child beads, never returning to\n      the original).\n\nThe post-attempt outcome classifier at\n`cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:1966` (Classify worker outcome:\ntask_succeeded / task_failed / task_no_changes / ...) is the natural place\nto call `WorktreeRemove` for non-success classes, but does not.\nThe existing landing path at\n`cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_land.go:1088,1329,1679` calls\n`gitOps.RemoveWorktree` correctly for landing-time temp worktrees, but\nthose are different (per-landing) worktrees, not the per-attempt execute-bead\nworktree under `~/.cache/ddx/exec-wt/`.\n\nPROPOSED FIX: Add an attempt-finalize cleanup hook that runs after outcome\nclassification (around `execute_bead.go:1966-2017`) and removes the\nper-attempt execute-bead worktree when the outcome is anything other than\n`task_succeeded`. Preserve only when:\n  1. The operator explicitly opted in via `ddx try --no-merge` (preserve\n     for inspection regardless of outcome).\n  2. An `executions_mirror.go` write or evidence-capture step requires the\n     worktree to persist past classification (verify by reading the call\n     chain at `execute_bead.go:2069-2114`).\n\nImplementation steps the executing agent should follow:\n  1. Read `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:1423-2017` to confirm the\n     outcome-classification flow and identify the right post-classify hook\n     point.\n  2. Add a helper `cleanupAttemptWorktree(gitOps, workDir, wtPath, outcome,\n     preserveFlag)` that calls `gitOps.WorktreeRemove(workDir, wtPath)` for\n     non-success outcomes unless `preserveFlag` is set.\n  3. Wire it into the outcome-classification path.\n  4. Add a unit test asserting the cleanup branch for each non-success\n     outcome class, and a negative test confirming success-path keeps the\n     worktree (landing path owns that cleanup).\n  5. Update `RecoverOrphans` docstring to reflect that it's now a\n     belt-and-suspenders sweep, not the primary cleanup path.\n\nNON-SCOPE:\n- Changing `RecoverOrphans` behavior or call sites (keep it; it covers\n  hard-crash cases the new hook can't reach).\n- Adding a periodic background sweeper or `ddx doctor` flag for stale\n  worktrees (potential follow-up).\n- Changing the worktree path under `~/.cache/ddx/exec-wt/`.\n- Changing outcome-classification logic or outcome taxonomy.\n- Adding telemetry/metrics for leak rates.\n\nIN-SCOPE FILES:\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go (add the cleanup hook + helper)\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_test.go or sibling _test file (add\n  cleanup tests for each non-success outcome)\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_orchestrator.go (docstring update on\n  RecoverOrphans only; behavior unchanged)\n\nOUT-OF-SCOPE FILES:\n- execute_bead_land.go — landing-time temp-worktree cleanup is correct\n  and untouched.\n- Any code under cli/cmd/ — no CLI surface change required.\n- docs/ — documentation update is downstream of the spec-evolution bead\n  ddx-828a1b8f (worktree resource isolation) and not required here.","events_attachment":"ddx-274943fc/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-274943fc","issue_type":"bug","labels":["area:agent","area:execution","kind:bug","kind:operability","phase:iterate","spec:FEAT-010"],"needs-human-reason":"consecutive_wedge","needs-human-since":"2026-05-31T05:20:40Z","needs-human-source":"ddx work","needs-human-suggested-action":"investigate the repeated wedge (resolver hang / phase-empty heartbeats) and clear the operator-attention state once resolved","needs-human-summary":"bead wedged on 2 consecutive claims (\u003e= threshold 2; last wedge \"progress_watchdog\"); stopped re-claiming and flagged for operator attention","priority":0,"queue-rank":1240,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-90ab9f5e","spec-id":"FEAT-010","status":"closed","title":"execute-bead: clean up worktree on non-success attempt outcomes (currently leaks on failed-then-retried-as-already_satisfied path)","updated_at":"2026-06-13T13:58:32.524062179Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:360:{"archived_at":"2026-07-02T22:52:12Z","closing_commit_sha":"277f6be2aa285202336cd399c669bd1f8f03cf81","created_at":"2026-06-28T04:37:40.306667675Z","description":"PROBLEM\nThe test TestPreDispatchDirtyPreserveRequiresStableImplementationDirt at cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop_stay_alive_test.go:836 fails on a normally-loaded developer machine because it uses a fixed 150ms context.WithTimeout for an in-process worker.Run() call that has to claim + execute + land + close one bead and continue polling. The 150ms budget is too tight; observed outcome on base revision edbcd9aa5: err is nil (work completes before deadline OR worker exits cleanly via another path), so require.ErrorIs(t, err, context.DeadlineExceeded) at line 882 fails.\n\nThis is a release-blocker: lefthook run pre-commit fails, blocking every subsequent bead from landing. Diagnosed in ddx-47d9100a's no_changes_rationale (the implementer correctly identified it as out-of-scope pre-existing breakage from commit 4555a083f, introduced by ddx-df319cf9).\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop_stay_alive_test.go:871 — context.WithTimeout 150*time.Millisecond\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop_stay_alive_test.go:882 — require.ErrorIs(t, err, context.DeadlineExceeded)\n- Adjacent test ~line 726 (TestPreDispatchDirtyPreservePersistsStableImplementationDirt) uses the correct pattern: 30s outer timeout, worker.Run in a goroutine, require.Eventually polling for bead closure, then cancel(). See the comment at lines 772-774 explaining why 750ms was too tight.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nRewrite TestPreDispatchDirtyPreserveRequiresStableImplementationDirt to match the surrounding require.Eventually pattern:\n1. Outer ctx timeout: 30*time.Second.\n2. Run worker.Run in a goroutine, push result+err to a runCh.\n3. require.Eventually (25s budget, 50ms tick) polls store.Get(\"ddx-int-0001\") until Status == StatusClosed.\n4. cancel() the outer ctx; \u003c-runCh to collect outcome.\n5. Assertions become: outcome.err is one of context.Canceled or context.DeadlineExceeded (use require.True with errors.Is check), Attempts=1, Successes=1, Failures=0, OperatorAttention nil, no \"loop.pre_dispatch_dirty_preserved\" event, no refs/ddx/pre-dispatch references.\n\nIN-SCOPE FILES\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop_stay_alive_test.go (only the failing test)\n\nOUT-OF-SCOPE\n- Do not modify production code.\n- Do not touch the passing adjacent test.\n- Do not modify other 150ms or sub-second timeouts in this file; this bead targets only the named test.\n\nAC\n1. cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop_stay_alive_test.go:TestPreDispatchDirtyPreserveRequiresStableImplementationDirt rewritten to use require.Eventually + goroutine pattern with 30s outer timeout, mirroring TestPreDispatchDirtyPreservePersistsStableImplementationDirt at ~line 726.\n2. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... -run 'TestPreDispatchDirtyPreserve' -count=5 green (5x to confirm non-flaky).\n3. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... -count=1 green.\n4. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n5. The test still verifies the same invariants: a single bead claim+close happens, OperatorAttention is nil, no pre-dispatch refs are written.","events_attachment":"ddx-298ade98/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-298ade98","issue_type":"bug","labels":["phase:iterate","area:test","area:agent","kind:bug","flaky","blocks-drain","pre-commit-blocker","regression:ddx-df319cf9"],"priority":0,"queue-rank":0,"schema_version":1,"status":"closed","title":"test: fix flaky 150ms timeout in TestPreDispatchDirtyPreserveRequiresStableImplementationDirt","updated_at":"2026-06-28T07:43:22.1532597Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:371:{"acceptance":"AC1. ddx try/ddx work treats success outcome and bead-state propagation as a single recoverable unit: if the finalize step fails after outcome=task_succeeded is written, the next pick of the same bead detects the dangling result_rev and either lands it or surfaces a structured error (not silent no_evidence_produced).\nAC2. A regression test exercises the dangling-success scenario by simulating a finalize failure and asserting the bead lands cleanly on retry.\nAC3. ddx doctor (or a new diagnostic command) detects executions where result.json claims success but result_rev is unreachable from any branch, and reports them with the recovery command (git merge --no-ff \u003csha\u003e + ddx bead close --commit \u003csha\u003e --session \u003csid\u003e).\nAC4. Documentation in the ddx skill or work.md describes this failure mode and how operators can recover manually until AC1 ships.","archived_at":"2026-05-15T00:08:56Z","closing_commit_sha":"004453de063a4e607c7178079ca1ff207be7014e","created_at":"2026-05-08T21:00:40.247216169Z","description":"PROBLEM: A ddx try/ddx work attempt that produces outcome=task_succeeded and a clean result_rev may fail to auto-merge or update the bead state, leaving the success commit unreachable from any branch and the bead stuck in_progress. Operators must manually recover by checking out the dangling SHA, verifying ACs, and merging.\n\nREPRO (observed in axon project, 2026-05-08):\n- Bead axon-d323acc9 (\"refactor(axon-schema): import named-query parser from axon-cypher-ast\")\n- Attempt 20260508T190516-8d61a244, session eb-b068c4db\n- result.json fields: outcome=task_succeeded, status=success, result_rev=c3386193ab1c18fdf5739901c41d2e69093f1030, base_rev=9194da47097b2d0d05899a51688950084b3995b8, duration_ms=1179708, exit_code=0\n- Master HEAD never advanced to include c3386193; bead remained in_progress until manual recovery\n- A subsequent attempt 20260508T192511-c4a200de fired 15 seconds later and recorded outcome=task_no_evidence with detail \"agent exited without a commit or no_changes_rationale.txt\", which suggests the worker re-ran and saw no work to do (the success was already in the dangling commit) but did not connect that to the prior success record.\n\nCURRENT STATE:\n- Both attempt result.json files are present and parsable.\n- Recovery required: git merge --no-ff \u003cresult_rev\u003e + ddx bead close --commit \u003cresult_rev\u003e --session \u003csession_id\u003e.\n- No evidence in the bead events indicated the attempt had succeeded; the success was discovered by inspecting result.json on disk.\n\nPROPOSED FIX DIRECTION (owned by ddx-loop/finalize maintainer):\n1. The post-execute finalize step (merge + bead update with success event) should be transactional with attempt outcome, or at minimum idempotent so a follow-up ddx work cycle can complete it.\n2. On bead pick, if status=in_progress and the most-recent attempt outcome=success but no merge commit references the result_rev, attempt to land that result before claiming new work or starting a fresh attempt.\n3. A startup self-check could enumerate result.json files where outcome=task_succeeded and ensure the corresponding result_rev is reachable from a branch; surface inconsistencies as recoverable state.\n\nNON-SCOPE: defining the merge strategy (no-ff vs ff-only is already settled by skill guidance); changing result.json schema.","id":"ddx-2b2d114e","issue_type":"bug","labels":["area:ddx-finalize","area:ddx-loop","kind:bug","priority:p1"],"priority":1,"schema_version":1,"status":"closed","title":"bug: ddx try success outcome leaves dangling commit when finalize step fails","updated_at":"2026-05-09T02:11:09.022316745Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:388:{"acceptance":"All three child beads are closed. The exit-gate one-liner above runs end-to-end against a real ready bead on a host with a healthy vidar-omlx provider and produces a non-error closing status (success / already_satisfied) or a meaningful provider-side error — not 'unexpected end of JSON input' and not 'Model not found' 404s for catalog-missing refs.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"cf4544f0cb71adcbe7ab7e10fec340474756704f","created_at":"2026-04-18T00:57:02.418274493Z","description":"## Target user experience\n\nAn operator declares a local MLX server (omlx flavor) once in .agent/config.yaml:\n\n    providers:\n      vidar-omlx:\n        type: openai-compat\n        base_url: http://vidar:1235/v1\n        flavor: omlx\n\nAnd invokes work with a canonical model ref:\n\n    ddx work --once --local --provider vidar-omlx --model-ref qwen/qwen3.6\n\nExpected outcome: DDx fuzzy-matches qwen/qwen3.6 against vidar-omlx's discovered models (finds Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-4bit), dispatches through the embedded agent runtime, streams a valid response, runs the execute-bead worktree loop, and lands or preserves the attempt with an honest status.\n\nToday this fails at multiple layers. The audit for this epic (2026-04-17) traced the resolution path end-to-end and identified concrete structural gaps between SD-015/SD-023 and the current implementation. A fresh-eyes review (codex + opus, 2026-04-17) pressure-tested the plan and led to the child-bead list below.\n\n## Child gaps (all must land for the target UX)\n\n**Foundation (unblocks everything):**\n- ddx-8610020e (P1, bug): RouteRequest has no Provider field; --provider is silently dropped at routing normalization unless it names a harness. AC includes explicit --harness × --provider precedence rules.\n\n**Discovery layer:**\n- ddx-0486e601 (P1, bug): fuzzy matcher needs canonical-prefix stripping + case-fold AND per-provider-aware pool variant. Merged from two earlier beads (normalization + per-provider) per fresh-eyes review — same file, same test surface, one coherent change.\n\n**Integration layer:**\n- ddx-2f5a2284 (P2, bug): catalog/Profile paths skip discovery; fuzzy only fires for uncataloged pins. Fix adds discovery consultation when req.Provider is pinned. AC includes bare-leaf refs ('qwen3.6' not just 'qwen/qwen3.6').\n- ddx-3c5ba7cc (P1, task): tier escalation respects --provider affinity.\n\n**Dispatch layer:**\n- ddx-6a5dfe35 (P1, bug): parse failure at ddx-agent ↔ omlx boundary. Re-scoped per fresh-eyes review to require wire-level evidence before blaming upstream — the 'direct curl works' isolation is insufficient to pin the defect.\n\n**Documentation:**\n- ddx-e3493010 (P2, task): 'Resolution Path' developer guide tracing CLI flag -\u003e HTTP dispatch. AC includes CI grep verifying file:line citations resolve (prevents doc rot).\n\n**Phase 2 — tracked as siblings, NOT exit-gate blockers:**\n- ddx-4817edfd (P2, task): capability gating (context window, tool support, effort, permissions). Tracks sub-bead decomposition; epic's exit gate does NOT require it.\n- ddx-0216b966 (P3, task): fuzzy match tiebreak — prefer latest version over shortest-suffix. Inherited quirk; flag + track.\n\n**Closed as invalid or merged:**\n- ddx-e59e7fe8 (catalog entries): wrong diagnosis (closed as invalid). Fuzzy normalization + per-provider pool + discovery integration make catalog entries unnecessary.\n- ddx-b388f45a (per-provider fuzzy): merged into ddx-0486e601 per review — same file, same test surface.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- .ddx/executions/20260418T005017-ac81ac97/ — attempt 1 (tier escalation + catalog mismatch)\n- .ddx/executions/20260418T005052-3aad2cfa/ — attempt 2 (parse failure)\n- Audit file:line citations in bead bodies; gap map in this description.\n\n## Exit gate\n\n'ddx work --once --local --provider vidar-omlx --model-ref qwen/qwen3.6' against a real ready bead on a host with healthy vidar-omlx completes with a closing status (success / already_satisfied) or a meaningful provider/model error — not 'unexpected end of JSON input' and not 'Model not found' 404s for refs the discovery layer could have fuzzy-matched.\n\nPhase-2 siblings (capability gating, tiebreak polish) remain open after the exit gate closes; they are tracked separately.","id":"ddx-2d974641","issue_type":"epic","labels":["ddx","phase:build","kind:implementation","area:agent","area:routing","area:catalog","goal:throughput-per-dollar"],"priority":1,"resolution_note":"Superseded by upstream agent work agent-1a486c2e (consolidated ResolveRoute) plus the routing capability gating beads (ddx-8610020e, ddx-0486e601, ddx-3c5ba7cc, ddx-2f5a2284, ddx-0216b966, ddx-4817edfd subtree). After agent v0.5.0 the routing engine is consolidated in agent's internal/routing.ResolveRoute with all capability gating in place. End-to-end omlx autorouting works via the unified resolver.","schema_version":1,"spec-id":"FEAT-006","status":"closed","title":"Epic: autorouting — 'there's an omlx on vidar, use qwen3.6' should Just Work end-to-end","updated_at":"2026-04-19T16:19:34.528683997Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:419:{"acceptance":"1. `TestExecuteBead_DirtyNoEvidencePreservesAttempt` proves a fake runner that leaves dirty code files, exits 0, and writes no commit/rationale returns `no_evidence_produced` with a non-empty preserve ref or patch artifact instead of deleting the attempt.\n2. `TestExecuteBead_CleanNoEvidenceStillCleansWorktree` proves a clean no-evidence attempt still cleans up normally and does not create a preserve artifact.\n3. `TestWorkLoopNoEvidenceReportsPreserveLocation` proves `ddx work` output/bead event includes the preserve ref or patch path for dirty no-evidence attempts.\n4. `TestRealGitOpsWorktreeRemoveReportsFailure` proves `RealGitOps.WorktreeRemove` returns an error when `git worktree remove --force` fails instead of swallowing it.\n5. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... -run 'TestExecuteBead_DirtyNoEvidencePreservesAttempt|TestExecuteBead_CleanNoEvidenceStillCleansWorktree|TestWorkLoopNoEvidenceReportsPreserveLocation|TestRealGitOpsWorktreeRemoveReportsFailure' -count=1` passes.\n6. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.\n","archived_at":"2026-07-02T22:52:12Z","closing_commit_sha":"8cde0b39a03e58d509551e8de4a4c12fabb5cc72","created_at":"2026-06-13T23:42:40.773782316Z","description":"PROBLEM\n\nDuring dogfood on 2026-06-13, `ddx work --once` for ddx-c02ce93c ran a provider attempt that edited implementation files and exited 0, but produced no commit and no `no_changes_rationale.txt`. DDx reported `no_evidence_produced` with dirty paths, then removed the isolated attempt worktree. The operator could not rescue the provider patch from the worktree and had to manually reimplement from partial observed output. A worker surface that destroys dirty provider output after a successful process exit is not acceptable: DDx must preserve or export recoverable evidence for underspecified provider/commit failures.\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\n\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:1416-1427` classifies clean-exit/no-commit/no-rationale as `task_no_evidence` and records dirty paths, but it does not convert dirty no-evidence into a preserved recoverable attempt.\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:943-954` defers attempt cleanup for all non-preserved worktree attempts; because `task_no_evidence` is not preserved, cleanup proceeds.\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:1577-1588` removes every non-success attempt worktree unless a preserve flag is set, including dirty `task_no_evidence` attempts.\n- `cli/internal/agent/gitops_real.go:35-37` ignores `git worktree remove --force` errors, so cleanup failures would also be underreported.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n\nTreat dirty `task_no_evidence` as recoverable provider output: before cleanup, preserve the worktree with a `refs/ddx/iterations/\u003cbead\u003e/\u003cattempt\u003e` ref or export a patch/artifact that contains every dirty path and enough metadata to reconstruct the attempt. Worker output and bead events must name the preserve ref or patch path. Only clean no-evidence attempts may be removed normally.\n\nIN-SCOPE FILES\n\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go\n- cli/internal/agent/gitops_real.go\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_integration_test.go\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_e2e_test.go\n\nNON-SCOPE\n\nDo not change legitimate `no_changes_rationale.txt` handling. Do not preserve clean no-evidence attempts without dirty paths. Do not kill or change provider subprocess supervision; ddx-c02ce93c handled that separately. Do not hand-edit `.ddx/beads.jsonl`.\n\nDOGFOOD EVIDENCE\n\nAttempt `20260613T225213-a01c938c` for ddx-c02ce93c exited 0 after editing `cli/cmd/work_status_test.go`, `cli/internal/agent/agent_runner_service.go`, `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go`, `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go`, provider child files, liveness/status files, and then DDx deleted `/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-c02ce93c-20260613T225213-a01c938c`.\n","events_attachment":"ddx-3141b561/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-3141b561","issue_type":"bug","labels":["phase:build","area:agent","area:work","kind:bug","kind:reliability","severity:critical","no-evidence","rescue"],"parent":"ddx-9d1af129","priority":0,"queue-rank":-600,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-f2b0c809","status":"closed","title":"agent: preserve dirty no-evidence attempts for rescue","updated_at":"2026-06-14T00:27:48.409705305Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:429:{"acceptance":"1. Add Niflheim-evidence regression fixtures or table-driven cases under `cli/internal/agent/...` that encode the four observed scenario families from this bead: empty review success, land/ref/index/evidence-staging failure, decomposed-parent no-changes rationale with child beads, and repeated pre-claim system-unready warning. The fixtures must be self-contained and must not reference Niflheim paths as required inputs.\n2. `TestExecuteBeadWorker_NiflheimEvidence_EmptyReviewResultCannotClose` proves a non-skipped success path with `cycle_trace.review_result={}` or an equivalent empty `ReviewResult` cannot close a bead and records `review_error` or operator-attention with a non-empty reason.\n3. `TestExecuteBeadWorker_NiflheimEvidence_NilReviewerRequiresExplicitSkip` updates the current nil-reviewer behavior so `Reviewer: nil` only closes when an explicit durable no-review/skip reason is present; otherwise it fails review gating.\n4. `TestExecuteBeadLoop_NiflheimEvidence_LandCoordinationFailureDoesNotRerunImplementation` simulates both observed details (`cannot lock ref refs/heads/main` after a candidate/merge is already landed, and `landing worktree has staged changes after waiting 2s`) and asserts the action is reconcile/retry-land/operator-attention, not a fresh implementation run and not model escalation.\n5. `TestExecuteBeadLoop_NiflheimEvidence_DecomposedParentIsExecutionIneligible` simulates `mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale` with `orchestrator_action: decompose`, child bead IDs, and `outcome_reason=decomposed`; it asserts the parent is marked execution-ineligible/proposed or dependency-waiting according to policy and that no further implementation attempt or min-power escalation is scheduled.\n6. `TestWorkRetryEscalation_NiflheimEvidence_OnlySemanticFailuresRaiseMinPower` proves only semantic acceptance/review failures can increase requested min power/profile. Land coordination, repeated pre-claim system warnings, decomposed-parent outcomes, and dirty generated DDx evidence must not raise min power.\n7. `TestExecuteBeadResult_NiflheimEvidence_CycleTraceCarriesDecisionAudit` proves result JSON/event bodies include `failure_class`, `retry_action`, `escalation_count`, requested/actual routing facts, review status/verdict or explicit skip reason, and land/reconcile status for the Niflheim scenario families.\n8. Existing related behavior from `ddx-2965925e`, `ddx-b2846610`, and `ddx-d67f124e` remains covered; this bead either reuses their helpers or waits for those dependencies, and does not add duplicate low-level implementations.\n9. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -run 'NiflheimEvidence|EmptyReviewResult|NilReviewer|LandCoordination|DecomposedParent|RetryEscalation|CycleTraceCarriesDecisionAudit' -count=1` passes.\n10. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -count=1` passes.\n11. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.","archived_at":"2026-07-02T22:52:12Z","created_at":"2026-06-06T15:55:41.332809555Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-334c0958","depends_on_id":"ddx-2965925e","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-06-06T15:55:53Z"}],"description":"PROBLEM\nA live Niflheim worker audit on 2026-06-06 showed that `ddx work` is not yet a stable release-grade autonomous worker. Strong-model escalation exists, but it is not reliably tied to the class of failure. The worker spent repeated attempts on structural or system failures that stronger models cannot fix, while automatic review evidence was empty on attempts that were recorded as successful. This violates the DDx engineering principle \"Cheapest Viable, Escalate on Evidence\" (docs/dev/engineering-principles.md:39-45): review, runtime, or retry evidence should determine escalation, and only lower-power inability to meet acceptance criteria should push to stronger routes. It also threatens FEAT-010 task-execution reliability because beads can be retried, escalated, or closed without a typed, auditable reason.\n\nThis bead is a Niflheim incident/regression closure bead. It is not a duplicate of the narrower queue items listed under INTERSECTIONS; instead it captures the external evidence DDx workers will not otherwise have, and requires a DDx-side regression suite proving those observed scenarios classify correctly before rerun, escalation, operator attention, or close.\n\nBACKGROUND AND OBSERVED NIFLHEIM EVIDENCE\nThe evidence was gathered from Niflheim worker logs and result bundles, but those files are not load-bearing for this bead. The relevant facts are copied here because an isolated DDx worker cannot access the Niflheim repository or `/tmp` logs.\n\n1. Decomposed parent kept consuming attempts and escalated to a stronger model anyway.\n- Niflheim bead: `niflheim-64217cc5`, title \"Instrument cold replicator with structured per-operation S3 tracing\".\n- Observed result bundle: `.ddx/executions/20260606T152006-a4ca7254/result.json` plus worker logs from 2026-06-05/2026-06-06.\n- Routing showed escalation exists: repeated routes started at `gpt-5.4-mini` with requested min powers 5, 7, 8, and 9, then reached `gpt-5.5` at requested min power 10.\n- Metrics on the bead showed `attempt_count=24`, `total_tokens=19371353`, and average duration about `244112ms`.\n- Despite triage recommending `close_decomposed_or_mark_execution_ineligible`, retries continued until the latest event recorded:\n  `mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale`\n  `powerClass=standard`\n  `rationale: status: open`\n  `orchestrator_action: decompose`\n  `reason: parent bead exceeds the Step 0 size threshold and is already decomposed into focused child beads for tracing, counters, tests, and runbook work.`\n  `child_beads: niflheim-f03c61a2, niflheim-df407aa8, niflheim-7a421ede, niflheim-0bbed6c9`\n  `outcome_reason=decomposed`\n- Expected DDx behavior: once the worker has reliable evidence that the bead is a decomposed parent or execution-ineligible parent, no further implementation attempt or model escalation should occur. It should mark execution-ineligible/proposed/operator-attention according to policy and move on.\n\n2. Land/evidence coordination failures were treated like implementation failure and retried expensively.\n- Niflheim bead: `niflheim-c75aba30`, title \"Materializer per-merge memory footprint OOMs even at concurrent_limit=8\".\n- Two expensive attempts both used `gpt-5.4-mini`; no useful stronger-model escalation was observed.\n- Metrics showed `attempt_count=2`, `total_tokens=65513510`, and average duration about `3306461.5ms`.\n- First attempt result: `.ddx/executions/20260606T113550-7b29ee42/result.json`.\n  - `status=execution_failed`, `outcome=error`.\n  - Implementation result commit was `7aaeb0712...`; a merge commit `2c6f4d6e6` was later observed as an ancestor of HEAD, but the result still recorded a land coordination failure.\n  - Error detail:\n    `land coordination failed: land advancer: restoring refs/heads/main to ba2d3059f14e834dcb147f2a6db3b294d83b0fac after evidence commit failed: git update-ref refs/heads/main: fatal: update_ref failed for ref 'refs/heads/main': cannot lock ref 'refs/heads/main': is at 5a176b332b182f2a959614f63769d835c47ffd97 but expected 2c6f4d6e6961b8a93742cde66bceec056934655a`\n  - `cycle_trace[0].final_decision=\"success\"` and `cycle_trace[0].review_result={}`.\n- Second attempt result: `.ddx/executions/20260606T142223-94f8f0f8/result.json`.\n  - `status=execution_failed`, `outcome=error`.\n  - Error detail:\n    `land coordination failed: land advancer: landing worktree has staged changes after waiting 2s: A .ddx/executions/20260606T150832-af40450b/result.json`\n  - `cycle_trace[0].final_decision=\"success\"` and `cycle_trace[0].review_result={}`.\n- At observation time the worker had claimed it again (`20260606T152024-a21d8c54`) and edited six files in a fresh isolated worktree:\n  `crates/niflheim-core/src/config/mod.rs`, `crates/niflheim-core/src/config/tests.rs`, `crates/niflheim-core/src/config/types.rs`, `crates/niflheim-delta-writer/src/materializer/config.rs`, `crates/niflheim-delta-writer/src/materializer/executor.rs`, and `crates/niflheim-delta-writer/src/materializer/tests.rs`.\n- Expected DDx behavior: land/ref/index/evidence-staging failures are system or coordination failures, not model-quality failures. The retry policy should reconcile a successfully landed candidate when possible, retry only the land/evidence step when safe, or park/operator-attention the bead when the landing worktree is dirty. It should not blindly rerun implementation at the same or stronger route.\n\n3. Pre-claim intake/system dirt caused repeated warning churn instead of a clear operator lane.\n- Niflheim bead: `niflheim-a62d31ce`, title \"Publish competitive benchmark artifacts and provenance metadata\".\n- A live worker repeatedly ran readiness/intake. The log showed readiness timeout after five minutes, then:\n  `preserved pre-dispatch implementation changes in /home/erik/Projects/niflheim under refs/ddx/pre-dispatch/20260606T153517-f7a32618; released niflheim-a62d31ce and continuing watch. dirty paths: .ddx/harness-sessions/-2929681.json. recover with git stash apply refs/ddx/pre-dispatch/20260606T153517-f7a32618`\n- Bead events included `pre_claim_intake.warn` with timeout/system-unready reason and generic suggested action.\n- Expected DDx behavior: repeated same/systemic pre-claim warnings and dirty generated DDx artifacts should become an operator-visible/system-unready state after the configured threshold, not an indefinite poll/release loop.\n\n4. Automatic reviews were not forcing meaningful quality improvement.\n- Recent Niflheim \"success\" attempts had empty review results:\n  - `niflheim-9dea95da`, result `.ddx/executions/20260606T043655-845c77ee/result.json`: closed success, `cycle_trace.review_result={}`, `final_decision=\"success\"`, model `gpt-5.4-mini`, result commit `78e51a168...`.\n  - `niflheim-da4e1311`, result `.ddx/executions/20260606T085358-d80ada3e/result.json`: closed success, `cycle_trace.review_result={}`, `final_decision=\"success\"`, model `gpt-5.4-mini`, result commit `d43be3a3...`.\n  - `niflheim-c75aba30` attempts listed above: `cycle_trace.final_decision=\"success\"` with `review_result={}` despite overall land failures.\n- Manual Claude review earlier improved bead wording and completeness, but the automatic worker path did not show enforceable per-AC review evidence.\n- Expected DDx behavior: unless review is explicitly skipped with a durable reason (`runtime.NoReview` or a valid `review:skip` + reason policy), an empty review result must be a review error or operator-attention signal. It must not be treated as approval, success, or evidence of quality improvement.\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\n- `cli/internal/agent/failclass/failclass.go:103-142` contains the normative routing table: only `OutcomeGenuineFailure` can escalate; dirty worktree, transport, quota, auth, setup, timeout, and merge-conflict do not escalate. The live Niflheim behavior shows execute-bead/work outcomes are not consistently reduced to this typed table before retry/escalation decisions.\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_orchestrator.go:305-309` wraps `LandingAdvancer` errors as generic `land advancer` errors. The caller can record an overall `execution_failed` without distinguishing landed-candidate reconciliation, ref/index contention, staged evidence dirt, or dirty landing worktree from implementation failure.\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:1967-2072` emits pre-claim timeout/system-unready outcomes as warn-only by default and continues implementation when strict intake blocking is off. This permits repeated same-fingerprint/system warnings to look like a live worker instead of a system-unready/operator lane.\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:2175-2315` handles `PreClaimIntakeTooLargeDecomposed`, but missing/empty decomposition paths can warn and continue. `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:3826-3831` can recognize execution-ineligible/decomposed state only after the bead has the right metadata. The Niflheim parent evidence shows structural/decomposed-parent outcomes can still reach repeated implementation attempts and power escalation.\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:3042-3138` treats success disposition/status as closeable once candidate-cycle review/landing has allowed success, and the old post-merge review is optional. `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_review_test.go:799-823` explicitly proves a worker with `Reviewer: nil` can skip review and close the bead. `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_review.go:168-193` defines `ReviewResult` with all fields optional except the zero-value enum field; no invariant rejects `{}` as a success-path review artifact.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- Add compact Niflheim-style regression fixtures under `cli/internal/agent/testdata/niflheim_worker_evidence/` or equivalent. The fixtures should encode the four scenario families above: empty review success, land coordination/ref-lock/staged-evidence failure, decomposed-parent no-changes rationale with child beads, and repeated pre-claim system-unready warning. Do not depend on Niflheim checkout paths.\n- Introduce or tighten a single execute-bead retry classification boundary that maps attempt result, land result, review result, no-changes rationale, and pre-claim intake outcome into exactly one action: close, retry same tier, escalate min power/profile, reconcile land/evidence, execution-ineligible/proposed, or operator-attention. Wire this boundary into `ddx work`/`ddx try` so `failclass.Classify` is not merely a standalone helper.\n- Enforce review evidence on success. For non-skipped success paths, `cycle_trace.review_result` or the equivalent result field must contain a non-empty verdict, per-AC evidence or documented reason, reviewer routing/session metadata when available, and a classification. `{}` is invalid and must prevent close or produce a review-error/operator-attention event. Explicit review skips remain allowed only when they are durable, reasoned, and visible in result JSON.\n- Classify land/ref/index/evidence-staging failures separately from implementation/model failures. If the candidate commit or merge is already landed or is an ancestor of the target, reconcile and close/continue without rerunning implementation. If the landing worktree has staged generated evidence or DDx metadata, retry/preserve the land/evidence step or move to operator attention according to the existing local reliability policy; do not escalate the model for this class.\n- Classify decomposed-parent/no-changes rationale as execution-ineligible or operator work before another implementation attempt. Stronger models cannot fix parent beads that are already split into executable children.\n- Make worker result JSON and event bodies carry enough audit fields to explain the decision: `failure_class`, `retry_action`, `escalation_count`, requested/actual power/profile/model, review status/verdict, and land/reconcile status.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Do not change Fizeau route selection or hard-code concrete provider/model names. DDx should continue to pass power/profile intent and let Fizeau choose concrete routes.\n- Do not edit Niflheim beads or Niflheim implementation code.\n- Do not duplicate the low-level index-contention fix tracked by `ddx-2965925e`; reuse or align with it.\n- Do not duplicate the post-commit review/land timeout work tracked by `ddx-b2846610`; this bead requires typed classification and review evidence, not another timeout implementation.\n- Do not duplicate the repeated pre-claim warn operator-attention bead `ddx-d67f124e`; this bead uses the Niflheim observation as cross-scenario regression coverage.\n- Do not implement a full operator-lane product workflow beyond the state transitions/events needed to keep the worker from blind retry or false close.\n\nINTERSECTIONS\n- Parent: `ddx-3106674f` (multi-worker hardening and local reliability gates). This bead is the external Niflheim regression/incident closure layer under that reliability epic.\n- Dependency: `ddx-2965925e` covers tracker commit index contention. This bead must not reimplement that fix; it must prove land/ref/index/evidence failures classify separately from model failure once the low-level path is hardened.\n- Dependency: `ddx-b2846610` covers bounded post-commit review/land. This bead must still require typed review/land outcomes after the timeout wedge is fixed.\n- Dependency: `ddx-d67f124e` covers same-fingerprint pre-claim warning escalation. This bead adds the Niflheim `niflheim-a62d31ce` family as regression evidence.\n- Related but not a dependency: `ddx-e1a576a7` is an execution-ineligible decomposed parent and a local precedent for the `niflheim-64217cc5` class.\n- Related quality framework: `ddx-a9d130d0` and `ddx-ac10e7af` own broader bead lifecycle/operator-lane policy; this bead is concrete worker behavior and evidence gating.","events_attachment":"ddx-334c0958/events.jsonl","execution-eligible":false,"id":"ddx-334c0958","issue_type":"bug","labels":["adr:024","area:agent","area:execute-bead","area:review","area:workers","incident:niflheim-2026-06-06","kind:bug","kind:reliability","phase:iterate","prevention","severity:critical","spec:FEAT-010","spec:TP-021"],"notes":"decomposed into ddx-044cd257, ddx-3a6f1ad6, ddx-d4817c9b, ddx-01aa7b18, ddx-1865eadc","parent":"ddx-3106674f","priority":0,"queue-rank":1850,"schema_version":1,"spec-id":"FEAT-010","status":"closed","title":"execute-bead worker: gate success on review evidence and classify Niflheim retry failures","updated_at":"2026-06-17T20:08:03.826920996Z","work-no-changes-count":1}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:465:{"acceptance":"1. **Root cause #1 fixed:** `attempted[candidate.ID] = struct{}{}` is moved to AFTER the pre-claim hook succeeds. Regression test in `execute_bead_loop_test.go` asserts: with a fake `PreClaimHook` that fails on the first call and succeeds thereafter, the loop processes the same bead on the second iteration (not skipped because of stale `attempted` state).\n\n2. **Root cause #2 fixed:** the post-`Execute` outcome-handling block (lines ~510-862) does not exit the loop on transient `Store.*` errors. Each `return result, err` in that block is converted to: log the error, emit a `kind:loop-error` bead event when possible, set the bead to a short cooldown, and `continue` to the next iteration. The only exception is context cancellation (`ctx.Err()`), which still terminates immediately.\n\n3. **Regression tests for AC-2:** for each `Store.*` call in the outcome block (Unclaim, IncrNoChangesCount, adjudicateNoChanges, CloseWithEvidence on each path, Reopen on each path, SetExecutionCooldown on each path, late AppendEvent), a test injects a transient error from a fake store and asserts: (a) the loop continues, (b) a `kind:loop-error` event is recorded with the failing operation name, (c) `result.Failures++` advances.\n\n4. **End-to-end reproduction guard:** an integration test seeds a bead.jsonl with 3 ready beads. The first returns `no_changes` (executor fake), the second returns `success`, the third returns `already_satisfied`. The loop runs to completion (all three processed) without exiting prematurely. With the pre-fix loop, this test fails on the first bead.\n\n5. **Worker-state semantics preserved:** existing tests that assert worker.State transitions (`running` → `exited` / `failed` / `stopped` / `reaped`) still pass. The fix changes loop *advancement*, not terminal-state classification.\n\n6. **Documented behavior:** `docs/agents/work.md` (or the closest existing doc) gains a \"loop termination\" section listing the only conditions that terminate the loop: context cancellation, `Once == true`, `PollInterval \u003c= 0` AND `nextCandidate` returns no candidate, `RoutePreflight` rejected. Explicitly states that Store errors during outcome handling do NOT terminate the loop.\n\n7. **Operator workaround retired:** the README's \"if `ddx work` exits early, restart it\" guidance (or equivalent) is removed; that workaround was masking this bug.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"1495ba706ffdc0e7bfb4833487ed068ffe732aeb","created_at":"2026-04-29T19:05:38.552407002Z","description":"## Symptom\n\n`ddx work` (no `--once` flag, no `--poll-interval`, default mode) exits after processing exactly one bead instead of draining the queue. Reproduced four times today on `/home/erik/Projects/agent` with `--harness lmstudio` pinned (which sidesteps the unrelated `ddx-c7081f89` server-worker tier-walk issue):\n\n| Run | Outcome on first bead | Worker terminal state | Queue still non-empty? |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 2 | `already_satisfied` (`agent-4aa3584e` adjudicated satisfied) | `already_satisfied` / `exited` | yes — 2 ready beads remained |\n| 3 | pre-claim hook rejected (diverged branch) | `exited`, attempts=0 | yes |\n| 4 | pre-claim hook rejected (diverged branch) | `exited`, attempts=0 | yes |\n| 5 | `no_changes` from agent (`agent-6c7a4c11` declined as epic; bead left **claimed**) | `exited`, attempts=1 | yes — 5 ready beads remained |\n\nIn all four runs the loop should have continued to the next ready bead. Per `agent/.claude/skills/ddx/reference/work.md`, only `success`/`already_satisfied` close the bead and `no_changes`/`land_conflict`/`*_failed` unclaim and continue. None of these outcomes is documented or expected to be loop-terminal.\n\n## Root cause #1 (verified)\n\n`cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:382`:\n\n```go\nattempted[candidate.ID] = struct{}{}\n\n// Pre-claim hook: fetch origin + verify ancestry before claiming.\n// On error the bead is skipped for this iteration; the loop\n// continues (ctx is not cancelled).\nif runtime.PreClaimHook != nil {\n    if hookErr := runtime.PreClaimHook(ctx); hookErr != nil {\n        // ... log + emit ...\n        continue\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThe bead is added to `attempted` **before** the pre-claim hook runs. On hook failure (e.g. diverged branch), the loop `continue`s but the bead stays in `attempted`. Next iteration, `nextCandidate()` (line 924) skips the still-ready bead because it's in `attempted`, returns `ok=false`, and the loop exits at line 374 because `PollInterval \u003c= 0`. Single-shot exit with `attempts=0`.\n\n**Reproduces:** runs 3 and 4 above.\n\n## Root cause #2 (suspected — needs targeted instrumentation)\n\nRuns 2 and 5 reached `Execute()` and got a real report back. Worker log shows the entry line `▶ \u003cbead\u003e: \u003ctitle\u003e` but no closing `✓ \u003cbead\u003e → \u003cresult\u003e` line (which is written at line 909). That means the loop exited somewhere between line 488 (`Executor.Execute`) and line 909 (the final summary log).\n\nBetween those bounds, **at least 16 distinct `return result, err` points** trigger if any `Store.*` operation returns an error: `Unclaim` (711, 700), `IncrNoChangesCount` (717), `adjudicateNoChanges` (721), `CloseWithEvidence` (520, 615, 694, 739), `Reopen` (635, 669), `SetExecutionCooldown` (749, 791, 803, 835, 844), late `AppendEvent` (862). Any single transient store error during outcome handling kills the worker.\n\nFor run 5 specifically, `agent-6c7a4c11` is now `Status: in_progress` with `Owner: ddx, Machine: sindri`. The bead was **never unclaimed** despite the agent returning `no_changes` — meaning the loop exited on or before line 711 (`w.Store.Unclaim`) failing. Investigation should look at what error `Unclaim` would return when called against a bead the same worker claimed seconds earlier; possible candidates: tracker-write race with concurrent worker, bead.jsonl re-write during a fetch by the pre-claim hook on a later iteration that already happened (no — pre-claim is pre-claim, not post-execute), or a malformed bead row that fails store-side validation.\n\nIndependent of the specific store error: the structural pattern of \"any Store.* error → exit the entire loop\" is the wrong default. A store error on outcome handling should at most park the bead and continue to the next, never terminate the worker.\n\n## Why this is loadbearing\n\nThe loop is the queue-drain primitive. Every observed failure-to-drain in the last 24 hours of operator complaints traces back to this — beads that should have been the worker's second/third/fourth attempt never got picked up because the worker exited after one attempt, and the operator manually restarts the drain (sometimes after a long delay). The visible queue depth is misleading: half the \"ready\" beads are sitting behind a worker that quietly died.\n\n## In-scope files\n\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go` — fixes for both root causes\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop_test.go` — regression tests for each path\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- Anything in the `agent` SDK (`/home/erik/Projects/agent`). The loop and all its store interactions are owned by ddx.\n- The pre-claim hook's divergence-detection logic itself — that's correct behavior; the bug is how the loop reacts to the hook's signal.\n- Adaptive min-tier / tier-walk machinery (`ddx-c7081f89`, `ddx-aec9d68c`) — independent.\n\n## Anti-goals\n\n- Do **not** swallow store errors silently. They must be surfaced (event + log) but should not kill the worker on transient/per-bead failures.\n- Do **not** convert the loop's Once/PollInterval semantics — they're correct.\n- Do **not** change worker terminal-state semantics (`exited`/`failed`/`stopped`/`reaped`).","events_attachment":"ddx-37cdb43a/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-37cdb43a","issue_type":"bug","labels":["area:work","kind:bug","phase:fix"],"notes":"REVIEW:BLOCK\n\nDiff only contains execution evidence (manifest.json + result.json) under .ddx/executions/. No changes to execute_bead_loop.go, tests, or docs are visible, so none of the 7 acceptance criteria can be evaluated as implemented.","priority":0,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-842ed336","status":"closed","title":"work: ddx work exits after one bead instead of draining the queue","updated_at":"2026-04-30T00:04:15.728726551Z","work-no-changes-count":1}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:471:{"acceptance":"1. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./... passes.\n2. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-07-02T22:52:12Z","created_at":"2026-06-07T02:17:59.120820292Z","description":"PROBLEM\nParent bead ddx-130cf9ab is too broad for one execution pass. This child owns part 3 of 3 of that parent scope.\n\nROOT CAUSE\nPROBLEM\nParent bead ddx-e19185aa is too broad for one execution pass. This child owns part 2 of 3 of that parent scope.\n\nROOT CAUSE\nThe decomposition action (currently invoked when a bead is too large for one execution and the agent splits it into child beads) is writing the parent's ID as a dep edge on every child. This produces an unbreakable deadlock:\n\n  e29892a4 (parent, open) -- parent --\u003e child_A\n  e29892a4 -- parent --\u003e child_B\n  child_A.deps = [e29892a4]           \u003c- BAD: parent is also a dep\n  child_B.deps = [child_A, e29892a4]  \u003c- BAD\n\nThe parent stays open until its children close. Every child is blocked on the parent. Nothing can be claimed. ddx work loops on the parent, the orchestrator emits 'mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale', the worker retries, and burns claim budget without progress.\n\nObserved scenario (niflheim, 2026-06-04 04:30-05:13 UTC):\n- Parent: niflheim-e29892a4 ('feat(delta): async write-behind ...')\n- 10 children created during planning loops (23223661, a44a8ceb, 054c89b7, 0470ba0d, f10e9e35, f076b08c, 6c041162, 94e1df73, 9da62c2d, 5e4f9fb2)\n- Every child carried deps=[..siblings.., niflheim-e29892a4]\n- ~50 minutes of agent time + 4 strong-policy claude/opus attempts with zero feature commits; only tracker chores\n- Unwedged manually by closing the parent via 'ddx bead close', after which siblings drained correctly in foundational order\n\nRoot cause is structural, not model-capability — auto-upgrading to a stronger model does NOT fix this. The orchestrator already detects the no-progress state but its only remediation is 'retry parent', which re-enters the same loop.\n\nThere is also a 'project root mutation rejected (continuing)' warning emitted by the readiness check during this state; that's a downstream symptom of the same problem, not the cause.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nImplement only this child acceptance slice:\n- Programmatic decomposition path (the action that fans a too-large bead into children) MUST NOT add the parent as a dep. Existing action templates / system prompts are audited and amended; one golden e2e test (decompose_does_not_self_dep) creates a bead with N children and asserts every child's deps set excludes the parent.\n- 'ddx bead doctor' (existing subcommand) gains a check 'parent_ancestor_in_deps' that scans the tracker, lists violating beads, and (with --fix) removes the offending edges. Output is stable / scriptable.\n...[truncated]\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nImplement only this child acceptance slice:\n- cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./... passes.\n- lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n\nNON-SCOPE\nDo not implement parent acceptance criteria assigned to sibling child beads. Preserve every parent non-scope constraint unless this child explicitly narrows it.","events_attachment":"ddx-3892c623/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-3892c623","issue_type":"task","labels":["ac-quality:needs-refinement","area:decomposition","area:lifecycle","area:tracker","decomposed","kind:correctness","kind:safety"],"needs-human-reason":"description is truncated — part-3 implementation scope is hidden","needs-human-since":"2026-06-17T19:25:21Z","needs-human-source":"ddx work","needs-human-suggested-action":"review intake result and accept, rewrite, split, block, or cancel","needs-human-summary":"pre-claim intake blocked execution","parent":"ddx-130cf9ab","priority":0,"queue-rank":1900,"schema_version":1,"status":"closed","title":"Reject bead dep edges that re-introduce the parent or any ancestor: part: part 3","updated_at":"2026-06-17T20:06:07.697695301Z","work-no-changes-count":6}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:493:{"acceptance":"1. Loop has triage step after each attempt's terminal event. 2. Per-failure-mode triage policy in .ddx/config.yaml. 3. Triage outcomes (re-attempt-with-context, escalate-tier, needs_human) align exactly with TD-031 TriageContract (per ddx-673833f4). **No new persisted statuses introduced — all triage state lives in labels (e.g., triage:needs-human) and events per bd/br compatibility (ADR-004).** 4. Default: BLOCK→re-attempt-with-context, then escalate-tier, then add 'triage:needs-human' label. 5. Lock-error handling delegates to ddx-da11a34a's implementation; this bead does NOT duplicate retry/backoff logic. Triage policy entry for lock errors invokes the lock-bead's published API. 6. Tests: BLOCK→re-attempt, BLOCK→escalate, lock-error→delegates-to-lock-bead, no_changes→re-evaluate. 7. Out of scope: rate-limit handling, quota-pause handling, lock-retry implementation, status-enum modification. 8. needs_human stays a LABEL per current code (cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_review_triage.go:19-23) and TD's resolution. 9. **schema_compat_test.go round-trip passes after this bead lands.**","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"4221a8f3596a23aedd4bab355865d023c9b3f344","created_at":"2026-05-02T13:04:11.868818227Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-3c154349","depends_on_id":"ddx-673833f4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-02T18:14:01Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-3c154349","depends_on_id":"ddx-7d7a17c8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-02T19:04:17Z"}],"description":"Currently when a bead hits a post-merge review BLOCK, the drain loop emits the BLOCK event, leaves the bead open, and moves to the next ready bead. The BLOCK then sits in the queue waiting for a human. Same for many substantive execution_failed cases — no automated triage.\n\nThis bead handles BLOCK + substantive failures only. Two SEPARATE beads cover related-but-distinct concerns:\n- ddx-aede917d: drain pause/resume on quota exhaustion (Fizeau-side state, DDx consumes typed error)\n- ddx-c6e3db02: per-bead rate-limit retry honoring Retry-After (provider stays in rotation)\n\nFailure modes triaged HERE:\n- post-merge review BLOCK → either (a) re-attempt-with-context (BLOCK reasons embedded in next prompt), (b) escalate to next tier in the S10_2 ladder, or (c) file follow-up bead capturing BLOCK reasons + mark original needs_human\n- 'staging tracker: Unable to create .git/index.lock' (git contention — see  / ddx-da11a34a) → retry with backoff after lock clears\n- substantive execution_failed (probe_ok+exec_fail; agent finished but produced no useful diff or wrong shape) → escalate per S10 ladder\n- 'no_changes' (agent decided nothing to do) → re-evaluate against the bead AC; if still seems valid, file a clarification follow-up rather than mark already_satisfied\n\nTriage policy is config-driven, per-failure-mode mapping in .ddx/config.yaml triage:. Default: BLOCK→re-attempt-with-context, then escalate-tier on second BLOCK, then needs_human on third.\n\nNOT in scope: rate-limit handling (ddx-c6e3db02) and quota-pause handling (ddx-aede917d) — those are separate beads with their own infrastructure.","events_attachment":"ddx-3c154349/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-3c154349","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2","story:10","area:agent","kind:fix","observed-failure"],"notes":"decomposed into 3 children: framework (.execute-bead-wt-ddx-3c154349-20260502T131050-bf2d17f5-0a700bd2), review-block integration (.execute-bead-wt-ddx-3c154349-20260502T131050-bf2d17f5-5f67936e), lock/execution_failed/no_changes integration (.execute-bead-wt-ddx-3c154349-20260502T131050-bf2d17f5-2b64cb0a). Children 2 and 3 depend on child 1.\n\nREVIEW:BLOCK\n\nDiff contains only execution manifest/result metadata for the parent bead. No source changes implementing triage step, config policy, BLOCK re-attempt, lock retry, or tests. Parent was decomposed into 3 children; implementation lives there, not here.","parent":"ddx-e34994e2","priority":1,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-7ec1c8ee","status":"closed","title":"ddx work: auto-triage on review BLOCK + substantive execution failures","updated_at":"2026-05-03T21:54:33.582788548Z","work-no-changes-count":2}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:494:{"acceptance":"execute-bead prompt contract explicitly invites no_changes with a rationale. The fake-agent test harness seeds a no_changes rationale file; execute_bead_test.go asserts ExecuteBeadResult.NoChangesRationale is populated; work uses the rationale to classify 'already_satisfied' when it references a prior commit SHA or test name; the rendered log (ddx server workers log) shows the rationale on its own line; 'agent made no commits' no longer appears without context.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","claimed-at":"2026-04-14T08:21:48Z","claimed-machine":"eitri","claimed-pid":"1412283","closing_commit_sha":"f495bf65ad5e6906f85e7c5260ce12f8c76a20be","created_at":"2026-04-14T04:03:21.715664968Z","description":"Today when execute-bead exits with no_changes, the operator sees 'agent made no commits' and nothing else. That's useless for triage — the operator cannot tell whether:\\n- the bead is genuinely already satisfied (work present in a prior commit)\\n- the agent gave up because it couldn't find the relevant files\\n- the agent classified the task as ambiguous or too risky\\n- the agent hit a tool limit or context cap\\n- the prompt contract was unclear\\n\\nThe fix is to make no_changes a structured result that carries a short rationale from the agent itself, written at the point where the agent decided not to commit. Example of what the operator should see:\\n\\n  status:    no_changes\\n  rationale: The epic filter requested by this bead was already added in\\n             commit 1da6495 (cli/internal/bead/store.go readyFiltered). I\\n             reviewed the current code and tests, confirmed the filter\\n             excludes 'epic' beads from ReadyExecution, and verified\\n             TestReadyExecutionExcludesEpics exists and passes. Nothing\\n             to do. Ref: 1da6495, TestReadyExecutionExcludesEpics.\\n\\nThis is specifically the case that motivated this bead: a continuous-drain worker processed ddx-b44ca394 ('Prevent work from launching open epics by default') after the epic filter had already been implemented on main. The agent instead made a synthesized no-op commit that only retargeted 17 .claude/skills/helix-* symlinks, which the loop classified as 'success' because a commit was produced. Had no_changes carried a rationale pointing at the prior commit, the loop could have closed the bead as 'already_satisfied' and moved on cleanly.\\n\\nScope:\\n1. Execute-bead prompt contract must explicitly instruct the agent: if you determine the bead's work is already present or cannot be done, report that in a structured way — do NOT make a synthesized commit to 'land something'. Today the prompt says 'Making no commits (no_changes) should be rare' which actively pushes agents toward the wrong behavior.\\n2. The agent's exit mechanism needs a way to carry a rationale string back. Simplest version: the agent writes a file to the worktree like .ddx/executions/\u003cattempt-id\u003e/no_changes_rationale.txt before exiting. ExecuteBead reads it if no commits were produced and attaches the text to the result.NoChangesRationale field.\\n3. The ExecuteBeadResult struct gains a NoChangesRationale string field, populated only when outcome == no_changes. Status: success and the unused 'reason' field need not change.\\n4. work close semantics: when no_changes arrives with a non-empty rationale pointing at a prior commit, the loop can optionally close the bead as already_satisfied with the rationale recorded in the close event body (instead of waiting for MaxNoChangesBeforeClose=3 strikes). Gate this behind a 'rationale references existing commit' heuristic to avoid flapping — if the rationale is a vague 'nothing to do', keep current cooldown behavior.\\n5. ddx server worker log should render the rationale prominently, not bury it in session metadata.\\n6. The prompt contract note that no_changes should be 'rare' is replaced with: 'If the work is already present, say so and provide a reference (commit SHA, test name, file path). A well-justified no_changes is always preferred to a cosmetic synthesized commit.'","events_attachment":"ddx-3c30bfa2/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-3c30bfa2","issue_type":"task","owner":"ddx","priority":1,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-reconcile-f495bf6","status":"closed","title":"no_changes reports must include a rationale the operator can act on","updated_at":"2026-04-14T14:12:46.040411073Z","work-heartbeat-at":"2026-04-14T08:43:48.707134432Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:534:{"acceptance":"1. TestExecuteBeadRejectsTopLevelSampleChildBeads simulates an execute-bead Step 0 agent running `ddx bead create \"Sample: lint cleanup\"` without parent metadata and proves the real tracker is not polluted with an open top-level bead.\n2. TestExecuteBeadDecompositionRequiresCurrentParent creates a legitimate child through the execute-bead decomposition path and proves the child parent equals the current bead ID, labels/spec-id are inherited, and invalid parentless children are rejected or quarantined.\n3. TestWorkStatusDropsStaleRunStateWhenWorkerPidGone creates a run-state record for a dead worker pid and proves `ddx work status --json` does not report it as active work after cleanup.\n4. Invalid execute-bead child creation emits durable operator_attention evidence with child IDs, attempted title, parent value, and rejection reason.\n5. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./cmd/... ./internal/agent/... -run 'TestExecuteBeadRejectsTopLevelSampleChildBeads|TestExecuteBeadDecompositionRequiresCurrentParent|TestWorkStatusDropsStaleRunStateWhenWorkerPidGone' passes.\n6. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-07-02T22:52:12Z","closing_commit_sha":"1b41b22bba8872069672d35d4ebffeb6ef795573","created_at":"2026-06-13T16:16:29.347711662Z","description":"PROBLEM\nDuring the 2026-06-13 dogfood run for ddx-aef128f7, an interrupted `ddx work` execution polluted the real DDx tracker with 20 top-level open beads titled `Sample: ...` (`ddx-5d26dc27`, `ddx-37dd1bef`, `ddx-e7f8ad72`, `ddx-2a77ac3f`, `ddx-d369d255`, `ddx-9646569a`, `ddx-3cf17faf`, `ddx-541bf722`, `ddx-e9384053`, `ddx-2a5286ae`, `ddx-fb8f9a90`, `ddx-552ec9c5`, `ddx-86e2a4ce`, `ddx-0b369a91`, `ddx-2eed7ae3`, `ddx-8c6abcc2`, `ddx-e64dea54`, `ddx-6479485f`, `ddx-8fbd3aba`, `ddx-10c17c2d`). I cancelled those bogus beads through `ddx bead update --status cancelled`, but the worker should never have been able to create them in the landing tracker.\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\ncli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:1885-1903 tells execute-bead agents that Step 0 may run `ddx bead create` for decomposition. cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:1981-1984 reiterates that Step 0 allows bead creation while current-bead lifecycle stays orchestrator-owned. The prompt requires `parent=\u003cparent-id\u003e`, but DDx does not enforce that an execute-bead-created child has the current bead as parent, inherits required labels/spec-id, or writes a valid `no_changes_rationale.txt` before mutating the real landing tracker. The dogfood attempt created top-level sample fixtures instead.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- Add a guarded decomposition command/path for execute-bead Step 0, or validate all bead-create mutations made from an execution worktree before they reach the landing tracker.\n- Reject or quarantine execute-bead-created beads whose title/description/AC look like sample fixtures, whose parent is empty or not the current bead, or whose required inherited labels/spec-id are absent.\n- Add cleanup/recovery that parks or cancels invalid child beads automatically and records an operator_attention event naming the invalid IDs.\n- Ensure stale run-state from a killed worker does not keep `ddx work status` reporting active work after the owning worker process is gone.\n\nNON-SCOPE\nDo not remove legitimate Step 0 decomposition. Do not rewrite or delete tracker history manually. Do not change normal operator-invoked `ddx bead create` behavior outside execute-bead/work execution contexts.\n\nINTERSECTIONS\n- ddx-aef128f7: the same aborted run also proved process-tree cleanup failures.\n- ddx-6d9a8bdb: the same run also proved pinned-provider escape.","id":"ddx-42124c23","issue_type":"bug","labels":["phase:build","area:work","area:beads","area:agent","kind:bug","kind:reliability","severity:critical","plan:server-managed-workers"],"parent":"ddx-9d1af129","priority":0,"queue-rank":"-90","schema_version":1,"spec-id":"IP-2026-06-13-server-managed-workers","status":"closed","title":"work: prevent execute-bead from polluting queue with sample child beads","triage.estimated_difficulty":"hard","updated_at":"2026-06-13T17:11:12.293723582Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:589:{"acceptance":"1. New test cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... -run TestAlreadySatisfiedRequiresAcStructuralCheck covers: bead with AC naming TestX; worker run does not exercise TestX; classification is NOT already_satisfied (instead no_changes or new ac_unmet class).\n2. Test covers: bead with AC naming a deleted file path; file still exists; classification is NOT already_satisfied.\n3. Test covers: bead with AC asserting a struct does not have field Y; field still exists; classification is NOT already_satisfied.\n4. Test covers: positive case — bead with AC naming TestX; worker run exercises TestX and TestX passes; AC structural property holds; classification IS already_satisfied (no regression).\n5. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./... -count=1 passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"5c8d9944ba65f86202c18b34a6b0dcc510c1f530","created_at":"2026-04-26T00:13:36.74476781Z","description":"Observed across multiple beads in agent v0.9.9 / v0.9.10 work (2026-04-25): worker classifies bead as already_satisfied when the regression test suite passes, even when the bead's acceptance criteria explicitly name structural test functions or properties that the implementation has not exercised.\n\n## Concrete instances\n\n- agent-9d120ece (route resolution): AC #1 was structural ('cmd/agent no longer contains provider-building helpers or route-provider wrapper types that depend on internal/core'). Regression tests passed because the AC also named a regression command. Bead closed already_satisfied — but cmd/agent/routing_provider.go and cmd/agent/provider_build.go still contained the forbidden helpers. False close.\n- agent-1023f072 (boundary tightening): same pattern earlier — AC structural property unmet, regression command passing, close.\n- agent-d9c358ba (smart-routing wiring): worker analysis correctly identified the bead was too broad and split it. Status still classified already_satisfied which is misleading — 'split deferred' is a different outcome from 'AC was already met.'\n\n## Principle\n\nalready_satisfied should mean: 'the AC's specific test functions or named structural properties were exercised and produced the asserted outcome without any code change in this attempt.' It should NOT mean: 'some unrelated regression command passed.'\n\nIf the AC names test functions (e.g. 'go test . -run TestX'), those tests must have run during the worker's verification step. If the AC names a structural property (e.g. 'no field X', 'file Y deleted', 'ProviderEntry.SupportsTools is OR-permissive'), the property must be checked.\n\n## Suggested fix\n\nParse the bead's acceptance criteria during worker verification. Extract:\n- Named test function references ('TestFoo', 'go test . -run TestFoo')\n- File-existence claims ('file X deleted', 'no longer contains')\n- AST-level claims ('field X removed', 'no import of Y')\n\nFor already_satisfied to be valid:\n- All named test functions must exist and pass.\n- All file-existence claims must hold via filesystem check.\n- AST-level claims must hold via parser pass.\n\nIf any check fails, classify as no_changes (or a new outcome class like ac_unmet_no_changes) so the loop unclaims and tries again rather than closing the bead.\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- Changes to the success / land_conflict / execution_failed / review_request_changes outcome classes.\n- Adding new structural-claim parsers beyond what the AC explicitly names.\n- Automatic AC-claim extraction beyond test names + file paths + simple AST patterns. Free-form prose stays operator-judgment territory.\n\n## Cross-reference\n\nDiscipline rule documented in agent repo AGENTS.md 'Review and Verification Discipline' section. Local mitigation (verify before accept, reopen with notes) caught three false closes in this session.","events_attachment":"ddx-4a751095/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-4a751095","issue_type":"bug","labels":["ddx","kind:bug","area:agent","area:work","area:harness"],"priority":2,"schema_version":1,"status":"closed","title":"work: tighten already_satisfied gate to require AC structural test name match","updated_at":"2026-04-28T02:47:46.245296011Z","work-last-detail":"no_changes","work-last-status":"no_changes","work-no-changes-count":3,"work-retry-after":"2026-04-28T07:35:37Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:616:{"acceptance":"1. Remove or demote RoutingMetricsStore consumers from provider availability, quota, route-status, and agent usage decisions; DDx must use Fizeau service ListHarnesses/ListProviders/RouteStatus/RecordRouteAttempt for those semantics.\n2. cli/internal/server/providers.go no longer reports stats-cache, quota-snapshot, http-balance, http-models, recent-session-log, or ddx-metrics as current provider signal sources unless they are direct Fizeau-provided source names with matching semantics.\n3. cli/cmd/agent_route_status.go no longer merges routing-outcomes.jsonl into current routing availability/status.\n4. cli/cmd/agent_usage.go does not infer current quota/headroom from DDx routing-outcomes.jsonl or burn-summaries.jsonl. Historical audit display remains allowed if clearly labeled audit-only.\n5. Tests cover stale local cache data not affecting provider quota/availability/status.\n6. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./cmd ./internal/agent ./internal/server/... passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"db188e91bfab3462af3d5fe073c43ffd4be3f401","created_at":"2026-05-05T01:36:05.000950891Z","description":"PROBLEM\nDDx still has local usage/routing cache consumers after the provider-native parser removal bead closed. These paths can contradict Fizeau route/status semantics and preserve stale source names like stats-cache, quota-snapshot, ddx-metrics, routing-outcomes, and burn-summaries.\n\nEVIDENCE\n- cli/internal/agent/routing_metrics.go still defines RoutingMetricsStore and reads/writes routing-outcomes.jsonl and burn-summaries.jsonl.\n- cli/cmd/agent_usage.go reads RoutingMetricsStore for agent usage enrichment.\n- cli/cmd/agent_route_status.go merges RoutingMetricsStore data into route status.\n- cli/internal/server/providers.go reads RoutingMetricsStore and maps stats-cache/quota-snapshot/http-balance/http-models/recent-session-log into provider signal sources.\n- cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go still emits stats-cache as a signal kind.\n- Existing removal bead ddx-3610f1fc is closed and only covered the old parser/health-shadow layer.\n\nGOAL\nMake DDx a thin consumer of Fizeau service routing/status data. DDx may keep execution logs for audit, but provider availability/quota/current usage must not be derived from stale DDx-side cache files or provider-native cache labels.","events_attachment":"ddx-4d81bb26/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-4d81bb26","issue_type":"task","labels":["area:agent","area:routing","kind:cleanup","thin-consumer","triage:no-changes-unjustified"],"priority":0,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-b46edbe9","status":"closed","title":"Remove remaining DDx-side usage/quota cache consumers","updated_at":"2026-05-05T18:00:07.912081799Z","work-last-detail":"agent exited without a commit or no_changes_rationale.txt; dirty paths: cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go, cli/cmd/agent_route_status.go, cli/cmd/agent_route_status_test.go, cli/cmd/agent_usage.go, cli/internal/server/providers.go, cli/internal/server/providers_test.go","work-last-status":"no_changes","work-no-changes-count":2,"work-retry-after":"2026-05-05T07:52:13Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:622:{"acceptance":"AC1. When an execute-bead session exits without committing in the worktree AND without writing .ddx/executions/\u003cid\u003e/no_changes_rationale.txt, the harness records a NEW dedicated status (e.g. 'agent_silent_exit' or 'no_evidence_produced') instead of letting ddx-land-coordinator land an iteration containing only execution evidence.\n\nAC2. The codex reviewer's BLOCK rationale ('change set only adds execution metadata files') becomes redundant — the harness catches this case before the reviewer is even invoked, saving a redundant review pass and its cost.\n\nAC3. The execute-bead prompt template is updated so the rationale-on-incomplete-work instruction is harder to skip — ideally a tool the agent must invoke (e.g. SubmitNoChangesRationale tool) rather than 'write a file and exit'.\n\nAC4. When the agent did run Edit tool calls but the worktree has no commit, the harness logs a warning naming each file the agent edited that is now uncommitted, so operators can recover the work or diagnose the silent-commit-failure.\n\nAC5. Documentation in docs/ explains the agent-self-commit contract, the rationale-file fallback, and the new 'agent_silent_exit' classification.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","claimed-at":"2026-04-30T12:43:25Z","claimed-machine":"sindri","claimed-pid":"3967690","closing_commit_sha":"cedf316fc6d5082eff11bff2f38ee5618958b20f","created_at":"2026-04-30T00:10:22.985451193Z","description":"Observed today across 5 attempts on the axon repo (claude/sonnet, claude/opus, codex/gpt-5.4-mini): the agent does real work in the worktree (multiple Edit tool calls touching real source files) but never runs git commit. Result: iteration commit is built by ddx-land-coordinator with ONLY execution-evidence files (.ddx/executions/\u003cid\u003e/result.json, manifest.json, usage.json), no actual code or doc changes. The post-merge codex reviewer correctly flags BLOCK with rationale 'change set only adds execution metadata files'.\n\nConcrete evidence (axon repo, 2026-04-29):\n\n  Attempt: 20260429T235353-d14f6b91 (axon-80979cb8 / A1 sub-bead)\n  Harness: claude / model: sonnet\n  Duration: 817 sec, cost $3.61, 132 tool calls\n  Tool breakdown: 79 Bash, 34 Read, 11 Grep, 8 Edit\n  Edit targets: ui/src/lib/api.ts, ui/src/lib/policy-evaluator.ts,\n    ui/src/routes/.../policies/+page.svelte, ui/tests/e2e/link-policy-retry.spec.ts\n  Iteration commit (ddx-land-coordinator): contains exactly 2 files —\n    .ddx/executions/20260429T235353-d14f6b91/result.json (23 lines)\n    .ddx/executions/20260429T235353-d14f6b91/usage.json (9 lines)\n  Net: zero actual edits landed despite $3.61 of model time spent making them.\n\nThe same pattern appeared on:\n  20260429T235406-20eeaf2c (axon-db7a6d0a, claude/sonnet, $0.57, 4.2 min, BLOCK)\n  20260429T190657-fa91f49b (axon-ab2e52e0, openrouter/gpt-5.4-mini, $0.08, 24s, stalled)\n  20260429T190634-579df880 (axon-80979cb8, openrouter/gpt-5.4-mini, $0.12, 104s, BLOCK)\n  20260429T190646-5aa5b46e (axon-db7a6d0a, openrouter/gpt-5.4-mini, $0.06, 25s, BLOCK)\n\nTotal burn today: ~$4.50 across 5 attempts on 3 beads, 0 closed.\n\nThe execute-bead prompt template tells the agent to commit:\n  '4. Commit once, when everything is green. Stage only the files you intentionally changed with git add \u003cspecific-paths\u003e...'\n\nSo agent self-commit is the contract. But:\n\n(a) When typecheck/lint/test fails, the agent is told to fix or write no_changes_rationale.txt — but apparently many agents are bailing silently without writing the rationale either, so the harness sees a clean worktree (no diff staged or committed) and treats it as 'agent made no commits'. The iteration then carries only the auto-generated execution evidence.\n\n(b) There may also be a path where the agent commits but a pre-commit hook silently rejects it. Have not confirmed; the worktree was reaped before I could inspect.\n\nThe issue spans multiple harnesses (claude, codex via embedded openrouter), so it is not specific to one provider's commit semantics. Either:\n  - The harness should reject 'agent made no commits AND no no_changes_rationale.txt' as a separate failure class instead of silently letting ddx-land-coordinator land an empty iteration\n  - The agent prompt should make rationale-writing on incomplete work non-optional with stronger language\n  - The harness should run a final-stage check 'did the agent produce ANY signal — commit OR rationale — and if not, treat as harness-execution-failed and surface to the operator'","id":"ddx-4e0a4a59","issue_type":"bug","labels":["area:agent","area:harness","area:execute-bead","kind:correctness"],"owner":"erik","priority":1,"schema_version":1,"status":"closed","title":"execute-bead: agents make edits but skip git commit; iteration commits land only execution evidence","updated_at":"2026-04-30T12:43:46.370829758Z","work-heartbeat-at":"2026-04-30T12:43:25.451101407Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:687:{"acceptance":"- [ ] Test asserts that a bead with empty governing IDs merges via the interactive path with RequiredExecSummary == \"skipped\" (or empty) and no GateResults\n- [ ] Test asserts the same for the server-managed coordinator path\n- [ ] Tests live in the same package(s) as the per-path regression coverage so they run in the same suite","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"a320445041f89d66dfb5b8804d4e636edaed1f75","created_at":"2026-04-18T19:10:41.632060085Z","description":"Cross-cutting safety net for the gate-wiring epic. After ddx-14c0e790 (interactive) and ddx-e437ebc1 (server) land, confirm a single fixture exercises a bead with NO governing IDs through both code paths and observes the legacy \"merged\" outcome with no gate evaluation invoked. May be foldable into the per-path tests above; file as standalone so the no-regression promise is explicit and discoverable. Close as already_satisfied if 14c0e790 + e437ebc1 fixtures fully cover the no-gate case.","id":"ddx-580f0193","issue_type":"task","labels":["ddx","area:agent","area:exec","kind:test"],"parent":"ddx-3e7f8213","priority":2,"schema_version":1,"status":"closed","title":"Backward-compat regression: no-gate beads still mergeable across both managed paths","updated_at":"2026-04-19T16:56:50.598399961Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:698:{"acceptance":"1. Node(id) at cli/internal/server/graphql/resolver_node.go resolves Bead IDs (prefix \"bead-\") via the bead store scoped to context WorkingDir.\n2. Node(id) resolves Execution run IDs (prefix \"exec-\" or whatever the run-id format is) via the executions store scoped to context WorkingDir.\n3. Returns nil + appropriate error for IDs that don't match any known prefix.\n4. Test: TestNode_ResolvesBeadByID_ScopedToProject — register two projects with overlapping bead IDs; query Node(\"bead-X\") via project A's scoped GraphQL; assert returns project A's bead, not B's.\n5. Test: TestNode_ResolvesExecRunByID_ScopedToProject — same shape for execution runs.\n6. Test: TestNode_ReturnsNilForUnknownPrefix — assert no panic, nil returned.\n7. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/server/graphql/... green; lefthook pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","created_at":"2026-05-03T01:27:08.83276105Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-5ae050dc","depends_on_id":"ddx-4c51d33e","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-03T01:27:15Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-5ae050dc","depends_on_id":"ddx-055e8d32","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-03T01:27:15Z"}],"description":"LAYER 3 of the GraphQL cross-project leak fix. Completeness work — fixes incomplete Relay spec compliance.\n\nPROBLEM\ncli/internal/server/graphql/resolver_node.go:86-101 (Node(id) Relay lookup) returns nil for any ID that isn't \"node-\" or \"proj-\" prefixed. Beads and Executions implement the Node interface in the schema but have no resolver. This breaks Relay clients that expect Node(id) lookup to work for any object type.\n\nLAYER 3 SCOPE\nImplement Node(id) resolution for:\n- Bead IDs (e.g., \"bead-ddx-abc12345\")\n- Execution run IDs (e.g., \"exec-20260502T220000-abc1\")\n\nResolution must respect the current project context (LAYER 2 dependency — without context-based WorkingDir, Node(id) can't scope correctly across projects).\n\nNOT IN SCOPE\n- Adding new node types beyond Bead/Execution\n- Schema changes\n- Backward-compat for clients that currently rely on nil-returning Node(id)\n\nDEP: ddx-4c51d33e (LAYER 1) AND the LAYER 2 bead — Node(id) needs context-based WorkingDir to scope correctly.","events_attachment":"ddx-5ae050dc/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-5ae050dc","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2","area:server","area:graphql","kind:feature","triage:no-changes-unjustified"],"parent":"ddx-e34994e2","priority":3,"schema_version":1,"status":"closed","title":"graphql LAYER 3: implement Bead/Execution Node(id) Relay resolution with project-aware lookups","updated_at":"2026-05-05T03:07:27.229962532Z","work-last-detail":"agent exited without a commit or no_changes_rationale.txt","work-last-status":"no_changes","work-no-changes-count":1,"work-retry-after":"2026-05-05T09:07:26Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:702:{"acceptance":"1. ExecuteBeadReport gains an explicit Disrupted bool (or Disposition variant) set when the loop detects: ctx.Err() != nil, executor exited via SIGKILL/SIGTERM, transport-class provider error, or worker process restart marker.\n2. Detection at: cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go where ExecutionFailed is set (current lines 513 routing-preflight, 629/637 executor-error, 1011 in execute_bead.go) — each set point evaluates whether the failure is Disrupted.\n3. The cooldown branch (lines 1074-1086) checks Disrupted FIRST: if Disrupted, skip SetExecutionCooldown entirely; just Unclaim so the bead returns to ready.\n4. shouldSuppressNoProgress unchanged for genuine no-progress (BaseRev == ResultRev AND not Disrupted AND no rationale).\n5. New diagnostic event `disruption_detected` with kind, reason, and bead context — emitted when Disrupted is set so operators can see disruption rates.\n6. (Optional) Exponential backoff for non-Disrupted no-progress: first failure 5min; second 30min; third 2h; cap at 24h. Reset on success. If implementing: replace flat noProgressCooldown with this curve; document in code comment.\n7. Tests:\n   - TestLoop_DisruptedExecution_NoCooldown — context cancelled mid-execution; assert no work-retry-after set; bead returns to ready\n   - TestLoop_GenuineNoProgress_StillCooldowns — model returns clean with no commit + rationale; assert 6h cooldown set\n   - TestLoop_PreflightRejection_NoCooldown — routing preflight fails; assert disruption classification (operator config, not model failure)\n   - TestLoop_DisruptionEventEmitted — assert disruption_detected event appears in bead events\n8. Manual verification: kill an in-flight worker mid-execution; assert the bead is immediately re-claimable by the next worker (no 6h park).\n9. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... green; lefthook pre-commit passes.\n10. Documentation: update FEAT-006 (or wherever the cooldown policy is documented) to describe Disrupted vs no-progress and the policy rationale.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","claimed-at":"2026-05-03T02:17:24Z","claimed-machine":"eitri","claimed-pid":"163374","closing_commit_sha":"89473d084d436e925934549d31f560e5d6b8702a","created_at":"2026-05-03T01:47:21.609526243Z","description":"The current cooldown logic treats any ExecutionFailed status as evidence the model can't make progress, applying noProgressCooldown=6h when BaseRev == ResultRev (cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:1074-1086 via shouldSuppressNoProgress at line 1550). This silently freezes important work whenever a worker is disrupted (killed, server restart, network blip, OS issue) — disruption produces ExecutionFailed + no commit, indistinguishable from \"model genuinely tried and produced nothing.\"\n\nOBSERVED (today, 2026-05-02)\nAfter the picker fix investigation found the four \"starved\" P0 beads (ddx-dc157075, ddx-aee651ec, ddx-29058e2a, ddx-9d55601f) all had work-retry-after timestamps ~3 hours in the future. Investigation per ddx-9d55601f confirmed these were NOT genuine model failures — they were prior worker disruptions during this development session (worker kills, server restarts) being treated as model-gave-up.\n\nUser directive: \"Cooldown should be reserved for cases where the model is truly unable to make progress on a task.\"\n\nCURRENT COOLDOWN POLICY (cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go)\n- LandConflictCooldown = 15min — short cooldown after merge/land conflicts (line 64)\n- noProgressCooldown = 6h default — when shouldSuppressNoProgress is true (line 367)\n- MaxLoopCooldown = 24h — push_failed, push_conflict, decomposition decline (line 57)\n\nshouldSuppressNoProgress (line 1550): returns true if BaseRev != \"\" AND ResultRev != \"\" AND BaseRev == ResultRev. This catches:\n- Model wrote nothing AND came back cleanly (true no_progress) ✓\n- Worker killed mid-execution before commit (FALSE no_progress — disruption)\n- Network/provider error before model started (FALSE no_progress — disruption)\n- Routing preflight rejection (FALSE no_progress — config issue)\n\nThe mis-classification is the bug.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n\nAdd a Disposition::Disrupted variant (or equivalent flag on ExecuteBeadReport) that explicitly marks results that are NOT evidence of model inability:\n- ctx.Err() != nil (cancellation, deadline, parent died)\n- syscall.SIGTERM / SIGINT received during execution\n- Provider-side 5xx, connection refused, timeout (transport disruption)\n- Worker process killed (parent never received clean result)\n- Server-restart-detected marker\n- Routing preflight rejection (operator config issue, not model failure)\n\nFor Disrupted: skip cooldown entirely (or use a tiny defer like 30s) and unclaim the bead so the next worker pickup is immediate.\nFor genuine no-progress (model returned clean with no commit AND rationale present): keep current 6h cooldown.\n\nALTERNATIVE: exponential backoff per bead. First failure: 5min; second: 30min; third: 2h; cap at 24h. Resets on any successful attempt or operator clear. This is more forgiving than the current flat 6h on the first hiccup.\n\nPROBABLY BOTH: Disrupted skips cooldown entirely; non-Disrupted failures use exponential backoff starting at 5min, not flat 6h.\n\nDETECTION POINTERS\n\n- ctx.Err() check at the call site that produces ExecutionFailed (line 513, 629, 637, 1011)\n- Check for `.ddx/executions/\u003crun-id\u003e/no_changes_rationale.txt` presence — if missing, the model never wrote one (likely disruption)\n- Check the executor's exit code: SIGKILL/SIGTERM = disruption; clean exit with empty result = no-progress\n- Track parent process restart count or boot ID; if changed since the attempt started, mark Disrupted\n\nNOT IN SCOPE\n- Changing the cooldown duration constants themselves\n- Reworking the per-bead retry policy framework (separate concern)\n- Changing land-conflict or push-failed cooldowns (those are correct as-is)\n- The exponential-backoff alternative is OPTIONAL; primary fix is Disrupted classification\n\nINTERSECTION WITH OTHER BEADS\n- ddx-dc157075 (worker stay-alive): the stay-alive fix prevents some classes of disruption (worker no longer exits on empty poll), but does NOT fix the cooldown-on-disruption mis-classification\n- ddx-076147ee (worker client-server architecture TD): if workers become long-lived clients, server-restart disruption goes away by construction. But this fix is needed BEFORE that TD is implemented because the disruption classification is needed regardless.\n- ddx-9228a484 C9 (StopCondition enum): may absorb this — the StopCondition enum could include Disrupted as a state. Verify and align.","events_attachment":"ddx-5b3e57f4/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-5b3e57f4","issue_type":"bug","labels":["phase:2","area:agent","kind:fix","observed-failure"],"owner":"erik","parent":"ddx-e34994e2","priority":1,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-59cfc8c5","status":"closed","title":"work: distinguish worker-disrupted from model-gave-up; do not cooldown on disruption","updated_at":"2026-05-03T02:30:29.374776912Z","work-heartbeat-at":"2026-05-03T02:29:24.332622724Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:762:{"acceptance":"1. 'ddx bead dep add \u003cbead\u003e \u003cdep\u003e' HARD-REJECTS the edge when \u003cdep\u003e is \u003cbead\u003e's parent OR any ancestor in the parent chain. Error message names the offending ancestor and prints the relevant parent-chain. Test: ddx_bead_dep_add_rejects_parent_ancestor.\n2. 'ddx bead create --depends-on X --parent Y' with X == Y (or X an ancestor of Y) HARD-REJECTS at creation time with the same error shape as AC #1. No silent rewrite.\n3. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./... passes.\n4. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-07-02T22:52:12Z","closing_commit_sha":"2bbb93e87a3920ca453101fdeaea9565f382c185","created_at":"2026-06-06T03:22:30.475161508Z","description":"PROBLEM\nParent bead ddx-e19185aa is too broad for one execution pass. This child owns part 1 of 3 of that parent scope.\n\nROOT CAUSE\nThe decomposition action (currently invoked when a bead is too large for one execution and the agent splits it into child beads) is writing the parent's ID as a dep edge on every child. This produces an unbreakable deadlock:\n\n  e29892a4 (parent, open) -- parent --\u003e child_A\n  e29892a4 -- parent --\u003e child_B\n  child_A.deps = [e29892a4]           \u003c- BAD: parent is also a dep\n  child_B.deps = [child_A, e29892a4]  \u003c- BAD\n\nThe parent stays open until its children close. Every child is blocked on the parent. Nothing can be claimed. ddx work loops on the parent, the orchestrator emits 'mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale', the worker retries, and burns claim budget without progress.\n\nObserved scenario (niflheim, 2026-06-04 04:30-05:13 UTC):\n- Parent: niflheim-e29892a4 ('feat(delta): async write-behind ...')\n- 10 children created during planning loops (23223661, a44a8ceb, 054c89b7, 0470ba0d, f10e9e35, f076b08c, 6c041162, 94e1df73, 9da62c2d, 5e4f9fb2)\n- Every child carried deps=[..siblings.., niflheim-e29892a4]\n- ~50 minutes of agent time + 4 strong-policy claude/opus attempts with zero feature commits; only tracker chores\n- Unwedged manually by closing the parent via 'ddx bead close', after which siblings drained correctly in foundational order\n\nRoot cause is structural, not model-capability — auto-upgrading to a stronger model does NOT fix this. The orchestrator already detects the no-progress state but its only remediation is 'retry parent', which re-enters the same loop.\n\nThere is also a 'project root mutation rejected (continuing)' warning emitted by the readiness check during this state; that's a downstream symptom of the same problem, not the cause.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nImplement only this child acceptance slice:\n- 'ddx bead dep add \u003cbead\u003e \u003cdep\u003e' HARD-REJECTS the edge when \u003cdep\u003e is \u003cbead\u003e's parent OR any ancestor in the parent chain. Error message names the offending ancestor and prints the relevant parent-chain. Test: ddx_bead_dep_add_rejects_parent_ancestor.\n- 'ddx bead create --depends-on X --parent Y' with X == Y (or X an ancestor of Y) HARD-REJECTS at creation time with the same error shape as AC #1. No silent rewrite.\n\nNON-SCOPE\nDo not implement parent acceptance criteria assigned to sibling child beads. Preserve every parent non-scope constraint unless this child explicitly narrows it.","events_attachment":"ddx-63780ef6/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-63780ef6","issue_type":"task","labels":["area:tracker","area:lifecycle","area:decomposition","kind:safety","kind:correctness","ac-quality:needs-refinement","decomposed"],"parent":"ddx-e19185aa","priority":0,"queue-rank":1790,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-7e9e7432","status":"closed","title":"Reject bead dep edges that re-introduce the parent or any ancestor: part 1","updated_at":"2026-06-13T13:58:34.845842756Z","work-no-changes-count":4}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:792:{"acceptance":"1. docs/helix/02-design/technical-designs/TD-\u003cNNN\u003e-bead-state-machine.md exists with all 11 sections plus 5 per-hygiene-bead contract subsections. 2. depends_on: [FEAT-004, SD-004, ADR-004]. 3. Persisted status list is the bd/br-canonical 6 (no additions). 4. Naming-role decision matrix covers ALL observed names with rationale. 5. Future-change process rule explicit. 6. Worker-state enumeration parallel section present. 7. ddx doc audit clean for the new TD artifact.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","claimed-at":"2026-05-02T19:04:45Z","claimed-machine":"eitri","claimed-pid":"3446284","closing_commit_sha":"b192a223325bb84409feb85b0995eefd6938f351","created_at":"2026-05-02T18:14:01.509934338Z","description":"Authoring-only sub-task of the bead state-machine work. Children (filed separately) handle the mechanical reconciliation, CI guards, and housekeeping that follow this design.\n\nThis bead OUTPUTS the canonical TD doc that the 5 hygiene beads + the 3 sibling reconciliation beads reference. NO code or schema changes in this bead — those are separate sub-beads.\n\n## Critical constraint (per ADR-004)\n\nThe bead-record schema MUST stay compatible with the bd/br interchange contract. Status enum is FIXED at the bd/br canonical 6 (open, in_progress, closed, blocked, proposed, cancelled). DDx-specific execution semantics live in labels, events, or Extra map — NOT in new statuses.\n\n## Today's actual state (verified)\n\n- bead-record.schema.json enum: 6 values (the bd/br canonical set)\n- FEAT-004 line 65 docs: 3 values (lags schema)\n- Persisted reality: 'ddx bead list --json | jq -r .[].status | sort -u' shows only open/in_progress/closed in active rows today\n- Code uses additional names (done, needs_human, pending, ready, review, needs_investigation) but these are NOT persisted statuses — event kinds, terminal phases, derived queue categories, or labels\n\n## Five in-flight hygiene beads each touch state-machine vocabulary (must align with this TD)\n\n- ddx-b24e9630 (no_changes verification): NoChangesContract subsection\n- ddx-3c154349 (auto-triage): TriageContract subsection\n- ddx-aede917d (drain pause on quota): QuotaPauseContract subsection\n- ddx-c6e3db02 (rate-limit retry): RateLimitRetryContract subsection\n- ddx-da11a34a (lock contention): LockContentionContract subsection\n\n## Scope (this bead authors the doc only)\n\nAuthor docs/helix/02-design/technical-designs/TD-NNN-bead-state-machine.md with:\n\n1. Distinguish category of every observed name as one of: persisted bead status (locked to bd/br set) / derived queue category / event kind / terminal phase / claim metadata / label / Extra metadata field / worker state.\n2. Persisted status enumeration — confirm the bd/br-compatible 6-value set. Status enum is NOT modified.\n3. Transition matrix — table or diagram: which status → which is allowed; who can drive each (operator-via-CLI, drain loop, agent, reviewer); what events fire on each transition.\n4. Event vocabulary — unified across hygiene beads (no_changes_*, drain-paused-quota, etc.).\n5. Outcome → label/event/Extra mapping — when execute-bead returns merged/already_satisfied/review_block/execution_failed/no_changes_*, the resulting bead state changes (status transition within the 6, label add/remove, event append, Extra field update).\n6. Claim semantics — when claimed, when released, stale claim handling.\n7. Naming-role decision matrix — every observed name labeled with role + rationale: blocked, in_progress, open, closed, cancelled, proposed (current schema 6), done, pending, ready, review (in code as non-status), needs_human (label today; stays label), needs_investigation (LABEL per bd/br compatibility, NOT status), blocked-on-upstream:\u003cid\u003e (label).\n8. Per-hygiene-bead contract subsection — one per bead (NoChangesContract, TriageContract, QuotaPauseContract, RateLimitRetryContract, LockContentionContract): status transitions used (within canonical 6), labels added/removed, events fired, claim behavior, loop interactions.\n9. Future-change process — explicit rule: any bead introducing or changing labels/events/outcome semantics/claim handling MUST cite the TD section authorizing it. Adding a new persisted status requires upstream bd/br coordination + ADR-004 amendment.\n10. Worker-state enumeration — parallel section: idle / draining / paused-quota / paused-rate-limit / exiting. Worker-state is distinct from bead-state, owned by worker process not bead store.\n11. Migration plan placeholder — say 'sibling bead handles survey + execution' (the actual survey runs in the sibling bead).\n\n## What does NOT land here\n\n- Schema/code/docs reconciliation (sibling bead handles)\n- CI guard tests (sibling bead handles)\n- Hygiene-bead AC TD-NNN substitution + migration survey (sibling bead handles)","events_attachment":"ddx-673833f4/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-673833f4","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2","story:10","area:specs","kind:design","foundation"],"owner":"erik","parent":"ddx-e34994e2","priority":0,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-961d10be","status":"closed","title":"TD: bead state machine — design + naming-role decisions (foundational doc)","updated_at":"2026-05-02T19:08:40.016568868Z","work-heartbeat-at":"2026-05-02T19:07:45.127165761Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:800:{"acceptance":"cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go ExecuteBead() contains ONLY: worktree setup (or accept pre-made worktree), prompt construction, agent harness dispatch, progress event emission, and a final completion event. No Merge, no UpdateRef, no preserveRef, no evaluateRequiredGates, no outcome classification beyond {task_succeeded, task_failed, task_no_changes}. All merge/preserve/gate logic moved to a new parent-side orchestrator that can be run interactively. Regression test: two workers on two different beads complete in arbitrary order; parent process merges both sequentially with interactive conflict resolution if needed; no worktree-internal merge code paths are exercised.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","claimed-at":"2026-04-14T05:36:33Z","claimed-machine":"eitri","claimed-pid":"1412283","closing_commit_sha":"49c3d2bda576630dd2f6555bc143082344f079ba","created_at":"2026-04-14T04:02:25.941816183Z","description":"The current execute-bead worker does WAY too much: creates a worktree, runs the agent, evaluates required gates, decides merge-by-default vs preserve vs land-conflict, writes preserve refs, synthesizes commits on IsDirty, classifies 7+ outcomes, manages heartbeats, handles claim/unclaim contention, runs recoverOrphans on stale worktrees. This surface is why (a) two concurrent workers race on the main-branch merge and the loser's good work ends up under refs/ddx/iterations/ needing manual rescue, (b) no_changes gets misclassified as synthesized-commit success, (c) the gate-enforcement path and the merge path are entangled, and (d) the worker needs special privileges (update-ref, merge, rebase) that a simple task-runner should never have.\\n\\nThe correct design is the one the operator just described: execute-bead is a thin worker. 'I have been handed a worktree and a task. I will execute that task and make commits in the worktree. I will stream progress events to ddx server. I will notify ddx server when I am done, reporting the worktree branch and the commit(s) I made. Then I exit.' That's it.\\n\\nEverything else — merge to main, conflict resolution, required-gate evaluation, preserve-under-ref, decide whether to close the bead — moves to the PARENT process (the operator, or a driver tool running interactively in the terminal). Merge conflicts are resolved interactively the same as any other merge. A human (or an outer agent with full git authority) reviews the agent's commits and decides what to do with them.\\n\\nThis simplification deletes most of ExecuteBead() in cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go and moves:\\n- resolveBase / baseRev tracking → parent\\n- Merge() call → parent\\n- preserveRef / UpdateRef / refs/ddx/iterations/ writes → parent\\n- evaluateRequiredGates → parent (or a separate 'ddx agent check' step)\\n- outcome classification 'merged/preserved/land-conflict/error' → parent\\n- recoverOrphans → parent (cleanup runs when parent next launches workers)\\n- heartbeatIsStale reclaim logic → parent (parent tracks worker health)\\n\\nWhat the worker keeps:\\n- Take a worktree dir + task description (prompt) as input\\n- Launch the agent harness with the prompt\\n- Stream progress events to ddx server (session log + structured JSONL)\\n- On exit, emit a final event: worktree path, branch, commit shas (or empty), exit code, duration\\n- That's it\\n\\nExecute-loop likewise shrinks or goes away. In the clean design, a driver loop in the parent process picks ready beads, creates a /tmp worktree per bead, calls 'ddx agent execute-bead' (worker-only mode), waits for the worker's exit event from ddx server, reviews the result, and merges or discards. When two beads are in flight concurrently, the parent serializes the merge step — no race possible.","events_attachment":"ddx-679d2fc7/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-679d2fc7","issue_type":"task","owner":"ddx","priority":0,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-reconcile-49c3d2b","status":"closed","title":"Simplify execute-bead worker: task-only, no merge/preserve/gate logic","updated_at":"2026-04-14T14:12:51.136077845Z","work-heartbeat-at":"2026-04-14T06:18:33.856661655Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:832:{"acceptance":"File exists at skills/ddx/reference/work.md. Sections cover: ddx work as default, ddx agent execute-bead as primitive, pick-by-default, verify-before-close, close-on-success/unclaim-on-failure with the exact outcome taxonomy (success, already_satisfied, no_changes, land_conflict, post_run_check_failed, execution_failed, structural_validation_failed), testing expectations with 'coverage only where the project tracks it', CLI reference. No mandatory TDD framing. Linked from skills/ddx/SKILL.md intent-router.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","created_at":"2026-04-17T22:05:46.08980466Z","description":"Create skills/ddx/reference/work.md — the reference file a harness reads when the user says 'do work', 'drain the queue', 'run the next bead', or 'execute this'.\n\nContent required:\n- Default queue-drain surface: ddx work is the primary command (alias for ddx agent work). ddx agent execute-bead \u003cid\u003e is the primitive for targeted re-runs.\n- Pick-by-default, not by ID: ddx work picks the top ready bead. Override with --id only when debugging.\n- Verify independently before closing: run the acceptance criteria command yourself; do not trust the agent self-report. Claude/Codex agents hallucinate successful completions.\n- Close on success/unclaim on failure: close only on outcome 'success' or 'already_satisfied'; unclaim on every other outcome (no_changes, land_conflict, post_run_check_failed, execution_failed, structural_validation_failed). Never leave beads half-owned.\n- Testing expectations for bead implementations (not AC-level, but default guidance): favor stubs over mocks when a collaborator behavior matters to the test; exercise all layers where the project has them (unit / integration / e2e); measure coverage only where the project tracks it — do not introduce coverage tooling just for this.\n- CLI reference: ddx work, ddx agent execute-bead \u003cid\u003e, ddx agent work, with a note that ddx work wraps work.\n\nSource material: existing /skills/ddx-run/SKILL.md. Keep the lifecycle enforcement (claim → implement → verify → close). Strip TDD-as-mandatory framing if present (TDD is a methodology opinion; the ddx-native stance is 'tests must be included and must run', not a specific methodology).\n\nIn-scope files:\n- skills/ddx/reference/work.md (new)\n\nOut-of-scope:\n- skills/ddx/SKILL.md (separate bead ddx-bd852e86)\n- Other reference/*.md files (separate beads)\n- Testing persona work (Phase 3)","id":"ddx-6aa90265","issue_type":"task","labels":["ddx","phase:build","kind:implementation","area:skills"],"parent":"ddx-f586b4fd","priority":1,"schema_version":1,"spec-id":"FEAT-011","status":"closed","title":"Create skills/ddx/reference/work.md — drain queue, execute-bead, verify+close","updated_at":"2026-04-17T22:23:03.221075141Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:864:{"acceptance":"New file cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_integration_test.go contains at minimum the 9 test cases enumerated in the description. Shared helper newScriptHarnessRepo lives in cli/internal/agent/integration_helper_test.go. Every test uses the script harness (not virtual, not fakeAgentRunner) and a real temp git repo created via git init with scrubbed GIT_* env. Every test verifies its assertion by running real git commands on the temp repo (git log, git rev-list, git for-each-ref) — no mock git. The suite runs under `go test ./internal/agent -run Integration -race -count=1` in under 60 seconds with all cases passing. Test 5 (FiveConcurrentBeads) proves linear history invariant that ddx-6aa50e57 acceptance demands. Test 6 (TwoWorkersSameBead) proves atomic claim invariant that ddx-3315dce2 acceptance demands. Test 7 (RebaseConflict) depends on the land coordinator from ddx-8746d8a6 being in place — it may be a t.Skip if the coordinator hasn't landed yet, with a TODO comment and a bead reference.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","created_at":"2026-04-14T14:50:02.413040703Z","description":"Build the integration test suite for work orchestration using the script harness + real git temp repos. This is the test gap the opus test-plan review identified as the most critical coverage hole: every \"concurrency\" or \"merge race\" test today uses in-memory fakes with per-worker orchestrators, so the shared-writer invariant the meta-bead design depends on is never actually exercised.\n\n## Test infrastructure helper\n\nBuild a shared helper `newScriptHarnessRepo(t *testing.T) (projectRoot, initialRev string)` in a new file `cli/internal/agent/integration_helper_test.go` that:\n\n1. Creates a temp dir via t.TempDir()\n2. Runs `git init` with scrubbed GIT_* env (so the test's own pre-commit hook env doesn't leak)\n3. Creates and commits an initial seed commit on `main`\n4. Seeds .ddx/beads.jsonl with N ready beads (parameterized by test)\n5. Returns projectRoot + the initial SHA\n\nThe helper must NOT inherit any GIT_DIR from the parent test environment.\n\n## Test cases\n\nCreate cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_integration_test.go with these cases. Each runs against the script harness and real git:\n\n1. **TestIntegration_ScriptHarness_SingleBead_AppendLine_Merged** — one bead, directive appends a line and commits, asserts git log main shows +1 commit, worktree is cleaned up, bead closed with closing_commit_sha.\n\n2. **TestIntegration_ScriptHarness_NoOp_ClassifiedAsNoChanges** — directive no-op, asserts outcome=no-changes, bead stays open (below adjudication threshold), no commit on main.\n\n3. **TestIntegration_ScriptHarness_DirtyWorktreeSynthesized** — directive creates files but omits explicit commit, asserts SynthesizeCommit fires, outcome=merged, single synthetic commit on main with the expected files.\n\n4. **TestIntegration_ScriptHarness_FailedExit_WithCommits_Preserved** — directive commits then set-exit 1, asserts outcome=preserved, refs/ddx/iterations/\u003cbead\u003e/\u003cts\u003e-\u003csha\u003e exists, main unchanged.\n\n5. **TestIntegration_ScriptHarness_FiveConcurrentBeads_LinearHistory** — seed 5 distinct beads, spawn 5 workers concurrently (single store, single projectRoot), assert `git log --merges main | wc -l` is 0, `git rev-list main ^initial | wc -l` is 5, every bead closed. **This is the ddx-6aa50e57 acceptance test that cannot be written today.**\n\n6. **TestIntegration_ScriptHarness_TwoWorkersSameBead_ClaimedOnce** — seed 1 bead, spawn 2 workers against the same store, assert exactly one executes and the other reports no_ready_work. **This is the ddx-3315dce2 acceptance test.**\n\n7. **TestIntegration_ScriptHarness_RebaseConflict_Preserved** — two beads both modify the same line in the same file, workers start from the same base, first lands cleanly, second gets rebase conflict and is preserved under refs/ddx/iterations/. Main has exactly +1 commit, ref exists for bead 2. (Only passes once the land coordinator from ddx-8746d8a6 is in place.)\n\n8. **TestIntegration_ScriptHarness_ContextCancelBetweenIterations** — two beads, cancel context after first completes, assert second bead is not claimed. **This is the regression for commit 21d16e6.**\n\n9. **TestIntegration_ScriptHarness_NoChangesRationale_ClosesBeadFast** — directive writes a no_changes_rationale.txt citing a commit SHA, asserts the bead closes as already_satisfied without the 3-strike cooldown wait.\n\nEach test runs in isolation, cleans up its temp dir, and completes in under 10s. The full suite runs in under 60s. Use `-race` to catch any coordinator goroutine races.\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- Server-layer wiring (that's bead C)\n- Real-AI acceptance tests (gated tier 4)\n- Multi-project isolation (a separate bead, not filed here)\n- Cross-machine scenarios (multi-machine topology bead)","id":"ddx-6f6bf12a","issue_type":"task","labels":["area:agent","area:testing","kind:integration","phase:build"],"parent":"ddx-8746d8a6","priority":0,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-43009cc","status":"closed","title":"Integration tests for work orchestration using script harness + real git","updated_at":"2026-04-14T15:26:48.671814475Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:887:{"acceptance":"1. TestAttempt_NoChanges_StaysCanonical_NotNeedsInvestigation verifies the attempt layer does not persist needs_investigation as a status and still emits triage:no-changes-* labels.\n2. TestAttempt_NoChanges_WiresAdjudicateNoChangesContract proves try.Attempt calls adjudicateNoChangesContract rather than leaving it only in execute_bead_loop.go.\n3. TestExecuteBeadWorkerNoChangesVerifiedClosesImmediately, TestExecuteBeadWorkerNoChangesVerificationFailsKeepsBeadOpen, TestExecuteBeadWorkerNoChangesNeedsInvestigationKeepsBeadOpen, and TestExecuteBeadWorkerNoChangesUnjustifiedStaysOpenWithLabel remain green after the move.\n4. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... green.\n5. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"9deda72f9b3832158b57535af1cfa516f0e957f9","created_at":"2026-05-05T16:16:48.458316019Z","description":"PROBLEM\nThe no_changes contract is still adjudicated in execute_bead_loop.go after Attempt returns, so the loop owns triage labels, no_changes_count bookkeeping, and already_satisfied closure policy instead of try.Attempt. That makes the attempt contract leaky and keeps no_changes policy split across packages.\n\nROOT CAUSE\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:975-1059 calls w.adjudicateNoChangesContract, increments the no_changes counter, applies triage labels, emits no_changes_* events, and closes the bead when the contract is satisfied.\n- cli/internal/agent/try/attempt.go:99-137 only returns OutcomeReported / OutcomeSuccess / OutcomePark for conflict recovery; it does not own the no_changes policy.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- Move ParseNoChangesRationale, verification_command execution, and triage label/event selection into cli/internal/agent/try/attempt.go near Attempt().\n- Extend the try outcome contract so the loop only consumes structured disposition data plus cooldown/park reason/event instructions.\n- Keep the persisted status canonical: needs_investigation is represented with triage labels/events, not a new status value.\n- Reduce execute_bead_loop.go to generic structured-outcome handling for the no_changes path.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Rate-limit retry handling.\n- Decomposition, push_failed, or push_conflict routing.\n- Any change to the canonical status vocabulary beyond the existing triage-label contract.\n\nINTERSECTIONS\n- Absorbs ddx-b24e9630 behavior.","events_attachment":"ddx-71a48703/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-71a48703","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2","area:agent","kind:refactor","story:10","observed-failure"],"parent":"ddx-c8f79963","priority":0,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-fe0ae579","status":"closed","title":"try.Attempt: relocate no_changes adjudication and labels","updated_at":"2026-05-05T16:39:37.58941544Z","work-no-changes-count":1}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:898:{"acceptance":"1. docs/helix/02-design/technical-designs/TD-031-bead-state-machine.md §5 contains a new row for push_failed declaring \"in_progress → open\" transition, no work-retry-after, and event push-failed.\n2. The same §5 contains a new row for push_conflict declaring \"in_progress → open\", optional 15min work-retry-after (recheckable cooldown), and event push-conflict.\n3. The §5 preamble invariant prose explicitly enumerates outcomes that MUST NOT set work-retry-after, and outcomes that MAY (with the recheckable-window rationale).\n4. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-15T00:08:56Z","claimed-at":"2026-05-10T16:04:57Z","claimed-machine":"eitri","claimed-pid":"3534627","closing_commit_sha":"fec4ac2e049a8b4e863435b4c444f2cdfbcf9250","created_at":"2026-05-10T15:57:05.826631456Z","description":"PROBLEM\n  TD-031 §5 outcome→Extra mapping table is missing rows for\n  push_failed and push_conflict. Today's implementation parks\n  push_failed at 24h cooldown (cli/internal/agent/try/attempt.go:272-283),\n  which violates the §5 invariant: \"work-retry-after may be\n  set only when retrying the same bead after time passes could\n  plausibly succeed without human/spec/dependency changes.\"\n\n  push_failed is caused by branch protection, auth-token expiry,\n  pre-push test failures (which require code fixes), or a data race\n  in executor.go (also a code fix). NONE of these are recheckable\n  by time elapsed alone. Without the spec row, implementers add\n  cooldowns that survive long after their cause is resolved. Today's\n  drain idled ~10h because of stale push_failed cooldowns set during\n  a data-race incident that was fixed within the hour.\n\n  This is a doc-only bead. It lands the spec row + the invariant\n  before the implementation fixes (sister beads handle code).\n\nCURRENT STATE\n  - docs/helix/02-design/technical-designs/TD-031-bead-state-machine.md\n    §5 has rows for review_pass, already_satisfied, review_fixable_gap,\n    review_spec_gap, review_too_large, review_error, execution_failed,\n    no_changes (multiple variants), parent/epic, external blocker,\n    superseded, transient infra/quota/transport, stale no_changes\n    metadata.\n  - No row for push_failed.\n  - No row for push_conflict.\n  - The §5 preamble invariant about work-retry-after is\n    correctly stated but lacks a concrete enumeration of which\n    outcomes may set the field vs which must not.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n  Edit docs/helix/02-design/technical-designs/TD-031-bead-state-machine.md\n  §5:\n\n  1. Add row for push_failed:\n     - Status transition: in_progress → open (claim released).\n     - Label changes: optional explanatory label (e.g.,\n       blocked-on-branch-protection if applicable).\n     - Events: push-failed with stderr detail and base-rev.\n     - Extra updates: Extra[\"last-run\"] only; DO NOT set\n       work-retry-after. Operator action OR a code fix on\n       origin clears the implicit block.\n\n  2. Add row for push_conflict (remote diverged, fast-forward\n     rejected by non-FF):\n     - Status transition: in_progress → open (claim released).\n     - Label changes: (none).\n     - Events: push-conflict.\n     - Extra updates: may set work-retry-after at 15min\n       (recheckable — remote advanced; a brief wait + re-fetch\n       resolves naturally).\n\n  3. Strengthen the §5 invariant prose:\n     - Add an explicit list of outcomes that MUST NOT set\n       work-retry-after: push_failed,\n       declined_needs_decomposition, review_spec_gap,\n       review_missing_acceptance, review_too_large at depth cap.\n     - Note: push_conflict, no_viable_provider, land_conflict,\n       transient infra/quota/transport ARE recheckable and may\n       use cooldowns.\n     - Reinforce: cooldown lifetime should match the recheckable\n       window (15min for transient, NOT 24h).\n\nNON-SCOPE\n  - Implementation fixes (sister beads).\n  - Bulk operator clear command (sister bead).\n  - Rev-bound auto-invalidation logic (sister bead).\n  - Other sections of TD-031.\n\nINTERSECTIONS\n  - Sister bead \"fix(try): push_failed must not set cooldown\" (R1)\n    depends on this row landing first.\n  - Sister bead \"fix(try): declined_needs_decomposition use\n    execution-eligible=false\" (R4) is referenced by the new\n    invariant prose.","events_attachment":"ddx-72cf3b8d/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-72cf3b8d","issue_type":"chore","labels":["area:agent","area:docs","kind:doc","phase:6","prevention","spec:TD-031"],"owner":"erik","priority":0,"queue-rank":"14","schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-0dd9692e","spec-id":"TD-031","status":"closed","title":"docs(TD-031): codify push_failed/push_conflict outcome rows + cooldown invariant","updated_at":"2026-05-10T16:07:25.946993626Z","work-heartbeat-at":"2026-05-10T16:04:57.27469304Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:899:{"acceptance":"1. docs/helix/02-design/contracts/API-001-execute-bead-supervisor-contract.md contains a status table or canonical delegation that covers every `ExecuteBeadStatus*` constant in cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_status.go.\n2. Any API-001 text that still lists only five statuses is removed or explicitly scoped as a historical minimal v1 subset.\n3. `rg -n \"status.*one of|structural_validation_failed.*execution_failed.*post_run_check_failed\" docs/helix/02-design/contracts/API-001-execute-bead-supervisor-contract.md` has no stale five-status-only contract hit.\n4. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... -run TestExecuteBeadStatus` passes.\n5. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.","archived_at":"2026-07-02T22:52:12Z","closing_commit_sha":"05d462e8b7f9ca2003e8f96d46a9a1e56830bf57","created_at":"2026-06-05T23:56:41.999712359Z","description":"PROBLEM\nAPI-001 documents only five supervisor-visible execute-bead statuses, but the implementation exposes a larger stable status contract used by `ddx try`, `ddx work`, retry logic, review outcomes, land conflict handling, and resource exhaustion. A worker or server consumer that follows API-001 literally will miss valid statuses.\n\nROOT CAUSE\n- docs/helix/02-design/contracts/API-001-execute-bead-supervisor-contract.md:177 lists only `structural_validation_failed`, `execution_failed`, `post_run_check_failed`, `land_conflict`, and `success`.\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_status.go:330 defines additional stable statuses including `ratchet_failed`, `push_failed`, `push_conflict`, `preserved_needs_review`, `no_evidence_produced`, `no_changes`, `already_satisfied`, `resource_exhausted`, review statuses, conflict-resolution statuses, and repair-cycle statuses.\n- docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-010-task-execution.md already describes richer candidate-cycle and drain lifecycle semantics, so API-001 is stale rather than the implementation being obviously wrong.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nUpdate API-001 to define the full supervisor-visible status taxonomy or explicitly delegate the canonical list to FEAT-010 plus the implementation enum. Add a compact status table with close/unclaim/operator-attention behavior categories and note which statuses are legacy/future-only if any are not emitted today.\n\nNON-SCOPE\nDo not change status strings or worker behavior. Do not redo landing semantics; ddx-693d504f covers that separately.","events_attachment":"ddx-72ee9fbc/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-72ee9fbc","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:iterate","area:docs","area:agent","kind:spec","spec-drift"],"parent":"ddx-4ac4da95","priority":1,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-df425ccf","spec-id":"API-001","status":"closed","title":"docs: align API-001 execute-bead status contract","updated_at":"2026-06-07T13:47:20.328145144Z","work-no-changes-count":2}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:917:{"acceptance":"1. TestLifecycle_NoChangesVerified_ClosesAndLeavesQueue creates a no_changes verified attempt and asserts the bead closes as already_satisfied and is absent from execution-ready output.\n2. TestLifecycle_NeedsInvestigation_NoCooldownAndExplainedSkip creates a needs_investigation no_changes attempt and asserts no work-retry-after is set and diagnostics explain the human/triage reason.\n3. TestLifecycle_UnjustifiedNoChanges_BadAttemptNotLongCooldown creates an absent-rationale no_changes attempt and asserts triage:no-changes-unjustified is applied without a long retry parking loop.\n4. TestLifecycle_TransientTransport_UsesCooldown creates a retryable transient outcome and asserts retry-after is set and diagnostics place it in cooldown, proving cooldown still works for time-based retry conditions.\n5. TestLifecycle_ReconcileLatestSuccessClearsStaleNoChanges seeds stale Extra plus a later success event and asserts reconcile dry-run/apply clears stale management metadata.\n6. TestLifecycle_ParentEpicNotOrdinaryExecutionReady covers a parent/epic/decomposed fixture and asserts ordinary ddx work does not pick it while diagnostics explain why.\n7. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./internal/bead/... ./cmd/... -run 'TestLifecycle_NoChangesVerified_ClosesAndLeavesQueue|TestLifecycle_NeedsInvestigation_NoCooldownAndExplainedSkip|TestLifecycle_UnjustifiedNoChanges_BadAttemptNotLongCooldown|TestLifecycle_TransientTransport_UsesCooldown|TestLifecycle_ReconcileLatestSuccessClearsStaleNoChanges|TestLifecycle_ParentEpicNotOrdinaryExecutionReady' -count=1 passes.\n8. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"f03b42811f6eacae918ea5631b679216c25d33a7","created_at":"2026-05-05T20:44:46.075544756Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-75e1f4a5","depends_on_id":"ddx-fd1766e5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-05T20:44:46Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-75e1f4a5","depends_on_id":"ddx-49eeb476","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-05T20:44:46Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-75e1f4a5","depends_on_id":"ddx-837a2254","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-05T20:44:46Z"}],"description":"PROBLEM\nThe no_changes/cooldown pile-up involved several interacting paths: try adjudication, live work store mutations, queue derivation, and reconciliation of stale Extra fields. Unit tests on each piece are necessary but not sufficient to prevent regressions where the pieces drift apart again.\n\nROOT CAUSE\n- cli/internal/agent/try/attempt_test.go can prove an action classification, but it does not prove work store mutation or queue eligibility.\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop_test.go can prove live mutation, but it does not prove the later queue view explains the resulting state correctly.\n- cli/internal/bead/store.go queue tests can prove filtering, but not that real no_changes outcomes produce the durable fields queue filtering expects.\n- There is no fixture suite built around the real pile-up patterns: verified already done, latest success with stale no_changes Extra, parent/epic already decomposed, external blocker, unjustified no rationale, and transient retryable cooldown.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- Add a small cross-path regression suite using existing in-memory/temp-repo test helpers.\n- Cover each observed pile-up class from input attempt/event through durable tracker state and execution-ready diagnostics.\n- Keep tests focused; do not add a broad e2e that shells out to real agents.\n- Reuse the TD-031 action semantics and queue diagnostic helpers implemented by dependency beads.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- New production behavior beyond fixing test seams needed to observe existing behavior.\n- Playwright/UI coverage.\n- Real provider/harness calls.\n- Historical tracker mutation outside test fixtures.\n\nPARENT\n- ddx-a9d130d0.\n\nDEPS\n- ddx-fd1766e5: live no_changes action application must exist.\n- ddx-49eeb476: execution-ready diagnostics must expose durable skip reasons.\n- ddx-837a2254: reconciliation command/pass must exist for stale tracker fixtures.\n\nINTERSECTIONS\n- This bead should move any regression fixture that would otherwise duplicate implementation-bead tests into the narrowest appropriate package, but it owns the cross-path coverage that spans multiple packages.","id":"ddx-75e1f4a5","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2","area:test","area:agent","area:beads","kind:test","reliability","bead-lifecycle","spec:TD-031"],"parent":"ddx-a9d130d0","priority":2,"schema_version":1,"spec-id":"TD-031","status":"closed","title":"test: lock TD-031 no_changes lifecycle regression fixtures","updated_at":"2026-05-06T00:30:22.219190749Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:933:{"acceptance":"1. Benchmark file exists at cli/internal/bead/benchmark_backends_test.go covering BenchmarkReady, BenchmarkBlocked, BenchmarkShow for both jsonl and axon on 1100-bead corpus.\n2. Runs via: cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test -bench=. ./internal/bead/... -run='^$' green.\n3. Results document parity-or-better for axon vs jsonl (wall-time + allocs) committed to .ddx/executions/\u003crun-id\u003e/axon-vs-jsonl-benchmark.md.\n4. Benchmark is reproducible via go test -bench.\n5. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/bead/... green (unit tests unaffected).\n6. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","created_at":"2026-05-02T14:48:36.359297654Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-781a15cf","depends_on_id":"ddx-c9ef6c4f","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-02T14:48:43Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-781a15cf","depends_on_id":"ddx-95ec5ed5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-04T21:59:05Z"}],"description":"PROBLEM\nNo performance benchmark exists comparing axon backend vs JSONL backend at realistic archive scale (1100 beads). Without this benchmark, the parent epic (ddx-5d49b14e) cannot evaluate its AC6 gate ('axon parity-or-better than JSONL for ready/blocked/show queue ops').\n\nROOT CAUSE\n- cli/internal/bead/ contains backend_jsonl.go but no axon backend implementation (ddx-95ec5ed5, a dep, must land first).\n- No benchmark file exercises ready/blocked/show operations on a 1100-bead corpus.\n- The missing dep edge (ddx-781a15cf → ddx-95ec5ed5) caused the queue to surface this bead prematurely (dep edge should be added via ).\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- After ddx-95ec5ed5 (axon backend) and ddx-bbdd7564 (Backend interface) land:\n  - Add cli/internal/bead/benchmark_backends_test.go (or bead_bench_test.go) with:\n    - BenchmarkReady_JSONL_1100: ready queue ops on 1100-bead JSONL corpus.\n    - BenchmarkReady_Axon_1100: same ops on 1100-bead axon corpus.\n    - BenchmarkBlocked_JSONL_1100 and BenchmarkBlocked_Axon_1100.\n    - BenchmarkShow_JSONL_1100 and BenchmarkShow_Axon_1100.\n  - Generate 1100-bead test corpus (mix of open + closed + archived).\n  - Capture wall-time and allocs. Commit results to .ddx/executions/\u003crun-id\u003e/axon-vs-jsonl-benchmark.md.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- axon backend implementation (ddx-95ec5ed5).\n- Adding a CI gate on benchmark results (gate belongs to a follow-up bead).","events_attachment":"ddx-781a15cf/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-781a15cf","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2"," area:beads"," area:storage"," kind:perf"," backend-migration","triage:needs-investigation","triage:no-changes-unjustified"],"parent":"ddx-5d49b14e","priority":2,"schema_version":1,"status":"closed","title":"Benchmark: axon backend vs JSONL on 1100-bead archive","updated_at":"2026-05-05T11:39:43.033381384Z","work-last-detail":"agent exited without a commit or no_changes_rationale.txt","work-last-status":"no_changes","work-no-changes-count":4,"work-retry-after":"2026-05-05T17:39:42Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1034:{"acceptance":"1. `ddx bead reconcile --dry-run` or equivalent default dry-run command reports proposed lifecycle metadata repairs without mutating the tracker.\n2. `ddx bead reconcile --apply` applies only supported store/API mutations and never edits .ddx/beads.jsonl directly.\n3. TestBeadReconcile_LatestSuccessClearsStaleNoChangesMetadata covers a fixture where latest execute-bead event is success but Extra still says work-last-status=no_changes.\n4. TestBeadReconcile_VerifiedNoChangesCanCloseAlreadySatisfied covers a verified no_changes rationale whose verification command passes.\n5. TestBeadReconcile_NonRetryableNeedsInvestigationClearsCooldown covers a needs_investigation event with retry-after and preserves the triage label/reason.\n6. TestBeadReconcile_ParentEpicMarksNotExecutableOnlyWithChildEvidence covers repeated parent/epic no_changes without creating new child beads.\n7. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/bead/... ./cmd/... -run 'TestBeadReconcile_LatestSuccessClearsStaleNoChangesMetadata|TestBeadReconcile_VerifiedNoChangesCanCloseAlreadySatisfied|TestBeadReconcile_NonRetryableNeedsInvestigationClearsCooldown|TestBeadReconcile_ParentEpicMarksNotExecutableOnlyWithChildEvidence' -count=1 passes.\n8. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"f03b42811f6eacae918ea5631b679216c25d33a7","created_at":"2026-05-05T20:44:22.956537264Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-837a2254","depends_on_id":"ddx-fd1766e5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-05T20:44:23Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-837a2254","depends_on_id":"ddx-49eeb476","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-05T20:44:23Z"}],"description":"PROBLEM\nThe current tracker can contain stale management metadata from prior attempts: latest events may show success while work-last-status still says no_changes; verified no_changes may remain open; retry-after may be expired or attached to a non-retryable lifecycle condition; parent/epic beads may have repeated no_changes attempts even though children own the work. Without a reconciliation path, fixing future ddx work behavior strands the existing pile-up.\n\nROOT CAUSE\n- cli/internal/bead/store.go:744-752 SetExecutionCooldown writes mutable work-* Extra fields, but there is no companion repair path that reconciles those fields against append-only events.\n- cli/internal/bead/store.go:754-779 IncrNoChangesCount accumulates no_changes counters, but no command classifies or clears stale counters when a later terminal event supersedes them.\n- cli/cmd/bead.go has cooldown show/clear around lines 1171-1273, but no broader lifecycle reconciliation dry-run/apply command.\n- Live tracker evidence shows the failure class this bead must encode as fixtures: latest execute-bead event summary=success while work-last-status=no_changes; open verified no_changes; non-retryable needs_investigation parked with retry-after.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- Add a supported reconciliation command or worker reconciliation pass, preferably `ddx bead reconcile`, with dry-run default and explicit apply mode.\n- Reconciliation reads bead events and Extra fields through the store API, not by manual JSONL editing.\n- Implement conservative rules only:\n  - latest success/already_satisfied event may clear stale no_changes/cooldown Extra and close only when close evidence is present or verifiable through existing close path;\n  - verified no_changes may be re-run/validated and closed as already_satisfied when the verification command passes;\n  - expired retry-after may be cleared;\n  - parent/epic repeated no_changes may be marked execution-eligible=false only when child/dependency evidence proves ordinary ddx work should not pick it;\n  - non-retryable needs_investigation may clear retry-after and leave triage labels/blocked explanation.\n- Output every proposed mutation with bead id, reason, current fields, proposed fields, and whether it is safe to apply.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Free-form human judgment or LLM review during reconciliation.\n- Broad historical migration of closed beads.\n- Manual edits to .ddx/beads.jsonl.\n- Creating or deleting beads; this command only reconciles state on existing beads.\n\nPARENT\n- ddx-a9d130d0.\n\nDEPS\n- ddx-fd1766e5: reconciliation should use the same lifecycle action semantics as live execution.\n- ddx-49eeb476: reconciliation output should use the same durable skip reasons exposed by queue diagnostics.\n\nINTERSECTIONS\n- Existing `ddx bead cooldown clear` handles one field manually; this bead should reuse or complement it without changing its simple behavior.\n- Existing bead doctor repairs malformed/oversized tracker rows; this bead is lifecycle metadata reconciliation, not JSONL structural repair.","id":"ddx-837a2254","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2","area:beads","area:cli","kind:feature","reliability","bead-lifecycle","spec:TD-031"],"parent":"ddx-a9d130d0","priority":1,"schema_version":1,"spec-id":"TD-031","status":"closed","title":"beads: reconcile stale no_changes lifecycle metadata","updated_at":"2026-05-06T00:30:21.868775188Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1065:{"acceptance":"A single per-project land coordinator goroutine owns all writes to target refs. Unit tests in cli/internal/agent/ (or cli/internal/server/) prove: (1) happy path — worker submits base=A result=B, coordinator fetches current tip X, rebases B onto X, fast-forwards, asserts the new tip is the rebased commit and no merge commits exist in the history between A and the new tip (use git log --merges --count to assert 0); (2) rebase conflict path — worker submits a commit that cannot rebase cleanly, coordinator preserves the submission under refs/ddx/iterations/\u003cbead-id\u003e/\u003cattempt-id\u003e and returns a \"preserved\" status, target branch is unchanged; (3) serialization path — 5 concurrent submissions against the same project against base=A produce 5 sequential rebased commits on the target branch with linear history (git log --merges returns 0), and the coordinator processes them in order; (4) server runWorker integration — a server-managed worker whose task produces a commit B actually advances the target branch to a rebased B, via the coordinator path, visible in git log main -1 after the worker exits; (5) --local mode integration — the --local work path runs a process-local coordinator that provides the same semantics. Secondary acceptance: RealOrchestratorGitOps.Merge is deleted from execute_bead_orchestrator.go OR clearly marked as the legacy path to remove; no production code path calls git merge --no-edit on the target branch; FEAT-006, API-001, FEAT-012 still describe the same contract (rebase + ff-only, linear history). Operator-visible smoke: running ddx agent work --harness claude --model sonnet against a seeded queue produces a linear history on main with no merge commits between the run's first and last commit.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","created_at":"2026-04-14T14:35:57.684173463Z","description":"Today's work orchestration is a pile of patches on a flawed mental model. The user's target model is \"human picks PR off the queue → rebases onto current tip → merges → next worker starts from the new tip.\" The code implements \"worker branches off whatever main was when it started → runs task → git merge --no-edit that result back → 2-parent merge commit fan.\" The two models are incompatible; no patch to the second model gets you to the first.\n\nEvidence the current model is wrong:\n\n1. FEAT-006 §\"Landing\" (line 414), API-001 §\"Landing \u0026 Preservation\" (lines 217-222), and FEAT-012 §\"Execute-Bead Git Operations\" (line 413) all explicitly require rebase + fast-forward with linear history. The code in cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_orchestrator.go:61 Merge() runs `git merge --no-edit` with a defensive `chore: checkpoint before merge` commit — zero rebase, zero ff-only, zero fetch, zero push. Three spec files aligned on one model; code implements a different one.\n\n2. cli/internal/server/workers.go:runWorker (around line 237) calls agent.ExecuteBead via an inline ExecuteBeadExecutorFunc closure at workers.go:248 and never calls LandBeadResult. LandBeadResult is only wired into two call sites: cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go:1372 (the `--local` work path) and cli/cmd/agent_execute_bead.go:134 (the interactive single-bead CLI). The default `ddx agent work` path (which submits to the server) produces worker commits that are NEVER landed on main. Commits sit in worktree refs and the loop reports \"success\" to the tracker anyway.\n\n3. The \"worker simplification\" commit 49c3d2b that closed ddx-679d2fc7 moved Merge/UpdateRef out of execute_bead.go's GitOps interface into a new OrchestratorGitOps in execute_bead_orchestrator.go. That is a code-level function split, not a process-level split. The \"parent orchestrator\" runs synchronously in the worker process from whichever call site reaches it first. Two workers racing on the same projectRoot will both call LandBeadResult with stale baseRev assumptions; the current Merge implementation papers over conflicts with ort-strategy merge commits. The user was explicit in their feedback: \"we may not be separating concerns appropriately — we have pushed too much functionality into work and it's causing us issues; it needs to be very simple: 'I've been handed a worktree and a task, I will execute that task and make commits, produce progress output, notify done.'\" The current code does not reflect that intent.\n\n4. Six open child beads of ddx-b7ee0d6f (bd42f640 fetch-before-claim, 6aa50e57 rebase-instead-of-merge, 83ec1430 push-on-land, 2791dc4f tracker concurrency, 42dd982c divergence monitoring, b0374901 multi-machine docs) each correctly identify one piece of the gap but do not compose into a coherent end-to-end workflow. The fix is not \"implement all six\"; the fix is to adopt the human-PR model as the single source of truth and then let those beads fall out as sub-tasks of a coherent design.\n\n## Target design\n\nThe human-PR mental model, encoded as code:\n\n1. **Worker.** Accepts a pre-made worktree and a prompt. Runs the agent harness. Emits structured progress events. Produces zero or more commits in the worktree. Exits with a simple terminal status (task_succeeded / task_failed / task_no_changes) and reports its worktree branch + commit SHAs to the server. The worker NEVER fetches, rebases, merges, pushes, or writes a ref. The worker NEVER interacts with target refs on the shared project repo. The worker does not care what main is doing.\n\n2. **Land coordinator.** A single goroutine per project (hosted on the ddx server) that owns all writes to the project's target refs. Workers submit their completed worktree branch SHAs to the coordinator via a server endpoint. The coordinator, for each submission, in order: (a) `git fetch origin \u003ctarget-branch\u003e` to refresh the target tip; (b) `git rebase --onto \u003ctarget-tip\u003e \u003cbase-rev\u003e \u003cresult-rev\u003e` to replay the worker's commits onto the latest tip; (c) if the rebase is clean, `git push --ff-only origin \u003ctarget-branch\u003e` (or equivalent local update-ref if no remote); (d) on rebase conflict or push rejection, move the submission to `refs/ddx/iterations/\u003cbead-id\u003e/\u003cattempt-id\u003e` and mark the bead as needing human review. The coordinator handles one submission at a time. No locks needed internally because there's only one goroutine.\n\n3. **Worker-to-coordinator handoff.** Workers submit to a new `POST /api/agent/workers/:id/land-submission` endpoint with {worktree_branch, base_rev, result_rev, bead_id}. The endpoint enqueues the submission onto the land coordinator's channel and returns 202 Accepted. Workers block (via long-polling GET, SSE, or channel-await) for the land result — success (pushed to target), preserved (moved to iteration ref), or failed (rejected, worker should retry from new tip).\n\n4. **Worker isolation.** Workers run in /tmp/ddx-exec-wt/ worktrees per the alpha14 worktree-relocation fix. They fetch their starting base from the coordinator (\"what is the current tip?\"), branch off it, work, and submit. They never touch the shared project .git beyond their own worktree's read-fetch.\n\n5. **Tracker (beads.jsonl) coordination.** Separate concern from the git target refs. ddx-2791dc4f stays as its own bead because the tracker is a second shared resource with its own write-serialization requirement. The land coordinator and the tracker lock must both be respected, but they are orthogonal locks.\n\n6. **Multi-machine.** When the server grows to multi-machine topology, each machine runs its own land coordinator against its local clone of the project. Coordinators push to a common origin. The origin becomes the single source of truth for the target branch. Rebase-then-push gives the per-machine coordinators a clean serialization point via origin's ref update (push is atomic at the remote).\n\n## What this replaces\n\n- ddx-bd42f640 (fetch+ancestry check before claim) → subsumed. The land coordinator owns the fetch; workers don't need to check ancestry because they're handed a branch from the coordinator.\n- ddx-6aa50e57 (rebase instead of merge) → subsumed. The coordinator's rebase step is the canonical implementation.\n- ddx-83ec1430 (push-to-origin on landing) → subsumed. Push is part of the coordinator's sequence.\n- ddx-42dd982c (divergence monitoring) → reframed. Becomes monitoring of the coordinator's rejection rate and conflict rate.\n- ddx-b0374901 (multi-machine topology docs) → reframed. Document the per-machine coordinator + push-to-origin model.\n- The missing \"server runWorker never lands\" bug (new P0 child, filed alongside) → subsumed. The new model HAS a land step by design.\n\nWhat this does NOT replace:\n\n- ddx-2791dc4f (beads.jsonl concurrent-write safety) — separate concern, separate lock.\n- ddx-679d2fc7 (simplify worker to task-only) — this bead is nominally closed by commit 49c3d2b, but that commit did a cosmetic function split, not the architectural process split. Re-open or file a follow-up that cleans up the nomenclature (\"OrchestratorGitOps\" → \"CoordinatorGitOps\" scoped to the single coordinator goroutine) and deletes Merge() in favor of Land(). OR leave it closed and track that cleanup under this meta-bead.\n\n## Why this is better\n\nThe core insight: **target-ref writes must be serialized through a single writer that always sees the current tip.** That is how every real PR queue works (GitHub merge queue, gerrit, Zuul). The current design has every worker trying to be its own merge-master; the fix is to have exactly one merge-master per project and let workers be contributors.\n\n## Rollout\n\nThis is a redesign, not a patch. Rollout steps:\n\n1. Land a new Land(projectRoot, baseRev, resultRev, targetBranch) coordinator function that implements fetch → rebase → ff-push → preserve-on-fail. Unit tests that cover the happy path, the rebase conflict path, and the concurrent-submission serialization path.\n2. Add POST /api/agent/workers/:id/land-submission + the land coordinator goroutine + per-project queue channel to cli/internal/server/workers.go.\n3. Rewrite workers.go:runWorker to have the worker's executor closure submit to the local coordinator (via channel; no HTTP round-trip needed since it's in the same process) instead of calling LandBeadResult inline.\n4. Delete or mothball the current LandBeadResult and its \"orchestrator\" naming. The new coordinator replaces it.\n5. Leave --local mode working by having it instantiate a process-local single-goroutine coordinator at startup. --local remains useful for single-bead debugging.\n6. Add a --coordinator-only server mode for the multi-machine eventual topology (out of scope for the first cut; reference ddx-e2f497c3 for the design).\n\nOut of scope for this bead (but related):\n\n- Interactive conflict resolution UI. The meta-bead says \"preserve under refs/ddx/iterations/\" and move on; a separate UI flow for human merge-conflict resolution is its own work.\n- Cross-machine coordinators talking to each other. Out of scope; origin push suffices.\n- PR approval / review gates before the coordinator lands. Separate feature.","id":"ddx-8746d8a6","issue_type":"epic","priority":0,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-43009cc","status":"closed","title":"work: adopt human-PR landing model end-to-end (meta redesign)","updated_at":"2026-04-14T15:26:48.420152946Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1067:{"acceptance":"cd cli \u0026\u0026 go build ./tools/lint/runtimelint/... passes. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./tools/lint/runtimelint/... passes including positive (no violations) + negative (each forbidden pattern flagged) test fixtures. lefthook run pre-commit on a synthetic branch introducing a violation exits non-zero. Running runtimelint against the post-cleanup tree exits 0.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"f809c33ca6ab8a2b165daaa7ca28426a6eaf6d39","created_at":"2026-04-25T14:31:28.605381382Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-880b7d8b","depends_on_id":"ddx-edbfa046","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-25T14:31:36Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-880b7d8b","depends_on_id":"ddx-ade5ebb3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-25T14:31:36Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-880b7d8b","depends_on_id":"ddx-a8eaef0a","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-25T14:31:36Z"}],"description":"Stage 4 of SD-024. Adds the runtimelint analyzer at cli/tools/lint/runtimelint/ following the FEAT-022 evidencelint pattern. Wires into Lefthook pre-commit + CI.\n\nThe analyzer flags:\n1. Forbidden field names on *Runtime structs in cli/internal/agent/ (closed list — see TD-024 §Lint rule)\n2. Composite literal of any legacy *Options type\n3. Function signature parameter of any legacy *Options type\n\nAllowed: NoReview, PollInterval, SessionLogDirOverride on *Runtime.\n\nIn-scope:\n- cli/tools/lint/runtimelint/ (new analyzer + tests)\n- lefthook.yml — add hook\n- CI workflow — add job\n\nDepends on beads 16, 22, 28 (all legacy types retired).","events_attachment":"ddx-880b7d8b/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-880b7d8b","issue_type":"task","labels":["ddx","kind:tooling","area:lint","sd-024","stage:4"],"notes":"REOPENED 2026-04-26: Bead was closed but no runtimelint code was produced. cli/tools/lint/runtimelint/ does not exist in tree; 'find . -name runtimelint' returns zero matches; no commit references the analyzer. The prior already_satisfied closure was wrong — likely the worker probed for an existing analyzer, didn't find one, but the loop closed the bead anyway. B33 (final sweep) flagged this in its closure detail. Need to actually build the analyzer per TD-024 §Lint rule.","parent":"ddx-0f3ae192","priority":1,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-f4eb1884","spec-id":"SD-024","status":"closed","title":"tools/lint: runtimelint analyzer + Lefthook + CI wiring","updated_at":"2026-04-26T17:45:15.750491457Z","work-no-changes-count":2}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1083:{"acceptance":"1. `TestDefaultVerificationCommandRunnerTimeoutKillsProcessGroup` proves a timed-out nested shell command (`sh -lc 'sleep ...'` or equivalent fixture) leaves no child/grandchild process alive after the runner returns.\n2. `TestDefaultVerificationCommandRunnerAllowsConfiguredLongGate` or equivalent proves the verification timeout is configurable/worker-derived and can run a command longer than 60s without forcing `no_changes_unverified`.\n3. `TestExecuteBeadWorkerNoChangesVerifiedLongCommandCloses` proves a `verification_command` that runs longer than the old 60s limit but exits 0 closes the bead as `already_satisfied` and emits `no_changes_verified`.\n4. `TestExecuteBeadWorkerNoChangesVerificationTimeoutKeepsOpenAndReaps` proves timeout keeps the bead open with `triage:no-changes-unverified`, records timeout evidence, and leaves no verification process tree behind.\n5. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... -run 'Test(DefaultVerificationCommandRunner|ExecuteBeadWorkerNoChanges.*Verification)' -count=1` passes.\n6. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.","archived_at":"2026-07-02T22:52:12Z","closing_commit_sha":"f609f22ef84a0d7b05ba89dd3e9fd5b92fbfa446","created_at":"2026-05-15T13:09:07.942514913Z","description":"PROBLEM\nA `no_changes_rationale.txt` with `verification_command:` can time out, leave its child process tree running, and let `ddx work --watch` move on to another bead while the old verification is still consuming the project. Live reproduction on 2026-05-15 in `/Users/erik/Projects/fizeau`: `fizeau-bc9586d7` returned `verification_command: sh -lc \"go test ... \u0026\u0026 lefthook run pre-commit\"`; the watcher logged `• fizeau-bc9586d7 → no_changes` and started `fizeau-7af3f548` at 13:07:21Z, while `ps` still showed orphaned PID 3510889 (`sh -lc go test ...`) and child PID 3512539 (`go test ./... -count=1`) under PPID 1.\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\n`cli/internal/agent/try/no_changes.go:117-128` hard-codes `DefaultVerificationCommandTimeout = 60 * time.Second` and runs the command with `exec.CommandContext(cctx, \"/bin/sh\", \"-c\", command)`. `exec.CommandContext` kills only the direct shell on timeout; because workers commonly emit nested shell commands such as `sh -lc \"go test ...\"`, the actual test process survives as an orphan. The 60s timeout is also shorter than normal bead acceptance gates like `go test ./...` plus `lefthook run pre-commit`, so legitimate already-satisfied checks are classified as unverified/no-progress instead of closing the bead.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nRun no_changes verification commands with the same process-tree discipline used by agent executors: start the shell in its own process group on Unix, terminate the group on timeout/cancel, and wait/reap before returning. Replace the hard-coded 60s ceiling with a worker/config-derived timeout that is long enough for normal acceptance gates, or make it configurable with a conservative default. Preserve the contract: exit 0 closes as `already_satisfied`; non-zero/timeout keeps the bead open with clear `no_changes_unverified` evidence.\n\nNON-SCOPE\nDo not weaken no_changes verification semantics. Do not let verification run asynchronously. Do not close a bead without a passing command. Do not change readiness classification or route selection.","events_attachment":"ddx-8a0aea8e/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-8a0aea8e","issue_type":"bug","labels":["area:agent","area:work","kind:bug","operator-ux","downstream:fizeau","dirty-tree"],"priority":0,"queue-rank":600,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-af6f8fc7","status":"closed","title":"work: reap and correctly budget no_changes verification commands","updated_at":"2026-06-13T13:58:29.795710244Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1089:{"acceptance":"1. 'ddx bead doctor' (existing subcommand) gains a check 'parent_ancestor_in_deps' that scans the tracker, lists violating beads, and (with --fix) removes the offending edges. Output is stable / scriptable. Test: ddx_doctor_detects_and_repairs_back_edge.\n2. ddx work no-progress remediation: when an attempted bead's outcome is 'mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale' AND any freshly-created child carries the attempted bead in its deps, ddx auto-emits an 'operator_attention' event with reason 'parent_back_edge' and stops re-claiming that bead. (Today it loops indefinitely.) Test: ddx_work_halts_on_parent_back_edge.","archived_at":"2026-07-02T22:52:12Z","closing_commit_sha":"51ca3004a5083cfdbe2d2a8be0e9349d8df5a3ab","created_at":"2026-06-07T02:17:59.011894436Z","description":"PROBLEM\nParent bead ddx-130cf9ab is too broad for one execution pass. This child owns part 2 of 3 of that parent scope.\n\nROOT CAUSE\nPROBLEM\nParent bead ddx-e19185aa is too broad for one execution pass. This child owns part 2 of 3 of that parent scope.\n\nROOT CAUSE\nThe decomposition action (currently invoked when a bead is too large for one execution and the agent splits it into child beads) is writing the parent's ID as a dep edge on every child. This produces an unbreakable deadlock:\n\n  e29892a4 (parent, open) -- parent --\u003e child_A\n  e29892a4 -- parent --\u003e child_B\n  child_A.deps = [e29892a4]           \u003c- BAD: parent is also a dep\n  child_B.deps = [child_A, e29892a4]  \u003c- BAD\n\nThe parent stays open until its children close. Every child is blocked on the parent. Nothing can be claimed. ddx work loops on the parent, the orchestrator emits 'mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale', the worker retries, and burns claim budget without progress.\n\nObserved scenario (niflheim, 2026-06-04 04:30-05:13 UTC):\n- Parent: niflheim-e29892a4 ('feat(delta): async write-behind ...')\n- 10 children created during planning loops (23223661, a44a8ceb, 054c89b7, 0470ba0d, f10e9e35, f076b08c, 6c041162, 94e1df73, 9da62c2d, 5e4f9fb2)\n- Every child carried deps=[..siblings.., niflheim-e29892a4]\n- ~50 minutes of agent time + 4 strong-policy claude/opus attempts with zero feature commits; only tracker chores\n- Unwedged manually by closing the parent via 'ddx bead close', after which siblings drained correctly in foundational order\n\nRoot cause is structural, not model-capability — auto-upgrading to a stronger model does NOT fix this. The orchestrator already detects the no-progress state but its only remediation is 'retry parent', which re-enters the same loop.\n\nThere is also a 'project root mutation rejected (continuing)' warning emitted by the readiness check during this state; that's a downstream symptom of the same problem, not the cause.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nImplement only this child acceptance slice:\n- Programmatic decomposition path (the action that fans a too-large bead into children) MUST NOT add the parent as a dep. Existing action templates / system prompts are audited and amended; one golden e2e test (decompose_does_not_self_dep) creates a bead with N children and asserts every child's deps set excludes the parent.\n- 'ddx bead doctor' (existing subcommand) gains a check 'parent_ancestor_in_deps' that scans the tracker, lists violating beads, and (with --fix) removes the offending edges. Output is stable / scriptable.\n...[truncated]\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nImplement only this child acceptance slice:\n- 'ddx bead doctor' (existing subcommand) gains a check 'parent_ancestor_in_deps' that scans the tracker, lists violating beads, and (with --fix) removes the offending edges. Output is stable / scriptable. Test: ddx_doctor_detects_and_repairs_back_edge.\n- ddx work no-progress remediation: when an attempted bead's outcome is 'mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale' AND any freshly-created child carries the attempted bead in its deps, ddx auto-emits an 'operator_attention' event with reason 'parent_back_edge' and stops re-claiming that bead. (Today it loops indefinitely.) Test: ddx_work_halts_on_parent_back_edge.\n\nNON-SCOPE\nDo not implement parent acceptance criteria assigned to sibling child beads. Preserve every parent non-scope constraint unless this child explicitly narrows it.","events_attachment":"ddx-8a8bf714/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-8a8bf714","issue_type":"task","labels":["area:tracker","area:lifecycle","area:decomposition","kind:safety","kind:correctness","ac-quality:needs-refinement","decomposed"],"parent":"ddx-130cf9ab","priority":0,"queue-rank":1890,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-285c7c4c","status":"closed","title":"Reject bead dep edges that re-introduce the parent or any ancestor: part: part 2","updated_at":"2026-06-13T13:58:35.225122795Z","work-no-changes-count":1}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1103:{"acceptance":"1. ddx classifies each outcome per the addendum table (table-driven test). 2. Exactly one middle-\u003emax escalation, only on typed genuine failure; no_changes/dirty/transport/quota/auth do NOT escalate. 3. Per-pool in-flight max-attempt cap enforced (test simulates concurrent genuine failures, asserts cap). 4. quota-exhausted -\u003e global pool cooldown, not N per-bead mutations (test). 5. cd /Users/erik/Projects/ddx/cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... green. 6. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-07-02T22:52:12Z","closing_commit_sha":"65f0da163dbdd3845b28118fbc84fc0a965bfa2d","created_at":"2026-05-31T15:22:49.608697929Z","description":"Implement the ddx side of the FEAT-004 failure-classification table: ddx work maps each attempt outcome to exactly the action in the addendum table (success/already_satisfied=close; no_changes=close/unclaim NO tier-escalation; genuine impl/capability failure=escalate middle-\u003emax ONCE; dirty=clean+same-tier retry; transport=same-tier reroute; quota-exhausted=global pool cooldown; auth/setup=operator-attention; timeout=clean+retry then operator-attention; merge-conflict=unclaim+retry; max genuine failure=operator-attention). ddx owns the ONE middle-\u003emax tier escalation (per the escalation-owner decision bead fizeau-994604ec); a per-pool in-flight max-attempt cap prevents multi-worker stampede. Depends on the escalation-owner contract + the shared classifier (fizeau-44e98499).","events_attachment":"ddx-8d6af771/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-8d6af771","issue_type":"task","labels":["area:execute-bead","area:workers","kind:feature","spec:FEAT-004","phase:1","triage:no-changes-unjustified"],"notes":"SELF-CONTAINED SPEC (the ddx-side FEAT-004 here is Beads; the ROUTING policy lives in the fizeau repo, NOT accessible to a cold ddx agent — so the normative failure-classification table is inlined below; implement against THIS, do not look for a ddx FEAT-004 routing addendum):\n\nMap each ddx-work attempt outcome to exactly one action:\n- success / already_satisfied -\u003e close bead\n- no_changes (agent produced nothing + rationale) -\u003e close or unclaim per rationale; do NOT escalate tier\n- genuine implementation/capability failure (tests fail after real work; AC unmet) -\u003e escalate middle-\u003emax ONCE\n- dirty worktree / partial write -\u003e clean/reset worktree, same-tier retry (not escalation)\n- provider transport failure (i/o timeout, conn refused, 5xx) -\u003e same-tier reroute to another dispatchable candidate; no tier change\n- quota exhausted (retry_after) -\u003e GLOBAL pool cooldown/sleep until reset; NOT per-bead mutation, not escalation\n- auth/config missing, toolchain/setup failure -\u003e operator-attention (typed bead state); do not escalate\n- timeout / no-progress watchdog -\u003e clean + same-tier retry once, then operator-attention\n- merge/land conflict -\u003e unclaim + retry later; not escalation\n- max-tier genuine failure -\u003e operator-attention (stop escalating)\n\noperator-attention = explicit bead state transition (not a notification/indefinite wait). The single middle-\u003emax escalation owner is ddx work; a per-pool in-flight max-attempt cap prevents multi-worker stampede. Scope tests to avoid hangs (the prior attempt hit a 3m test timeout — bound any test that spawns/loops).","priority":0,"queue-rank":1290,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-f5db2b63","spec-id":"FEAT-004","status":"closed","title":"routing P1: ddx applies shared failure-classification table; single-owner one-hop middle-\u003emax escalation","updated_at":"2026-06-13T13:58:32.746455781Z","work-no-changes-count":1}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1152:{"acceptance":"1. Sub-skill bead-lifecycle/SKILL.md exists in all 5 shipped paths: skills/ddx/, cli/internal/skills/ddx/, .agents/skills/ddx/, .claude/skills/ddx/, .ddx/skills/ddx/. Identical content (or symlinked per existing bead-breakdown/ packaging convention).\n\n2. SKILL.md frontmatter has name=bead-lifecycle + description matching the proposed wording.\n\n3. SKILL.md body has 4 sections: LINT MODE, TRIAGE MODE, REFINE MODE, WAIVER TABLE. Each MODE section has explicit JSON output contract with named fields.\n\n4. bead-lifecycle/examples/ directory has 5-10 example files (curated by epic owner from closed beads; one per bead-type at minimum).\n\n5. WIRED-IN: parent ddx skill (.agents/skills/ddx/SKILL.md router section) gains a line pointing operators/agents at bead-lifecycle/ for \"score a bead\" / \"triage a failed attempt\" / \"refine a bead\" intents.\n\n6. Manual verification: 'find . -path \"*/bead-lifecycle/SKILL.md\" -not -path \"./.git/*\"' returns 5 paths.\n\n7. Manual verification: invoke skill via 'ddx agent run --harness=sonnet --text=\"MODE: lint\\nUse the bead-lifecycle skill to lint bead ddx-1e516bc9. Return JSON only.\"' and observe valid JSON output with score field.\n\n8. Conventional commit ending [\u003cthis-bead-id\u003e]. Stage the 5 SKILL.md paths + bead-lifecycle/examples/* only.\n\n9. lefthook run pre-commit passes (skill-schema check exists at lefthook config; will validate SKILL.md frontmatter).","archived_at":"2026-07-02T22:52:12Z","claimed-at":"2026-05-04T15:12:56Z","claimed-machine":"eitri","claimed-pid":"3551096","closing_commit_sha":"3af8c162d43c34005e61b8333d09ebee47f603b2","created_at":"2026-05-04T03:21:21.339191551Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-922b5b1f","depends_on_id":"ddx-9210f95a","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-04T03:21:23Z"}],"description":"PROBLEM\nPer epic ddx-a9d130d0 + ADR-023 (filed as ddx-XXXX): a sub-skill is needed at .agents/skills/ddx/bead-lifecycle/ (and 4 other shipped paths) carrying the rubric, examples, and judge prompts for lint + triage + refine modes. ddx try will compose this sub-skill via the runner library.\n\nROOT CAUSE\n.agents/skills/ddx/bead-breakdown/SKILL.md (existing) is the precedent for nested workflow sub-skills under the parent ddx skill. No equivalent exists for bead authoring quality. The bead-authoring-template.md at docs/helix/06-iterate/bead-authoring-template.md is the canonical template (per codex review) but only has 1 strong example + 1 weak example (line 98 of template).\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n1. Create sub-skill directory bead-lifecycle/ under each of 5 shipped paths (codex amendment): skills/ddx/, cli/internal/skills/ddx/, .agents/skills/ddx/, .claude/skills/ddx/, .ddx/skills/ddx/. SKILL.md + supporting files identical across all 5 (or symlinked if the build process supports it; check current bead-breakdown/ packaging).\n\n2. SKILL.md frontmatter: name=bead-lifecycle, description=\"Score, classify, and refine ddx beads. Used by ddx try hooks pre-dispatch (lint mode) and post-attempt (triage mode); operator-invocable for refine mode.\"\n\n3. SKILL.md body sections:\n   - LINT MODE: input=bead JSON; output=JSON {score 0-8, rationale, suggested_fixes, waivers_applied}. References the 8-criterion rubric from bead-authoring-template.md.\n   - TRIAGE MODE: input=bead + outcome event + session log excerpt; output=JSON {classification ∈ {already_satisfied, ambiguous, investigated_no_path, decomposed, operator_input_needed, routing, quota, transport, tests_red, merge_conflict, review_block, timeout}, recommended_action ∈ {refine_bead_and_retry, retry_with_more_context, file_children_and_supersede, escalate_to_operator, close_as_already_done, wait_and_retry, give_up}, rationale, suggested_amendments, suggested_followup_beads}.\n   - REFINE MODE: input=bead + (optional) prior triage output; output=YAML diff suggesting amendments to bead description + AC.\n   - WAIVER TABLE: per-bead-type criterion skips (doc-only skips named-tests + test-name; epic skips concrete-implementation; deletion skips wired-in-assertion). Codex: rubric-first, per-bead label override second.\n   - 5-10 CURATED EXAMPLES under bead-lifecycle/examples/: code bug, feature, doc-only, epic, deletion/rename, no-op investigation, upstream/external work. Operator (epic owner ddx-a9d130d0) curates from existing closed beads; LLM does not pick.\n\n4. Mode selection: invocation prompt MUST include \"MODE: lint|triage|refine\" as first line; SKILL.md instructs the LLM to read mode and apply only that mode's contract.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- LLM judgment baked into Go (this bead is data + markdown only; no code)\n- ddx try hook integration (separate child bead)\n- Tooling to validate skill output JSON (deferred; LLMs are usually well-behaved with structured-output prompts)\n- Cross-project skill packaging (DDx-only first per FEAT-015)","events_attachment":"ddx-922b5b1f/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-922b5b1f","issue_type":"task","labels":["adr:023","area:beads","area:skills","bead-quality","kind:feature","phase:2","reliability"],"owner":"erik","parent":"ddx-a9d130d0","priority":1,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-6b3018f9","status":"closed","title":"skill: bead-lifecycle sub-skill (lint + triage + refine modes) shipped to all 5 paths + 5-10 curated examples","updated_at":"2026-05-04T15:31:29.985073721Z","work-heartbeat-at":"2026-05-04T15:28:01.068427348Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1210:{"acceptance":"1. Add a regression test where a `ddx work --watch` attempt subprocess exits/cancels mid-implementation; the bead is unclaimed or closed with committed tracker evidence, and `ddx work status --json` reports no stale active work when no worker is alive.\n2. Add a regression test where an implementation produces no product commit but DDx records success; DDx must classify it as `already_satisfied` with explicit rationale/evidence or leave the bead open/unclaimed, not silently close as generic success with only metadata.\n3. Add a regression test for stale `.ddx/run-state/*.json` plus no live worker: startup cleanup or status reconciliation removes/ignores stale active work so the queue exposes ready beads again.\n4. Add a test or guard proving pre-claim readiness/lifecycle dispatch does not mutate the project root; if mutation is intentionally blocked, the warning includes a stable code and does not repeat as operator noise for every bead.\n5. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./cmd/... ./internal/agent/... ./internal/workerstatus/... -run \"Work|RunState|Readiness|Lifecycle|Status\" -count=1` passes.\n6. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.","archived_at":"2026-07-02T22:52:12Z","closing_commit_sha":"6225d6c4a5e72f474b4b475c184d0ca693d14cf8","created_at":"2026-06-13T03:51:59.987209153Z","description":"Incident observed in sibling repo `/home/erik/Projects/axon` on 2026-06-13 while running `ddx work --watch --idle-interval 15s --request-timeout 45m` from Codex.\n\nSymptoms:\n1. Two background launches of `ddx work --watch` exited immediately with empty logs: PID 819208 `/tmp/axon-ddx-worker-20260612-232505.log`, then PID 819691 `/tmp/axon-ddx-worker-20260612-232537.log`. `ddx work plan --json` showed a valid next bead, so the queue was not empty.\n2. Foreground `ddx work --once --request-timeout 45m` succeeded on Axon bead `axon-5c6af8f0`, proving the route/queue could execute.\n3. Foreground `ddx work --watch --idle-interval 15s --request-timeout 45m` repeatedly emitted pre-claim readiness warnings: `readiness route unavailable: lifecycle dispatch: project root mutation rejected for bead \u003cid\u003e (continuing)`. Seen for Axon beads `axon-5c6af8f0`, `axon-7e75384c`, and `axon-a8e564c1`. The warning was recorded as `intake.warn` with `rule_id=pre_claim_intake.system_unready`.\n4. For Axon bead `axon-7e75384c`, watch/attempt output included `Cancel received, shutting down gracefully`; DDx recorded `status: success` and closed the bead even though the landed implementation commit trail contained only execution evidence / harness metadata, no product code diff. The acceptance tests happened to pass independently, but `.ddx/beads.jsonl` closure was left dirty and had to be committed manually (`7351979f`).\n5. For Axon bead `axon-a8e564c1`, the watch session exited with code -1 during implementation after reading CI/package files. After exit, `ddx work status --json` reported no live workers but still reported active work from `.ddx/run-state/20260613T034907-3d00f60f.json`; the bead remained open/claimed and queue status was `ready=0`, `worker_ready=0`, `active_work.count=1`. That jams the queue until an operator manually unclaims/cleans/restarts.\n\nExpected behavior: if the worker process exits or its harness subprocess is cancelled, DDx should either complete/close with committed tracker evidence, or release the bead and clear stale active run-state. `ddx work --watch` should not leave the project with zero workers, a claimed open bead, stale active run-state, and no ready work. The readiness route should not attempt a project-root mutation during pre-claim analysis, or the warning should include a precise non-blocking explanation and not recur on every bead.\n\nReproduction context from Axon:\n- project: `/home/erik/Projects/axon`\n- ready beads: `axon-5c6af8f0`, then `axon-7e75384c`, then `axon-a8e564c1`\n- stale files after crash: `.ddx/run-state/20260613T034907-3d00f60f.json`, `.ddx/workers/agent-loop-1781322253776691221/status.json`\n- command: `ddx work --watch --idle-interval 15s --request-timeout 45m`\n\nIn-scope files: DDx worker/watch loop, run-state/liveness cleanup, pre-claim readiness/lifecycle dispatch, and tests around process exit/cancel handling.\nOut-of-scope: Axon product code, model routing policy, and general host process cleanup not tied to DDx run-state.","events_attachment":"ddx-9aa2151d/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-9aa2151d","issue_type":"bug","labels":["area:lifecycle","area:run-state","area:workers","kind:bug","kind:reliability","source:axon-incident"],"notes":"Additional Axon evidence from 2026-06-14: after manually implementing and verifying Axon bead axon-cd532283, ddx bead close axon-cd532283 produced no output for roughly 93 seconds before exiting 0. This repeated the prior slow-close behavior seen on Axon tracker-only closes. The command eventually updated the tracker, but the silent delay is operationally ambiguous for agents because it looks like a stuck close while holding the tracker workflow.","priority":0,"queue-rank":2200,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-1e2e1b93","spec-id":"FEAT-010","status":"closed","title":"fix: keep ddx work watch from leaving stale active run-state","updated_at":"2026-06-29T20:41:18.367528934Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1247:{"acceptance":"1. internal/agentmetrics/ package with loader + bucket classifier. 2. Run-store first, bundles fallback. 3. already_satisfied counts as success per locked decision. 4. Tests cover bucket assignment, multi-source dedupe (matches Story 8.0 semantics).","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","claimed-at":"2026-05-03T05:55:58Z","claimed-machine":"eitri","claimed-pid":"4025192","closing_commit_sha":"abb746e78f5430091768feb11c898bbfb0216550","created_at":"2026-05-02T07:03:45.40862623Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-9fea5624","depends_on_id":"ddx-65543530","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-02T07:03:45Z"}],"description":"Create cli/internal/agentmetrics/ that loads attempt outcomes from FEAT-010 run-store first, .ddx/executions/ as fallback. Per-attempt cost/duration/exit_code is in result.json today; harness/provider/tier come from bead events (kind:routing, kind:escalation-summary). Bucket classifier defines outcome buckets terminal-status aligned.","events_attachment":"ddx-9fea5624/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-9fea5624","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2","story:11","area:metrics","kind:feature"],"owner":"erik","parent":"ddx-64b9a198","priority":2,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-7ab2d4e0","status":"closed","title":"agentmetrics: internal/agentmetrics package over storage-abstracted loader (run-store first, legacy bundles fallback)","updated_at":"2026-05-03T06:07:06.488860751Z","work-heartbeat-at":"2026-05-03T06:05:28.871697704Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1268:{"acceptance":"- [ ] work runs post-merge review by default\n- [ ] Review tier auto-selected (max(impl_tier+1, smart))\n- [ ] Review verdict JSON is stable and documented\n- [ ] APPROVE closes bead with review evidence attached\n- [ ] REQUEST_CHANGES reopens bead via ddx bead reopen and triggers next tier\n- [ ] BLOCK stops escalation and flags for human\n- [ ] --no-review opt-out works; 'review:skip' label works\n- [ ] Integration test: impossible-AC bead produces REQUEST_CHANGES forever without infinite-looping (bounded by max-tier)","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","claimed-at":"2026-04-15T05:36:55Z","claimed-machine":"eitri","claimed-pid":"3766264","closing_commit_sha":"3c149a123610788c014051e0bae082cb89aee69d","created_at":"2026-04-15T00:49:48.524036278Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-a317208c","depends_on_id":"ddx-fdf031c9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-15T00:49:53Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-a317208c","depends_on_id":"ddx-518b2690","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-15T00:49:53Z"}],"description":"work currently closes a bead on merge. There is no automated post-merge review step validating the commit against the bead's AC. Real-world practice requires a second-opinion agent (typically a higher-capability tier) to produce APPROVE / REQUEST_CHANGES.\n\n## Principle\n\nReview is on-by-default with zero flags. The tool picks a tier \u003e= the implementation tier (defaulting to smart). The user overrides only in exceptional cases.\n\n## Default flow\n\n- Implementation agent runs at current tier (see ddx-dc231144 tier-based escalation)\n- On successful merge, tool automatically renders a review prompt via 'ddx bead review' (ddx-fdf031c9)\n- Review agent runs at max(impl_tier + 1, smart)\n- Review result is structured JSON: { verdict: APPROVE | REQUEST_CHANGES | BLOCK, findings: [...] }\n- APPROVE → close bead, attach review evidence\n- REQUEST_CHANGES → reopen bead via 'ddx bead reopen' (ddx-44084b3e), append review body, let the tier-escalation policy pick the next attempt\n- BLOCK → stop escalating, flag for human\n\n## Rare overrides\n\n- --no-review (skip review entirely — e.g., doc-only beads in a tight loop)\n- --review-harness / --review-model (explicit reviewer override for debug)\n- Per-bead opt-out via a 'review:skip' label on the bead\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- ddx-fdf031c9 (ddx bead review command) provides the review prompt template\n- ddx-44084b3e (ddx bead reopen) provides the atomic reopen primitive\n- ddx-518b2690 (plain --output text) makes extracting the review verdict trivial\n- ddx-5bac3c6b (provider health probe) feeds the reviewer tier selection\n\n## Context\n\nObserved during axon ADR-018 work:\n- qwen3-coder-next merged A1 with real AC gaps (missing round-trip tests, zero Postgres coverage, scope creep)\n- Without review, the bead would have closed silently and the gaps would surface only at epic rollup — much later and much more expensive to fix\n- Review took 41s + a few minutes of reading. Cheap relative to the real cost of shipping broken code downstream.","events_attachment":"ddx-a317208c/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-a317208c","issue_type":"task","labels":["helix","area:agent","area:exec","kind:feature","gap:review-loop"],"notes":"\u003coperator-feedback 2026-04-15\u003e\nCritical gap discovered during axon ADR-018 work:\n\nWhen a bead is reopened after a REQUEST_CHANGES review, the REVIEW FINDINGS must be surfaced to the next execute-bead attempt. Today this fails silently because:\n\n1. Review findings posted via 'ddx bead update --notes' are NOT included in the execute-bead prompt.md. Execute-bead threads only \u003cdescription\u003e and \u003cacceptance\u003e into the XML payload.\n\n2. Therefore a reopen-via-notes does NOT communicate the review findings to the next agent. The agent reads the original description + AC, sees the existing code already matches the description, and declares 'already_satisfied' — auto-closing the bead.\n\n3. The workaround I had to use was updating the DESCRIPTION directly with the review findings. But then the description is no longer a stable spec — it's a moving target carrying review history.\n\n## Required behavior\n\nWhen a bead is reopened with a review verdict attached, execute-bead's generated prompt MUST include the most recent REQUEST_CHANGES review findings as a distinct section, e.g.:\n\n  \u003creview-findings iteration=\"2\" reviewer=\"claude-opus-4-6\"\u003e\n  BLOCKING: UserIdentity field 'subject' should be 'external_id' per ADR-018 §3\n  PARTIAL: aud-array test asserts serde_json::Error instead of AuthError::CredentialMalformed\n  ...\n  \u003c/review-findings\u003e\n\nAnd the execute-bead instructions should read: 'If \u003creview-findings\u003e is present, address each BLOCKING finding before claiming the work complete. Do not declare already_satisfied if any BLOCKING finding is unaddressed.'\n\n## Observed failure mode\n\nSonnet at iter 2 of axon-43ed769b read the prompt (which had the original description with 'subject' and the unchanged AC), verified all type shapes match, ran tests green, and wrote a no_changes_rationale declaring the work complete. The 'already_satisfied' close path auto-closed the bead. The actual BLOCKING issue (wrong field name) was invisible to the execute-bead layer. I had to manually reopen and rewrite the description with fix-up instructions inline.\n\n## This should be part of the post-review epic scope\n\nMaking review findings round-trip through the prompt is half of what 'post-review agent in work' means. Adding to this bead's scope:\n\n- Review verdict JSON includes a 'findings' array with severity (blocking|partial|nit) and location\n- Reopen path persists the findings to the bead\n- execute-bead prompt rendering pulls latest review findings and injects them as a distinct XML section\n- Execute-bead instructions teach the agent to treat blocking findings as first-class work items\n- no_changes / already_satisfied paths check for unaddressed blocking findings before closing\n\u003c/operator-feedback\u003e","owner":"ddx","parent":"ddx-32b3008e","priority":1,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-451c8bc5","status":"closed","title":"exec: post-merge review agent on-by-default in work","updated_at":"2026-04-15T05:57:50.41702859Z","work-heartbeat-at":"2026-04-15T05:57:25.094183105Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1322:{"acceptance":"1. cli/internal/agent/types.go Result includes predicted route fields for speed TPS, cost USD per 1k tokens, cost source, and predicted power without removing ActualPower.\n2. TestDrainServiceEvents_CapturesRouteEconomics verifies routing_decision.candidates for the selected eligible model populate speed_tps, cost_usd_per_1k_tokens, cost_source, and power.\n3. TestExecuteBead_ReportIncludesRouteEconomics verifies ExecuteBeadReport/result.json carries harness/provider/model plus predicted speed/cost/power fields.\n4. TestWorkDefaultOutput_PrintsSelectedRouteEconomics verifies non-JSON ddx work output includes harness, provider, model, predicted speed, cost, and power for an attempted bead.\n5. TestWorkJSONOutput_IncludesRouteEconomicsWithoutHumanLines verifies --json includes the fields structurally and does not include the human route line.\n6. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... green.\n7. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"4e84daafb828099fa148950212e2ecfdbecd8eb9","created_at":"2026-05-04T21:40:38.258600505Z","description":"PROBLEM\n  The default human output for ddx work should tell the operator which harness/provider/model were selected and the predicted speed, cost, and power for that route. Today the summary is mostly bead-level status, so operators cannot quickly see whether fizeau routed to the expected class of model or why a run is slow/expensive.\n\nROOT CAUSE\n  fizeau already emits routing_decision with selected harness/provider/model and candidate components: service_execute.go:431 emits ServiceRoutingDecisionData, and service_events.go:142-183 exposes candidates[].cost_usd_per_1k_tokens plus components.power and components.speed_tps. DDx drains only harness/provider/model and selected candidate power in cli/internal/agent/agent_runner_service.go:234-318; Result in cli/internal/agent/types.go:96-122 has ActualPower but no predicted_speed_tps or predicted_cost_usd_per_1k_tokens. cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:831-850 copies only harness/provider/model/ActualPower from Result, and cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go:1955-1961 prints failed attempts without route economics.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n  - Extend cli/internal/agent.Result and ExecuteBeadReport with route prediction fields: PredictedSpeedTPS float64, PredictedCostUSDPer1kTokens float64, PredictedPower int, and CostSource string if available. Keep ActualPower for final/routing_actual behavior.\n  - Update drainServiceEvents to select the eligible candidate matching routing_decision.model and copy components.speed_tps, cost_usd_per_1k_tokens, cost_source, and components.power.\n  - Propagate the fields through executeOnService -\u003e ExecuteBeadWithConfig -\u003e ExecuteBeadReport -\u003e result.json and execute-bead event bodies.\n  - In default non-JSON ddx work / work output, print a concise route line near bead claim or first attempt completion: harness=\u003ch\u003e provider=\u003cp\u003e model=\u003cm\u003e power=\u003cn\u003e speed=\u003ctps\u003e tok/s cost=$\u003cx\u003e/1k tok. Keep --json output machine-readable and add fields there rather than human prose.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n  - Changing fizeau routing scoring.\n  - New upstream fizeau fields; current routing_decision already has the needed candidate data.\n  - Progress-event rendering; tracked in ddx-cad808ea.\n\nPARENT\n  No parent.\n\nDEPS\n  No deps. fizeau already emits routing_decision candidate cost/speed/power fields.","events_attachment":"ddx-ad41ccb1/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-ad41ccb1","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2","area:agent","area:cli","kind:feature","operator-ux","routing","triage:no-changes-unjustified"],"priority":1,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-b91e3c92","status":"closed","title":"agent-output: print selected route economics in default ddx work output","updated_at":"2026-05-06T00:10:59.782348627Z","work-last-detail":"agent exited without a commit or no_changes_rat