.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1412:{"acceptance":"1. testdata/omlx-wire/ contains at least 2 JSONL fixtures: one happy-path (successful bead close), one error-path (model-side failure cleanly recorded).\n\n2. cli/internal/agent/omlx_e2e_test.go runs a ddx work execute-bead orchestration against a test-double provider that replays the fixtures, asserting: no 'unexpected end of JSON input', final outcome matches fixture expectation, bead state mutates correctly.\n\n3. Test runs in CI without requiring a live omlx endpoint.\n\n4. Opt-in live smoke test (//go:build omlx_smoke) covers the same happy-path scenario against a real vidar-omlx when invoked manually.\n\n5. README or docs/ entry describes how to regenerate fixtures via scripts/capture-omlx-fixture.sh when omlx server behavior changes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","claimed-at":"2026-04-18T04:14:07Z","claimed-machine":"eitri","claimed-pid":"1833233","closing_commit_sha":"ad14ee84ff0faa5b8754f5274ea795fb1511cde7","created_at":"2026-04-18T03:01:36.207143767Z","description":"## Context\n\nddx-agent v0.3.14 shipped the SSE comment-frame filter that unblocks omlx. Manual dogfooding (2026-04-18) confirmed a single bead executing via vidar-omlx for 6+ minutes with 17,000+ streaming events before the fix caused the regression this bead is meant to prevent: we have no automated assertion that the omlx path actually stays healthy.\n\nBoth fresh-eyes reviews (codex + opus, 2026-04-18) flagged: 'missing bead for v0.3.14 consumer-side smoke test in DDx'. This is that bead.\n\n## Fix\n\nAdd an end-to-end smoke test that runs a real ddx work invocation against a recorded-or-live omlx endpoint and asserts the attempt closes (or at least produces a closing-status result: success / already_satisfied / a genuine model-side error) without surfacing 'unexpected end of JSON input' or silent stream termination.\n\nTwo implementation options:\n\n1. **Record + replay via virtual harness** (preferred for CI isolation). Capture a full AGENT_DEBUG_WIRE_STREAM_FULL=1 trace of a successful vidar-omlx run, store it as a fixture, replay via a test double that emulates omlx's SSE quirks (keep-alive comment frames, reasoning warmup silence, reasoning_content deltas). Test asserts ddx-agent SDK consumes the full stream, ddx work's execute-bead orchestrator records closing status, and bead state mutates correctly.\n\n2. **Live smoke, opt-in** (developer-machine only). A test file guarded by build tag  that makes a real request to vidar-omlx. Useful for catching provider-side regressions (e.g., omlx server ships a breaking change). Skip in CI.\n\nDo BOTH: option 1 for CI signal, option 2 for manual release verification.\n\n## What this prevents\n\n- Regression: a future ddx-agent bump reintroduces the SSE-comment-frame bug or similar streaming defect. CI fixture test catches it before the bump merges.\n- Regression: DDx-side change breaks the omlx dispatch path (e.g., adds a header that trips omlx's parser). CI catches it.\n- Silent-success: ddx work completes but actually landed a bogus result_rev because of a subtle SSE-frame-dropping bug. Fixture replay asserts the expected final outcome.\n\n## Coverage target\n\nMinimum: one happy-path fixture (successful bead close) AND one error-path fixture (model returns malformed tool-call; execute-bead records task_failed cleanly without corrupting the bead tracker).\n\n## Files likely touched\n\n- cli/internal/agent/omlx_e2e_test.go (new) — fixture replay + assertions\n- testdata/omlx-wire/ (new) — captured AGENT_DEBUG_WIRE JSONL fixtures\n- scripts/capture-omlx-fixture.sh (new) — helper to regenerate fixtures against a live endpoint\n\n## Depends on\n\n- agent-941e7e42 (AGENT_DEBUG_WIRE_STREAM_FULL=1) shipped in v0.3.14 — needed to capture full fixtures.","events_attachment":"ddx-bbb2d177/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-bbb2d177","issue_type":"task","labels":["ddx","phase:test","kind:testing","area:agent","area:omlx","goal:throughput-per-dollar"],"owner":"erik","priority":1,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-a32f1082","spec-id":"FEAT-006","status":"closed","title":"eval: v0.3.14 consumer-side end-to-end smoke — ddx work via vidar-omlx closes one bead","updated_at":"2026-04-18T04:31:47.76623379Z","work-heartbeat-at":"2026-04-18T04:30:37.397634223Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1482:{"acceptance":"1. cli/internal/server/workers.go does not call Fizeau RouteStatus and does not iterate route candidates. 2. Any remaining ResolveRoute calls in worker code are status/preflight only, documented, and covered by tests that they do not pin or mutate Execute routing. 3. Worker GraphQL/API status uses Fizeau HarnessInfo/ProviderInfo availability fields directly for display. 4. rg -n 'RouteStatus\\(|\\.Routes|\\.Candidates' cli/internal/server/workers.go returns no hits. 5. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/server/... -run 'Worker|Provider' passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","created_at":"2026-05-05T01:55:25.997358202Z","description":"Worker health/status paths should not inspect Fizeau route tables or infer provider eligibility. DDx should either display Fizeau's harness/provider status DTOs directly or call a purpose-built health/status method. Audit cli/internal/server/workers.go and related GraphQL worker surfaces for code that calls ResolveRoute or RouteStatus to infer harness health, candidate availability, or provider cooldown. Keep execution-time routing inside Fizeau Execute. Status-only previews may call ResolveRoute, but worker lifecycle decisions should not duplicate Fizeau routing semantics.","events_attachment":"ddx-c47ec03b/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-c47ec03b","issue_type":"task","labels":["area:server","area:workers","area:routing","kind:cleanup","triage:no-changes-unjustified"],"priority":1,"schema_version":1,"status":"closed","title":"Stop DDx worker health checks from interpreting routing internals","updated_at":"2026-05-05T02:09:34.688942684Z","work-last-detail":"agent exited without a commit or no_changes_rationale.txt","work-last-status":"no_changes","work-no-changes-count":1,"work-retry-after":"2026-05-05T08:09:34Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1528:{"acceptance":"1. ddx bead migrate --to axon command exists and is documented in --help.\n2. After migration, every bead (including events and archive entries) round-trips: ddx bead export | diff against pre-migration export = empty.\n3. Idempotent: running twice produces no duplicate beads.\n4. Test fixture at cli/internal/bead/testdata/ covers representative beads.jsonl + archive.\n5. TestMigrate_AxonBackend_RoundTrip verifies post-migration export matches pre-migration export.\n6. TestMigrate_AxonBackend_Idempotent verifies re-run does not duplicate beads.\n7. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/bead/... green.\n8. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"669fac38d22846713fd3084fe44c8fe701e07cf0","created_at":"2026-05-02T23:09:25.439706849Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-cb63cdfc","depends_on_id":"ddx-95ec5ed5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-02T23:09:48Z"}],"description":"PROBLEM\nBeads stored in .ddx/beads.jsonl and .ddx/beads-archive.jsonl cannot be migrated to the axon backend without a dedicated migration command. Operators switching to the axon backend must manually reconstruct state or risk data loss.\n\nROOT CAUSE\n- cli/cmd/ does not contain a 'ddx bead migrate' subcommand or --to flag.\n- cli/internal/bead/ has backend_jsonl.go (JSONL reader) but no migration path to write into the axon Backend interface (ddx-95ec5ed5, a dep).\n- Without an idempotent migration, re-running risks duplicates; without a round-trip check, data loss is silent.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- Add ddx bead migrate --to axon command under cli/cmd/ reading .ddx/beads.jsonl and .ddx/beads-archive.jsonl and writing losslessly into the axon backend via the Backend interface.\n- Idempotent: re-running on an already-migrated store is a no-op (dedup by bead ID).\n- Does not delete source files (operator removes after verification).\n- Add test fixture under cli/internal/bead/testdata/ covering: representative beads.jsonl + archive.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Axon backend implementation (ddx-95ec5ed5, a dep).\n- Migration to backends other than axon.\n- Automatic deletion of source files.","events_attachment":"ddx-cb63cdfc/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-cb63cdfc","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2","area:beads","area:storage","kind:tool","backend-migration","triage:no-changes-unjustified"],"notes":"REVIEW:BLOCK\n\nDiff contains only execution evidence files (manifest.json, result.json) under .ddx/executions/. No implementation of the migrate --to axon command, no test fixtures, no source code changes. Cannot evaluate AC against missing implementation.","parent":"ddx-5d49b14e","priority":2,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-f4c44895","status":"closed","title":"Migration tool: .ddx/beads.jsonl + archive → axon backend","updated_at":"2026-05-05T18:29:24.396245515Z","work-last-detail":"agent exited without a commit or no_changes_rationale.txt","work-last-status":"no_changes","work-no-changes-count":2,"work-retry-after":"2026-05-05T17:41:36Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1577:{"acceptance":"1. `TestExecuteBeadLoop_NiflheimEvidence_DecomposedParentIsExecutionIneligible` adds a self-contained Niflheim evidence case for `mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale` with `orchestrator_action: decompose`, child bead IDs, and `outcome_reason=decomposed`; it asserts the parent is marked execution-ineligible/proposed or dependency-waiting according to policy.\n2. `TestWorkRetryEscalation_NiflheimEvidence_DecomposedParentDoesNotRaiseMinPower` proves decomposed-parent and no-changes-decompose outcomes do not schedule another implementation attempt and do not increase requested min power/profile.\n3. `TestExecuteBeadResult_NiflheimEvidence_DecomposedParentDecisionAudit` proves result JSON/event bodies include `failure_class`, `retry_action`, `escalation_count`, requested/actual routing facts, decomposed-child bead IDs, and the execution-ineligible/proposed/dependency-waiting decision.\n4. Existing related behavior from `ddx-e1a576a7` remains aligned as precedent; this bead does not edit Niflheim beads or implement child work.\n5. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -run 'NiflheimEvidence|DecomposedParent|RetryEscalation|DecomposedParentDecisionAudit' -count=1` passes.\n6. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -count=1` passes.\n7. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.","archived_at":"2026-07-02T22:52:12Z","closing_commit_sha":"c7b3605270fbae8055c09d3e04a656736d208a5f","created_at":"2026-06-08T06:21:15.999176918Z","description":"PROBLEM\nA Niflheim decomposed parent bead kept consuming attempts and escalated to stronger routes despite evidence that the bead was already split into executable children. Stronger models cannot implement a parent bead whose correct action is decompose/execution-ineligible/operator work.\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:2175-2315` handles `PreClaimIntakeTooLargeDecomposed`, but missing or empty decomposition paths can warn and continue.\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:3826-3831` recognizes execution-ineligible/decomposed state only after the bead has the right metadata.\n- `cli/internal/agent/failclass/failclass.go:103-142` says only genuine failure should escalate, but decomposed-parent/no-changes outcomes can still reach implementation retry and min-power escalation.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nAdd a self-contained Niflheim-style decomposed-parent fixture or table-driven case under `cli/internal/agent/...` with `mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale`, `orchestrator_action: decompose`, child bead IDs, and `outcome_reason=decomposed`. Classify the parent as execution-ineligible, proposed, dependency-waiting, or operator-attention according to policy before another implementation attempt is scheduled. Preserve child bead evidence in the event/result audit.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Do not change Fizeau route selection or hard-code concrete provider/model names.\n- Do not edit Niflheim beads or Niflheim implementation code.\n- Do not duplicate the low-level index-contention fix tracked by `ddx-2965925e`.\n- Do not duplicate the post-commit review/land timeout work tracked by `ddx-b2846610`.\n- Do not duplicate the repeated pre-claim warn operator-attention bead `ddx-d67f124e`.\n- Do not implement a full operator-lane product workflow beyond state transitions/events needed to keep the worker from blind retry or false close.\n\nINTERSECTIONS\nParent: `ddx-3106674f`. Dependencies to preserve: `ddx-2965925e`, `ddx-b2846610`, `ddx-d67f124e`. Related precedent: `ddx-e1a576a7` for execution-ineligible decomposed parent behavior. Related quality framework: `ddx-a9d130d0`, `ddx-ac10e7af`. Governing references: FEAT-010, TP-021, ADR-024, docs/dev/engineering-principles.md:39-45.","events_attachment":"ddx-d2725150/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-d2725150","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:iterate","area:agent","area:execute-bead","area:workers","area:review","kind:bug","kind:reliability","severity:critical","spec:FEAT-010","spec:TP-021","adr:024","incident:niflheim-2026-06-06","prevention"],"parent":"ddx-334c0958","priority":0,"queue-rank":2100,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-e413b018","status":"closed","title":"Mark decomposed parent beads execution-ineligible before retry","updated_at":"2026-06-13T13:58:36.039852043Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1592:{"acceptance":"1. `TestExecuteBeadLoop_NiflheimEvidence_DecomposedParentIsExecutionIneligible` simulates `mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale` with `orchestrator_action: decompose`, child bead IDs, and `outcome_reason=decomposed`.\n2. The test asserts the parent is marked execution-ineligible/proposed or dependency-waiting according to policy and that no further implementation attempt or min-power escalation is scheduled.\n3. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -run 'DecomposedParent' -count=1` passes.\n4. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -count=1` passes.\n5. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.","archived_at":"2026-07-02T22:52:12Z","closing_commit_sha":"a37b69f7e9ab1baf6e14e96006d53d56b8cf9bb5","created_at":"2026-06-08T06:13:49.850658966Z","description":"PROBLEM\nA parent bead that has already been decomposed can still re-enter the worker as if it were an executable task. That keeps spending attempts on a structurally ineligible parent instead of moving on to its children.\n\nROOT CAUSE\n`cli/internal/agent/recovery_decompose.go:130-210` already marks decomposed children with `Parent=beadID` and sets the parent execution-eligible flag to false, but the main worker loop still has paths that continue past decomposition-like intake and retry handling. `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:2175-2315` handles some intake decomposition cases, and `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:3818-3840` continues processing other outcome branches without consistently parking a parent whose own `no_changes` rationale says to decompose.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- When the worker sees `mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale` with `orchestrator_action: decompose`, child IDs, and `outcome_reason=decomposed`, mark the parent execution-ineligible or proposed before another implementation attempt.\n- Do not schedule another implementation run or min-power escalation for that parent.\n- Keep the parent visible as a decomposition boundary, not as a retriable implementation failure.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Do not change child-bead content, land handling, or review gating in this child.\n- Do not alter the decomposer output format beyond what is needed to detect the decomposed-parent state.","events_attachment":"ddx-d4817c9b/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-d4817c9b","issue_type":"bug","labels":["phase:iterate","area:agent","area:execute-bead","area:workers","area:review","kind:bug","kind:reliability","severity:critical","spec:FEAT-010","spec:TP-021","adr:024","incident:niflheim-2026-06-06","prevention"],"parent":"ddx-334c0958","priority":0,"queue-rank":2050,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-5e04821f","spec-id":"FEAT-010","status":"closed","title":"agent: park decomposed parents before retrying implementation","updated_at":"2026-06-13T13:58:35.835830846Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1657:{"acceptance":"1. `TestExecuteBeadLoop_NiflheimEvidence_RepeatedPreClaimSystemWarningBecomesOperatorAttention` adds a self-contained Niflheim evidence case for repeated readiness timeout/system-unready warnings with generated DDx artifact dirt and asserts the worker records an operator-visible system-unready/operator-attention state after the configured threshold.\n2. `TestWorkRetryEscalation_NiflheimEvidence_OnlySemanticFailuresRaiseMinPower` proves only semantic acceptance/review failures can increase requested min power/profile; repeated pre-claim system warnings, land coordination, decomposed-parent outcomes, and dirty generated DDx evidence do not raise min power.\n3. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./cmd/... ./internal/agent/... -run \"TestExecuteBeadLoop_NiflheimEvidence_RepeatedPreClaimSystemWarningBecomesOperatorAttention|TestWorkRetryEscalation_NiflheimEvidence_OnlySemanticFailuresRaiseMinPower\" -count=1`\n4. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 lefthook run pre-commit`","archived_at":"2026-07-02T22:52:12Z","closing_commit_sha":"9fdbe3d79c685109d6f07dd675a0fcc250535490","created_at":"2026-06-08T16:59:04.725269086Z","description":"PROBLEM\nParent bead ddx-eea2dfca is too broad for one execution pass. This child owns part 1 of 3 of that parent scope.\n\nROOT CAUSE\nPROBLEM\nA Niflheim worker repeatedly emitted pre-claim readiness/intake warnings for the same systemic dirty/generated DDx artifact condition and continued polling/releasing. That looks like forward progress but does not create a clear operator-visible system-unready lane after the configured threshold.\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:1967-2072` emits pre-claim timeout/system-unready outcomes as warn-only by default and continues implementation when strict intake blocking is off.\n- `cli/internal/agent/failclass/failclass.go:103-142` says setup/dirty worktree/system outcomes should not escalate, but repeated pre-claim warnings are not consistently classified into retry/operator-attention decisions before worker retry loops continue.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nAdd a self-contained Niflheim-style pre-claim fixture or table-driven case under `cli/internal/agent/...` for repeated readiness timeout/system-unready warnings with generated DDx artifact dirt such as `.ddx/harness-sessions/...json`. After the configured same-fingerprint threshold, classify the condition as system-unready/operator-attention and release/park without implementation retry or model escalation. Align with `ddx-d67f124e` rather than duplicating its lower-level implementation.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Do not change Fizeau route selection or hard-code concrete provider/model names.\n- Do not edit Niflheim beads or Niflheim implementation code.\n- Do not duplicate the low-level index-contention fix tracked by `ddx-2965925e`.\n- Do not duplicate the post-commit review/land timeout work tracked by `ddx-b2846610`.\n- Do not duplicate the repeated pre-claim warn operator-attention bead `ddx-d67f124e`; this bead only adds the Niflheim observation as regression coverage and decision/audit wiring.\n- Do not implement a full operator-lane product workflow beyond state transitions/events needed to keep the worker from blind retry or false close.\n\nINTERSECTIONS\nParent: `ddx-3106674f`. Dependencies to preserve: `ddx-2965925e`, `ddx-b2846610`, `ddx-d67f124e`. Related: `ddx-e1a576a7`, `ddx-a9d130d0`, `ddx-ac10e7af`. Governing references: FEAT-010, TP-021, ADR-024, docs/dev/engineering-principles.md:39-45.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nImplement only this child acceptance slice:\n- `TestExecuteBeadLoop_NiflheimEvidence_RepeatedPreClaimSystemWarningBecomesOperatorAttention` adds a self-contained Niflheim evidence case for repeated readiness timeout/system-unready warnings with generated DDx artifact dirt and asserts the worker records an operator-visible system-unready/operator-attention state after the configured threshold.\n- `TestWorkRetryEscalation_NiflheimEvidence_OnlySemanticFailuresRaiseMinPower` proves only semantic acceptance/review failures can increase requested min power/profile; repeated pre-claim system warnings, land coordination, decomposed-parent outcomes, and dirty generated DDx evidence do not raise min power.\n\nNON-SCOPE\nDo not implement parent acceptance criteria assigned to sibling child beads. Preserve every parent non-scope constraint unless this child explicitly narrows it.","events_attachment":"ddx-df319cf9/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-df319cf9","issue_type":"task","labels":["adr:024","area:agent","area:execute-bead","area:review","area:workers","decomposed","incident:niflheim-2026-06-06","kind:bug","kind:reliability","phase:iterate","prevention","severity:critical","spec:FEAT-010","spec:TP-021","triage:no-changes-unjustified"],"needs-human-reason":"circuit-breaker: mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale repeated within 24h; operator review required","needs-human-since":"2026-06-16T07:10:13Z","needs-human-source":"ddx work","parent":"ddx-eea2dfca","priority":0,"queue-rank":2120,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-f0946b14","status":"closed","title":"Classify repeated pre-claim system warnings as operator-visible worker s: part 1","updated_at":"2026-06-28T03:22:52.088572401Z","work-no-changes-count":1}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1738:{"acceptance":"1. Each named function/file confirmed unreferenced (production + tests + reflection). 2. Removed. 3. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./... green. 4. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go build ./... green. 5. ~500 LOC reduction documented.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"bbe9fe2e28fb1d1af784a692611f5b1a98f6f5a8","created_at":"2026-05-02T20:15:16.841978071Z","description":"Per /tmp/agent-surface-dead-code-audit.md: format.go (entirely), grade.go:buildGradingPrompt (un-bounded variant superseded), routing_metrics.go:AppendBurnSummary + parseWindowMinutes, model_catalog_yaml.go:WriteModelCatalogYAML, cmd-side harnessHealthyViaService + loadExecutionsMirrorConfig. ~500 LOC of dead code.\n\nVerify each is genuinely unreferenced (deadcode -test ./... output at /tmp/deadcode-agent-with-tests.txt) before deleting. Some may be reflection-invoked or test-only — confirm with grep before removal.\n\nIndependent of refactor.","events_attachment":"ddx-edcbebb2/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-edcbebb2","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2","story:10","area:agent","kind:cleanup","dead-code","triage:needs-investigation","triage:no-changes-unjustified"],"parent":"ddx-e34994e2","priority":3,"schema_version":1,"status":"closed","title":"cleanup: drop quorum/benchmark/grading/metrics dead functions (~500 LOC)","updated_at":"2026-05-05T10:17:59.060327001Z","work-last-detail":"agent exited without a commit or no_changes_rationale.txt","work-last-status":"no_changes","work-no-changes-count":2,"work-retry-after":"2026-05-05T16:17:58Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1753:{"acceptance":"AC1. Land-coordinator refuses to merge a bead result whose net diff deletes more than N lines from a single file (configurable threshold, default 200) UNLESS the agent's no_changes_rationale.txt or commit message explicitly acknowledges and justifies the deletion (e.g. 'intentional file removal: \u003creason\u003e').\n\nAC2. Land-coordinator runs a basic sanity gate before merging: the file must still parse for its filetype (TypeScript files compile, Svelte files have valid \u003cscript\u003e/\u003ctemplate\u003e/\u003cstyle\u003e structure if they had one previously, JSON is valid JSON, etc.). Failed parse = preserve as iteration ref, do not merge.\n\nAC3. When a parse-fail or large-deletion gate trips, the bead is marked 'preserved-needs-review' and the operator is alerted via the bead's notes field, with a link to the iteration ref and a one-line summary of what gate fired.\n\nAC4. Post-merge typecheck/build is run as a final gate (project-level command from .ddx/config.yaml or sensible default like 'cargo check' / 'bun run build'). If post-merge build fails, AUTOMATICALLY revert the merge and preserve the result instead. This is the safety net for cases AC2 doesn't catch.\n\nAC5. Documentation in docs/ explains the safety gates, how to override them when intentional (e.g. for genuine large deletions), and what 'preserved-needs-review' means operationally.\n\nAC6. A regression test on the harness validates that an attempt to merge a result deleting \u003eN lines (or producing a parse failure) is correctly preserved+rejected, not merged.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","claimed-at":"2026-04-30T12:21:44Z","claimed-machine":"sindri","claimed-pid":"3881188","closing_commit_sha":"77715556bbfaf9ed63d5b9aa0d23da6ca724b02f","created_at":"2026-04-30T01:17:03.251053789Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-efe058be","depends_on_id":"ddx-fd31b628","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-30T08:02:53Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-efe058be","depends_on_id":"ddx-e2a51cd1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-30T08:02:53Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-efe058be","depends_on_id":"ddx-e19c5181","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-30T08:02:53Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-efe058be","depends_on_id":"ddx-b6c42808","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-30T08:02:54Z"}],"description":"Today on axon repo, the ddx-land-coordinator merged a bead-result branch onto master that deleted 1448 lines from one Svelte component (1552 → 104 lines). The same merge also corrupted a second test file (1043 → 158 lines, overwritten with unrelated content). Master became unbuildable: vite-plugin-svelte threw 'Expected token }' because the policies/+page.svelte file lost its \u003cscript lang=\"ts\"\u003e wrapper along with the entire HTML template and style sections.\n\nThe damaging merge:\n\n  commit be1073f4333c289e48680cf8c05ceefa7ea9c075\n  Merge: 0c5557b 2f35ad2\n  Author: ddx-land-coordinator \u003ccoordinator@ddx.local\u003e\n  Date:   Wed Apr 29 20:56:46 2026 -0400\n\n      Merge bead axon-80979cb8 attempt 20260430T005434- into master\n\n       .../databases/[database]/policies/+page.svelte     | 1448 --------------------\n       1 file changed, 1448 deletions(-)\n\nThe post-merge codex reviewer DID block subsequent attempts that built on the broken base ('the diff only adds execution metadata' / 'the new Playwright coverage is incorrect... the collection view never loads'), but the original 1448-line deletion went through unchecked. Five subsequent worker attempts ran on top of the now-broken master, each adding ~80 lines of partial reconstructions, none producing a valid Svelte file.\n\nNet damage on master before manual recovery:\n  ui/src/routes/.../policies/+page.svelte      1552 → 186 lines (1366 lines lost)\n  ui/tests/e2e/policy-enforcement.spec.ts      1043 → 158 lines (885 lines lost)\n  master state: vite-plugin-svelte fails to compile, UI bundle cannot build, docker e2e harness cannot start\n\nManual recovery (commit bc4b492 on axon master): git checkout HEAD~14 of both files, re-stage, commit, push. 2415 lines restored across 3 files.\n\nWhy this happened (hypothesis):\n  1. The bead-attempt branch had a partial reconstruction of the file (104 lines of just imports/state, no template).\n  2. The land-coordinator did a 3-way merge with master at base_rev. The base_rev was ALSO the partial reconstruction (because EARLIER attempts had already truncated it).\n  3. Three-way merge produced a 'clean' delete of the 1448 lines that existed only on master's side because base_rev was already broken.\n\nOr alternatively: the agent's tool calls deleted content from the worktree without re-emitting the full file (e.g. used Edit with overlapping replace blocks that effectively truncated), the harness committed whatever was on disk without sanity-checking magnitude, and the land-coordinator merged the partial content as authoritative.","id":"ddx-efe058be","issue_type":"bug","labels":["area:agent","area:execute-bead","area:land-coordinator","kind:safety","severity:critical"],"owner":"erik","priority":0,"schema_version":1,"status":"closed","title":"execute-bead: land-coordinator merged a result that deleted 1448 lines from a single file (catastrophic damage)","updated_at":"2026-04-30T12:22:05.677486788Z","work-heartbeat-at":"2026-04-30T12:21:44.162888426Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1763:{"acceptance":"1. cli/cmd/try.go exists implementing 'ddx try \u003cbead-id\u003e' as a cobra subcommand. Help text describes operator-targeted execution + the relationship to 'ddx work'.\n\n2. 'ddx try unknown-bead-id' exits non-zero with stderr 'bead not found: unknown-bead-id'.\n\n3. 'ddx try \u003cclosed-bead-id\u003e' exits non-zero with stderr 'bead is not claimable (status=closed)'. Same shape for cancelled.\n\n4. 'ddx try \u003cbead-id-with-unmet-deps\u003e' exits non-zero with stderr 'bead has unmet dependencies: \u003clist\u003e'.\n\n5. 'ddx try \u003cready-bead-id\u003e' claims the bead, executes via the existing execute-bead-loop machinery (one iteration, one bead), writes evidence to .ddx/executions/\u003crun-id\u003e/, and exits with the bead's terminal status code (0 = success/already_satisfied; 1 = preserved_for_review/no_changes; 2 = execution_failed).\n\n6. Flag plumbing: --harness, --model, --profile, --provider, --effort, --opaque-passthrough, --no-review, --review-harness, --review-model. Each flag, when set, plumbs identically to the corresponding 'ddx work' flag (same struct fields in the runtime config).\n\n7. WIRED-IN: the new 'ddx try' command is registered in cli/cmd/root.go (or wherever the cobra root command assembles subcommands). Verified by 'ddx try --help' output AND by 'git grep \"tryCmd\\|NewTryCommand\" cli/cmd/' showing the registration.\n\n8. Tests in cli/cmd/try_test.go:\n   - TestTry_BeadNotFound — invalid ID returns the documented stderr + non-zero exit\n   - TestTry_BeadClosed — closed bead returns the documented stderr + non-zero exit\n   - TestTry_BeadUnmetDeps — bead with unclosed dep returns the documented stderr + non-zero exit\n   - TestTry_HappyPath_ClaimsAndExecutes — fixture bead + stub executor; assert bead is claimed, attempted, and outcome reported (use the existing test fixtures from agent_execute_loop_test.go as a template)\n   - TestTry_FlagsPlumbThrough — set --harness=codex --model=gpt-5.4-mini and assert these reach the runtime config (capture via stub)\n\n9. Quality gates:\n   - cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./cmd/... ./internal/agent/...\n   - lefthook run pre-commit\n\n10. Conventional commit message ending [\u003cthis-bead-id\u003e]. Stage cli/cmd/try.go + cli/cmd/try_test.go + any cli/cmd/root.go registration line specifically; DO NOT use git add -A.\n\n11. Manual verification (operator runs after merge): 'ddx try ddx-50da9674' (closed fixture-repo bead) returns non-zero with the closed-bead message; 'ddx try \u003csome-ready-bead\u003e' actually claims and executes it.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","claimed-at":"2026-05-03T20:06:45Z","claimed-machine":"eitri","claimed-pid":"463338","closing_commit_sha":"ff5e64cecc17f3094f3933986966b94a50dc4f59","created_at":"2026-05-03T20:06:37.62309311Z","description":"PROBLEM\nOperators have no way to dispatch a SPECIFIC bead through the production execution machinery (claim → try.Attempt → land → review). Today's surfaces:\n- 'ddx work' drains by picker priority — can't force a specific bead\n- 'ddx work --once' drains the top of the queue once — still picker-controlled\n- 'ddx agent run --prompt' invokes the agent but doesn't claim, doesn't merge, doesn't write to bead event log\n\nThis blocks: (1) deterministic queue ordering during refactor execution, (2) the 3-path comparison study (ddx-31f745cd) which needs a way to target one fixture bead at a time, (3) operator-driven debugging when a bead misbehaves under autonomous drain.\n\nROOT CAUSE\n'ddx try' was originally bundled into refactor child C13 (ddx-387a0178) along with the file rename. C13 is sequenced AFTER C7 / C9 because the rename touches execute_bead_loop.go which those children also touch. But 'ddx try' itself is ADDITIVE — a new CLI subcommand that delegates to existing machinery — and doesn't conflict with the refactor children. Splitting 'ddx try' out lets it ship FIRST and unblocks operator-controlled execution for the entire rest of the refactor work.\n\nCode today (relevant entry points):\n- cli/cmd/work.go: 'ddx work' command implementation (calls into agent.ExecuteBeadLoopRuntime)\n- cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go: 'ddx agent work' (the underlying loop runner)\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go: ExecuteBeadWorker.Run + nextCandidate\n- cli/internal/bead/store.go:1246 ReadyExecution + Claim\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nAdd a new top-level command at cli/cmd/try.go:\n\n  ddx try \u003cbead-id\u003e [--harness=\u003cname\u003e] [--model=\u003cname\u003e] [--profile=\u003cname\u003e]\n\nBehavior:\n1. Look up the bead by ID via the bead store; fail-fast with a clear message if not found.\n2. Verify the bead is in a claimable state (status open OR stale-in_progress per existing semantics); fail-fast if status closed/cancelled OR if it has unmet dependencies.\n3. Force-target this single bead. Two implementation strategies (pick simpler):\n   STRATEGY A (thin wrapper): construct an ExecuteBeadLoopRuntime with --once + a custom nextCandidate that returns ONLY this bead-id, skipping the picker. Call ExecuteBeadWorker.Run.\n   STRATEGY B (direct invocation): claim the bead, build the runtime config, call try.Attempt directly (or whatever the underlying single-bead execution function is today). Skip the loop.\n   Recommend STRATEGY A — reuses the existing claim + executor + outcome paths; smaller diff; less risk of behavior divergence.\n4. Honor --harness / --model / --profile / --opaque-passthrough exactly the way 'ddx work' does (same flag plumbing).\n5. Exit with the bead's terminal status (success → 0; preserved/no_changes/blocked → non-zero with structured stderr).\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- File rename of execute_bead_loop.go (still owned by C13)\n- Refactor of execute-bead surface into try/work packages (refactor epic)\n- Multi-bead try (use 'ddx work' for that)\n- Server-side targeting (a future enhancement; v1 is local CLI only)\n- Auto-discovery of dependencies (operator must use 'ddx bead ready' first)\n\nINTERSECTION\n- C13 (ddx-387a0178) currently includes 'ADD ddx try CLI command' in its scope. After this bead lands, amend C13 to drop that line.\n- 3-path comparison study (ddx-31f745cd) Path A uses 'ddx try' as the production-path executor; this bead unblocks that study.\n- Refactor children Wave 2 dispatch will use 'ddx try' (codex harness) to deterministically dispatch each child in dep order.","events_attachment":"ddx-f261d2a0/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-f261d2a0","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2","area:cli","area:agent","kind:feature","reliability","bead-quality","wave:0"],"notes":"Shipped at commit 88dde5dc: ddx try \u003cbead-id\u003e subcommand. 7 tests added.","owner":"erik","parent":"ddx-e34994e2","priority":0,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-5aa83717","status":"closed","title":"cli: add 'ddx try \u003cbead-id\u003e' command — operator-targeted one-shot bead execution","updated_at":"2026-05-03T20:33:23.906719751Z","work-heartbeat-at":"2026-05-03T20:32:45.728149146Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1773:{"acceptance":"1. `TestFormatLoopResultLine_SuccessUsesSuccessMarker` proves success and already_satisfied statuses render with the success marker and unchanged concise result text.\n2. `TestFormatLoopResultLine_FailuresDoNotUseSuccessMarker` proves review malfunction, execution_failed, post_run_check_failed, no_evidence_produced, and preserved-error statuses do not render with `✓`.\n3. `TestExecuteBeadLoop_LogLineDoesNotUseSuccessMarkerForReviewError` covers a loop result with `Detail=\"pre-close review: review-error: transport\"` and asserts the emitted log line does not start with `✓`.\n4. Existing `formatLoopResult` behavior remains covered for `merged`, `already_satisfied`, `no_changes`, `preserved: ...`, and `error: ...` text.\n5. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... -run \"TestFormatLoopResult|TestExecuteBeadLoop_LogLine\" -count=1` passes.\n6. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-15T00:08:56Z","closing_commit_sha":"31559c7f739b2c6eb92cabeea1906e6550cea622","created_at":"2026-05-06T17:16:30.820398584Z","description":"PROBLEM\n`ddx work` prints a success-looking terminal line for failed iterations. Operators see output such as `✓ ddx-8fa7ecf6 → error: pre-close review: review-error: transport`, where the leading checkmark contradicts the error detail and makes it unclear whether the bead closed successfully.\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\n`cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:1214-1215` always prints `✓ \u003cbead\u003e → \u003cformatted-result\u003e` whenever an iteration finishes, regardless of `ExecuteBeadReport.Status`. `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:1590-1616` formats failed statuses as `error: ...`, but the caller still prefixes them with the success glyph.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- Add a small terminal result-line formatter near `formatLoopResult` that returns both a status marker and the existing concise result text.\n- Use a success marker only for `success` and `already_satisfied` results.\n- Use a neutral or failure marker for `no_changes`, review malfunction, execution_failed, post-run check failures, and other non-closing statuses so the first token no longer implies success.\n- Keep persisted `bead.result` events and status enums unchanged; this bead is CLI/log presentation only.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Renaming `pre-claim intake` / `pre-dispatch lint` readiness-hook terminology; that is owned by `ddx-1c0de0af`.\n- Review retry/manual-required policy; that is owned by `ddx-639af4ef` and related review beads.\n- Changing status taxonomy or persisted event schemas; classification work is owned by `ddx-e2479b81`.","events_attachment":"ddx-f326f001/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-f326f001","issue_type":"bug","labels":["area:agent","area:cli","kind:bug","operator-ux","phase:2","reliability","spec:FEAT-010"],"lifecycle-migrated-at":"2026-05-09T13:09:06Z","lifecycle-migrated-from-status":"closed","lifecycle-migrated-to-status":"closed","parent":"ddx-a9d130d0","priority":0,"schema_version":1,"spec-id":"FEAT-010","status":"closed","title":"work: render terminal result lines with status-specific markers","updated_at":"2026-05-08T15:18:10.968417102Z"}
