erride: one sentence (~70-\u003e~25w). Constraints tail bullets including '.ddx/executions/ intact' and 'never ddx init' as separate items (~60-\u003e~40w). Add load-bearing-guardrail comment block above each constant per FEAT-022 amendment (full guardrail list in /tmp/story-12-final.md Diagnosis section). Selector at execute_bead.go:1343: agent/fiz/embedded -\u003e Agent variant; claude/codex/opencode/unknown -\u003e Claude variant — must be preserved.","events_attachment":"ddx-f7b4bbc3/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-f7b4bbc3","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2","story:12","tier:cheap"],"owner":"erik","parent":"ddx-a61bf8ee","priority":0,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-e556e04e","status":"closed","title":"B2: Tighten execute-bead shared blocks; add guardrail-list comment + invariant/selector/missing-governing tests","updated_at":"2026-05-02T12:28:05.471955573Z","work-heartbeat-at":"2026-05-02T12:26:55.546746999Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1826:{"acceptance":"1. cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go consumes the no_changes lifecycle action from the try package instead of treating all unsatisfied no_changes outcomes as the same cooldown/no-progress case.\n2. TestExecuteBeadWorkerNoChangesVerifiedClosesImmediately remains green and asserts verified no_changes closes as already_satisfied.\n3. TestExecuteBeadWorkerNoChangesNeedsInvestigationKeepsBeadOpen asserts needs_investigation unclaims/labels the bead and does not set work-retry-after by default.\n4. TestExecuteBeadWorkerNoChangesUnjustifiedKeepsOpenWithoutLongCooldown asserts absent rationale records triage:no-changes-unjustified and avoids long retry cooldown unless a retryable action is explicitly returned.\n5. TestExecuteBeadWorkerSuccessClearsStaleNoChangesMetadata proves a later success/already_satisfied close removes stale work-retry-after and no_changes last-status fields while preserving events.\n6. Retryable transient paths such as rate-limit, transport, push_failed, push_conflict, and land_conflict still set cooldown where existing tests require it.\n7. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... -run 'TestExecuteBeadWorkerNoChangesVerifiedClosesImmediately|TestExecuteBeadWorkerNoChangesNeedsInvestigationKeepsBeadOpen|TestExecuteBeadWorkerNoChangesUnjustifiedKeepsOpenWithoutLongCooldown|TestExecuteBeadWorkerSuccessClearsStaleNoChangesMetadata|TestAttempt_RateLimit_Retry_HonorsRetryAfter' -count=1 passes.\n8. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","claimed-at":"2026-05-05T21:20:02Z","claimed-machine":"eitri","claimed-pid":"379238","closing_commit_sha":"321a158384af457b9daf3a4fbb4ca1ba47fd8642","created_at":"2026-05-05T20:43:32.954547685Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-fd1766e5","depends_on_id":"ddx-84d016dc","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-05T20:43:33Z"}],"description":"PROBLEM\nEven after no_changes adjudication knows the TD-031 lifecycle action, the live execute loop must apply that action with existing tracker mechanisms. Today no_changes paths can still write retry-after cooldowns for cases that should be closed, labeled for human triage, or removed from ordinary execution eligibility.\n\nROOT CAUSE\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:962-1070 applies attemptOut.NoChanges by appending events, closing satisfied attempts, and otherwise using no-progress/cooldown logic. The branch does not yet consume an explicit TD-031 action from the try package.\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:1024 and 1063 call SetExecutionCooldown from no_changes/no-progress paths, which is correct only for retryable/transient outcomes.\n- cli/internal/bead/store.go:744-752 SetExecutionCooldown persists work-retry-after plus last status/detail; callers must be narrowed so this field does not become a generic parking lot.\n- Existing events can show later success while Extra still says work-last-status=no_changes, so the live close path must avoid leaving stale no_changes management fields behind.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- Consume the lifecycle action added by dependency ddx-84d016dc in the execute loop.\n- For verified already-satisfied action, close the bead with evidence and append the existing already_satisfied/closed event path.\n- For needs-human / needs-investigation / unjustified no_changes action, unclaim and apply the existing label/event outputs without setting a long retry cooldown by default.\n- For retryable transient action, preserve current cooldown behavior and cap rules.\n- Clear or overwrite stale work-last-status / work-last-detail / work-retry-after when a later success or already_satisfied action closes the bead.\n- Keep append-only events intact; only management Extra fields may be cleared/updated.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Defining the lifecycle action type; ddx-84d016dc owns it.\n- Queue derivation and diagnostics; follow-up bead handles that.\n- Reconciliation of historical tracker rows; follow-up bead handles existing pile-up.\n- New persisted statuses.\n\nPARENT\n- ddx-a9d130d0.\n\nDEPS\n- ddx-84d016dc: live mutation code needs the try/no_changes lifecycle action shape.\n\nINTERSECTIONS\n- Closed ddx-b24e9630 distinguished verified no_changes from gave-up-without-progress; this bead enforces that distinction in live store mutations.\n- Closed ddx-5b3e57f4 and ddx-a458af7c narrowed cooldown behavior for disrupted/push-failed paths; preserve those rules while narrowing no_changes cooldowns.","id":"ddx-fd1766e5","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2","area:agent","area:beads","kind:fix","reliability","bead-lifecycle","spec:TD-031"],"owner":"codex","parent":"ddx-a9d130d0","priority":0,"schema_version":1,"spec-id":"TD-031","status":"closed","title":"agent: apply TD-031 no_changes actions in live work mutations","updated_at":"2026-05-05T21:26:36.152459735Z","work-heartbeat-at":"2026-05-05T21:20:02.433444006Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:1833:{"acceptance":"(1) Root cause documented in code comment next to SynthesizeCommit. (2) SynthesizeCommit completes with exit 0 when only change is in a gitignored directory. (3) Regression test: a project with non-empty .ddx/agent-logs and no real changes yields SynthesizeCommit → (false, nil) (no commit, no error). (4) Regression test: a project with one real modification + non-empty .ddx/agent-logs yields (true, nil) with only the real change committed. (5) ddx work --once drains ddx-672cf2bf or another ready bead end-to-end without hitting staging-changes exit 1.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","created_at":"2026-04-20T14:57:38.058551192Z","description":"Blocks `ddx work` whenever the gitignored runtime directories `.ddx/agent-logs/` and `.ddx/workers/` have any content. Every real-world project hits this after the first agent run.\n\n## Symptom\n\nEvery tier attempt in the work aborts:\n\n```\npre-execute-bead checkpoint: staging changes: exit status 1\n```\n\n## Root cause\n\ncli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:363 `RealGitOps.SynthesizeCommit` runs:\n\n```\ngit -C \u003cdir\u003e add -A -- . ':(exclude).ddx/agent-logs' ':(exclude).ddx/workers' ':(exclude).ddx/executions/*/embedded' ':(exclude).ddx/executions/*/no_changes_rationale.txt' ':(exclude).claude/skills' ':(exclude).agents/skills'\n```\n\nWhen `.ddx/agent-logs/` and `.ddx/workers/` exist as untracked directories (normal after the first agent run), and both are in .gitignore (lines 421-422), git add emits:\n\n```\nThe following paths are ignored by one of your .gitignore files:\n.ddx/agent-logs\n.ddx/workers\nhint: Use -f if you really want to add them.\n```\n\nAND exits with status 1. The `:(exclude)` magic pathspec is not sufficient to silence this exit-1 in git's add behavior with `-C` form — even `-c advice.addIgnoredFile=false` does not suppress it.\n\n## Fix candidates (not pre-decided)\n\n1. Check `git status --porcelain` first; only run `git add` if there are tracked changes to stage.\n2. Enumerate dirty files in Go (via `git status --porcelain`), filter out excluded paths, pass the survivors explicitly to `git add --`.\n3. Distinguish stderr \"benign ignored-files warning\" from real errors; accept exit 1 when that's the only message.\n4. Move `.ddx/agent-logs/` and `.ddx/workers/` out of the repo tree so they're outside the pathspec entirely.\n\nPrefer (1) or (2) — they're honest about the intent \"stage only real modifications.\" Option (3) is fragile against git message changes; (4) touches a lot of downstream tooling.\n\n## Evidence\n\nWorker: worker-20260420T145025-61dc. Bead ddx-672cf2bf. All three tier attempts (cheap/standard/smart) failed identically. Confirmed reproducible via manual run of the exact add command in `/Users/erik/Projects/ddx`.\n\n## Relationship to other beads\n\nIndependent of ddx-672cf2bf (silent-exit on epic queues) — this is loud-exit on staging. Independent of v0.7.0. Blocks the wave:1 smoke test in ddx-e7254128.","id":"ddx-feb1d4a5","issue_type":"bug","labels":["area:agent","area:exec","kind:bug","phase:build","wave:1","workstream:ddx-local"],"notes":"Fixed in commit edbf8a17. Dropped :(exclude) pathspecs for already-gitignored paths (.ddx/agent-logs, .ddx/workers). Regression test TestSynthesizeCommit_GitignoredDirsDoNotFail covers AC (3) and (4). AC (5) verified: worker-20260420T150211-60cc got past the pre-execute-bead checkpoint and dispatched the agent on ddx-004eccbc without the prior 'staging changes: exit status 1' error.","priority":1,"schema_version":1,"status":"closed","title":"exec: pre-execute-bead checkpoint fails when .ddx/agent-logs or .ddx/workers are untracked","updated_at":"2026-04-20T15:07:37.467363117Z"}
