.ddx/attachments/ddx-c9ef6c4f/events.jsonl:3:{"actor":"erik","body":"status: needs_investigation\nreason: |\n  Bead ddx-c9ef6c4f (\"Implement axon backend behind selectable backend flag\")\n  cannot be completed in a single execute-bead pass because two upstream\n  prerequisites are not yet in place, and the AC as written requires a\n  working end-to-end integration against an external Rust service. Forcing\n  a commit here would land non-functional scaffolding (the failure mode\n  the parent epic ddx-5d49b14e was already BLOCKED for).\n\n  Specific gaps observed in the current worktree (base ab0a056a):\n\n  1. Dependency bead ddx-bbdd7564 (\"Introduce selectable bead Backend\n     interface in cli/internal/bead\") is still status=open. The current\n     cli/internal/bead/backend.go defines only the legacy interface:\n\n         Backend interface {\n             Init() error\n             ReadAll() ([]Bead, error)\n             WriteAll(beads []Bead) error\n             WithLock(fn func() error) error\n         }\n\n     TD-030 (docs/helix/02-design/technical-designs/TD-030-axon-bead-backend.md\n     §\"Backend interface (Go)\") explicitly says this interface is \"too\n     coarse for Axon — WriteAll(beads []Bead) cannot reasonably be\n     implemented against a remote entity store\" and prescribes a richer\n     per-entity surface (Get/Create/Update with OCC Version,\n     AppendEvent, AddDep/RemoveDep, Ready, Close, Export/Import,\n     ErrVersionMismatch, etc.). Implementing the axon backend against\n     the legacy 4-method interface would (a) violate TD-030 and (b)\n     produce a backend that cannot honor claim/OCC semantics that the\n     bead description and AC #3 require (\"plus claim semantics and\n     event append\"). This bead's <description> says it \"follows the TD\n     authored in the design child\" — that TD assumes the interface\n     refactor has landed first.\n\n  2. No Axon Go SDK or generated gRPC client exists in this repo.\n     /home/erik/Projects/axon ships axon.proto at\n     crates/axon-server/proto/axon.proto (377 lines, AxonService with\n     CreateEntity/GetEntity/UpdateEntity/CommitTransaction/Traverse/\n     QueryEntities/PutSchema/CreateCollection/etc.) but no Go bindings.\n     TD-030 §\"Wire transport\" specifies generation via\n     protoc-gen-go + protoc-gen-go-grpc into cli/internal/bead/axon/pb/\n     with a `make gen-axon-client` target and a checked-in axon.proto\n     plus sha256. None of that scaffolding exists; protoc toolchain\n     setup, proto vendoring, and the make target are themselves a\n     non-trivial chunk of work that should be its own bead.\n\n  3. AC #5 (\"ddx bead commands work end-to-end against the axon\n     backend on a fresh repo, no migration required\") cannot be\n     verified inside this worktree. Per TD-030 §D1 the operator runs a\n     separate axon-server process; per §D4 the backend refuses all ops\n     when Axon is unreachable. There is no Axon server running in this\n     execution environment and no fixture / test-double that the AC\n     would accept (\"end-to-end ... on a fresh repo\" rules out an\n     in-memory fake).\n\n  Additional context: the parent epic ddx-5d49b14e was BLOCKED in\n  post-merge review on 2026-05-02 for landing only execution evidence\n  with no implementation, then decomposed into seven children. This\n  bead is one of those children but was queued out of dependency order\n  — ddx-bbdd7564 (the interface refactor child) needs to land first.\n\nwhat_is_done:\n  - Read TD-030 (the design child's output) end-to-end.\n  - Confirmed current Backend interface in cli/internal/bead/backend.go\n    is the legacy form, not the TD-030 form.\n  - Confirmed dependency bead ddx-bbdd7564 is still open.\n  - Confirmed no axon proto/client is vendored under cli/internal/bead/.\n\nwhat_is_blocking:\n  - ddx-bbdd7564 must land first to introduce the per-entity Backend\n    interface (Get/Create/Update with Version/OCC, AppendEvent,\n    AddDep/RemoveDep, Ready, Close, Export/Import, error sentinels)\n    that this bead's axon implementation needs to satisfy.\n  - A separate bead should establish the gRPC client generation\n    pipeline: vendor cli/internal/bead/axon/proto/axon.proto from the\n    axon repo (with sha256 pin), add the make gen-axon-client target,\n    add tooling docs for protoc-gen-go / protoc-gen-go-grpc, and\n    commit the generated cli/internal/bead/axon/pb/ tree. This is\n    explicitly called out by TD-030 §\"Wire transport\" but is not in\n    the current bead's scope and has no existing bead covering it.\n  - AC #5 needs a clarified verification path: either (a) require a\n    running Axon test server in CI (with the deployment work that\n    implies), or (b) loosen \"end-to-end\" to mean \"round-trip against\n    a vendored Axon test harness\" and add the harness as a bead.\n\nwhat_a_followup_would_need:\n  - Re-queue this bead (ddx-c9ef6c4f) only after ddx-bbdd7564 closes\n    with the TD-030-shaped Backend interface in place.\n  - Add (and close) a new prerequisite bead for the axon gRPC client\n    generation: vendor proto, wire `make gen-axon-client`, commit\n    generated stubs under cli/internal/bead/axon/pb/.\n  - Add a new prerequisite bead for the Axon test harness used by AC\n    #5 (either a test-only docker-compose entry, a `go test`-managed\n    server-under-test, or an explicit \"skip if AXON_ADDR unset\"\n    integration-test gate per the project's existing test-tier\n    conventions).\n  - Then this bead becomes a focused implementation: wrap the\n    generated client in cli/internal/bead/axon/, register the\n    \"axon\" backend in cli/internal/bead/registry.go, plumb the\n    DDX_BEAD_BACKEND / .ddx/config.yaml selector, and add the\n    create/claim/close/dep unit tests AC #4 names (against the\n    harness from the new prerequisite bead).\nrationale: status: needs_investigation\nreason: |\n  Bead ddx-c9ef6c4f (\"Implement axon backend behind selectable backend