ription: \"Depends on beads 16, 22, 28 (all legacy types\nretired).\" Repo grep shows three of the five types are still live:\n\n  cli/internal/agent/types.go:36   type RunOptions struct { ... }\n  cli/internal/agent/types.go:81   type QuorumOptions struct { ... }\n  cli/internal/agent/types.go:171  type CompareOptions struct { ... }\n\nCounts of constructions/parameters detected by the analyzer on the\ncurrent tree (sampled from `runtimelint ./...` output):\n\n  RunOptions composite literals (test files):\n    cli/internal/agent/agent_test.go (7),\n    cli/internal/agent/claude_stream_test.go (5),\n    cli/internal/agent/models_test.go (1),\n    cli/internal/agent/prompt_ingress_oversize_test.go (3),\n    cli/internal/agent/session_index_test.go (2),\n    cli/internal/agent/virtual_test.go (3).\n  Legacy-options function parameters (test files):\n    execute_bead_artifacts_test.go, execute_bead_e2e_test.go (×2),\n    execute_bead_env_isolation_test.go,\n    execute_bead_review_evidence_test.go,\n    execute_bead_review_test.go,\n    execute_bead_runtime_test.go.\n\nProduction code in cli/internal/agent/ (compare_adapter.go,\nquorum_adapter.go, the *_runner.go family) still composes the\nlegacy options types internally inside the new *Runtime adapters;\nthose sites are not flagged because the analyzer scopes pattern 2\nto composite literals of the legacy types, but they keep the type\ndeclarations live for the test sites above.\n\nRetiring RunOptions / CompareOptions / QuorumOptions is a substantial\nrefactor of cli/internal/agent/ — clearly outside this bead's stated\nin-scope (\"cli/tools/lint/runtimelint/\", \"lefthook.yml — add hook\",\n\"CI workflow — add job\"). Doing it under this bead would silently\nexpand scope and risk a poor merge.\n\nWhy no CI block entry was added either\n--------------------------------------\n\nA `runtimelint-all` entry in lefthook.yml's `ci:` block would mirror\n`evidence-lint-all` (lefthook.yml:425-430) and is the cleanest CI\nwiring (the GitHub Actions workflow already runs `lefthook run ci`,\nso no .github/workflows/ci.yml change is needed once the lefthook ci\nblock is populated). However, adding it now would put CI red against\nthe same 30+ legitimate diagnostics described above. AC4 explicitly\nrequires \"Running runtimelint against the post-cleanup tree exits 0\";\nthat is the gate that licenses turning on the CI block.\n\nWiring the CI block before the retirement beads land would also\nsilently break ddx-development unrelated to SD-024 (any PR rebased\non main would fail the new gate), violating the staged-rollout\nprinciple that the staged-file-scoped pre-commit hook already\nrespects.\n\nRecommended path forward\n------------------------\n\nThis bead's analyzer + pre-commit hook should stand as-is in main\n(they already do, via ec83a30b6fc81dddfc8415599dfcbff8a7f36978).\nWhat is needed is one or two new tracker beads:\n\n  1. Retire RunOptions: replace remaining test-site composite\n     literals with the *Runtime + ResolvedConfig pair; remove the\n     internal use inside the *Runtime adapters; delete the type\n     declaration. Acceptance: `go run ./tools/lint/runtimelint/\n     cmd/runtimelint ./...` produces no RunOptions diagnostics.\n\n  2. Retire CompareOptions and QuorumOptions: same pattern; delete\n     the `opts.RunOptions = RunOptions{...}` style internal\n     composition in cli/internal/agent/compare_adapter.go and\n     quorum_adapter.go; remove the type declarations.\n     Acceptance: `runtimelint ./...` exits 0.\n\n  3. Then a tiny follow-up bead enables the CI gate by adding a\n     `runtime-lint-all` entry under `ci:` in lefthook.yml mirroring\n     `evidence-lint-all`.\n\nReopening this bead a second time without doing that retirement\nwork first will not change the answer. The analyzer is built; the\nhook is wired; the missing piece is RunOptions/CompareOptions/\nQuorumOptions retirement, which is explicitly listed as a\ndependency on this bead and is not part of its in-scope.\n\nWhy no_changes is the right answer this pass\n--------------------------------------------\n\nThe previous attempt already produced and merged the analyzer +\npre-commit hook (commit 40ac58bb, merge ec83a30b). This worktree's\nbase-rev includes that work; there is nothing further to commit\nthat would advance the four AC items without expanding scope into\nthe dependency beads. Producing a redundant commit (e.g. moving\nthe hook around, tweaking comments) would only churn history. The\nhonest signal is no_changes with a clear pointer to what unblocks\nAC4.\nresult_rev=f809c33ca6ab8a2b165daaa7ca28426a6eaf6d39\nbase_rev=f809c33ca6ab8a2b165daaa7ca28426a6eaf6d39","created_at":"2026-04-26T17:45:15.623559136Z","kind":"execute-bead","source":"ddx agent work","summary":"already_satisfied"}
