.ddx/attachments/ddx-7aa810b8/events.jsonl:16:{"actor":"ddx","body":"Bead: ddx-7aa810b8 — Track execute-bead worktree lifecycle\n\nVerdict: no_changes. The bead is multi-surface and the AC set cannot be\ncompleted to the specified quality in a single pass without committing\npartial or red code across several surfaces. Per the bead instructions\n(\"a well-justified no_changes is better than a bad commit\"), this attempt\nreturns for breakdown/re-queue with a stronger budget or a pre-split bead set.\n\nWhat the AC demands (11 items, summarized):\n\n  1. GraphQL resolver executeBeadWorktrees(projectId) returning\n     {path, branch, beadId?, executionId?, baseRev, headRev, state,\n     createdAt, lastActivityAt} with unit tests for all four states.\n  2. Pure, table-driven state classifier\n     (active | completed | abandoned | orphan) with ≥2 edge cases per state.\n  3. New SvelteKit route /nodes/<n>/projects/<p>/worktrees — sortable,\n     filterable table.\n  4. Row actions (Remove, Force-remove) wired through GraphQL mutations\n     with confirm-gating and typed confirmation for force-remove.\n  5. CLI: `ddx server state worktree-prune [--dry-run] [--project] [--yes]`\n     with an integration test against a fixture repo containing one of\n     each state.\n  6. Server-side sweep with configurable interval (default 15m), a\n     GraphQL counter rollup type, and opt-in `worktrees.auto_prune` config.\n  7. Cross-links to /executions/<id> (depends on ddx-726bc5f2) and a\n     reciprocal \"Worktree\" section on the execution detail page.\n  8. Fixture seed with ≥100 worktrees across states; p95 ≤ 200ms.\n  9. Playwright e2e that seeds one of each state, asserts state badges,\n     exercises Remove confirm flow, and asserts active-worktree gating.\n 10. Design note in docs/helix/02-design/ for Part 4 canonical path\n     convention + migration plan (required only if Part 4 ships).\n 11. Cross-reference notes to ddx-12cae4dd, ddx-71fbe968, ddx-726bc5f2,\n     ddx-15f7ee0b.\n\nWhat is in place already (checked):\n\n  - Server package cli/internal/server/ with graphql resolver module,\n    state.go / state_executions.go, workers.go, and a land_coordinator\n    — the sweep / state-classification pattern has prior art here.\n  - Frontend SvelteKit tree includes /nodes/[nodeId]/projects/[projectId]\n    with executions, workers, beads, documents, etc. No worktrees route yet.\n  - Executions detail page already exists at .../executions/[executionId].\n    Cross-link target in AC 7 is therefore implementable, not blocked on\n    ddx-726bc5f2 (which may itself be partial or separate).\n  - Two worktree path conventions confirmed at runtime:\n      .claude/worktrees/agent-<hash>/   (branch-based, older)\n      /tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-<bead>-<ts>-<hash>/ (detached)\n    This execution itself is running from the /tmp convention.\n\nWhat is blocking a single-pass completion:\n\n  - The surface area spans Go (resolver + mutations + sweep + classifier +\n    CLI subcommand + config plumbing), SvelteKit (new route, table with\n    sort/filter, two confirm dialogs, mutation wiring, Houdini type\n    regeneration), fixtures (≥100-worktree seeder), unit tests, an\n    integration test, and a Playwright e2e. Each surface has its own\n    test-green bar; shipping them all together green within one pass\n    risks red commits on the surfaces that get squeezed last.\n  - AC 5 (CLI subcommand) requires a new `ddx server state` command\n    group; the current CLI surface exposes `ddx server` but does not\n    have a `state` subcommand tree — adding one is a small but\n    independent surface that interacts with the wider command layout.\n  - AC 6 (sweep + counter + config) needs config-schema changes\n    (.ddx/config.yaml worktrees block), which touches the config loader\n    and every test that loads config. This is a cross-cutting change\n    and deserves its own attempt slot.\n  - AC 8's ≥100-worktree fixture is cheap to generate but the p95\n    claim must be measured against a real handler — per the user's\n    standing perf stance (feedback_testing_and_performance), a perf\n    claim requires baseline + boundary + harness, not just a seed and\n    a one-shot timing.\n\nRecommended breakdown (for re-queue):\n\n  A. Inventory resolver + pure classifier + unit tests.\n     (AC 1, AC 2; pure, no UI, no config changes.)\n  B. Worktrees route + list view + cross-links to executions.\n     (AC 3, AC 7; depends on A; no mutations yet.)\n  C. Remove / Force-remove mutations + row actions + Playwright e2e.\n     (AC 4, AC 9; depends on B.)\n  D. CLI worktree-prune subcommand + integration test.\n     (AC 5; can run parallel to C once A is done.)\n  E. Sweep + counter + config + opt-in auto_prune.\n     (AC 6; depends on A; config-surface change.)\n  F. ≥100-worktree fixture + perf harness with p95 measurement.\n     (AC 8; depends on A; separate because of the perf methodology bar.)\n  G. Path-convention design note + Part 4 migration plan.\n     (AC 10, AC 11 for cross-refs; docs-only.)\n\nA follow-up attempt should take A alone, or A+B together, to stay\nwithin a single pass's green-bar budget.\n\nNo files were modified in this worktree.\nrationale: Bead: ddx-7aa810b8 — Track execute-bead worktree lifecycle\n\nVerdict: no_changes. The bead is multi-surface and the AC set cannot be\ncompleted to the specified quality in a single pass without committing\npartial or red code across several surfaces. Per the bead instructions\n(\"a well-justified no_changes is better than a bad commit\"), this attempt\nreturns for breakdown/re-queue with a stronger budget or a pre-split bead set.\n\nWhat the AC demands (11 items, summarized):\n\n  1. GraphQL resolver executeBeadWorktrees(projectId) returning\n     {path, branch, beadId?, executionId?, baseRev, headRev, state,\n     createdAt, lastActivityAt} with unit tests for all four states.\n  2. Pure, table-driven state classifier\n     (active | completed | abandoned | orphan) with ≥2 edge cases per state.\n  3. New SvelteKit route /nodes/<n>/projects/<p>/worktrees — sortable,\n     filterable table.\n  4. Row actions (Remove, Force-remove) wired through GraphQL mutations\n     with confirm-gating and typed confirmation for force-remove.\n  5. CLI: `ddx server state worktree-prune [--dry-run] [--project] [--yes]`\n     with an integration test against a fixture repo containing one of\n     each state.\n  6. Server-side sweep with configurable interval (default 15m), a\n     GraphQL counter rollup type, and opt-in `worktrees.auto_prune` config.\n  7. Cross-links to /executions/<id> (depends on ddx-726bc5f2) and a\n     reciprocal \"Worktree\" section on the execution detail page.\n  8. Fixture seed with ≥100 worktrees across states; p95 ≤ 200ms.\n  9. Playwright e2e that seeds one of each state, asserts state badges,\n     exercises Remove confirm flow, and asserts active-worktree gating.\n 10. Design note in docs/helix/02-design/ for Part 4 canonical path\n     convention + migration plan (required only if Part 4 ships).\n 11. Cross-reference notes to ddx-12cae4dd, ddx-71fbe968, ddx-726bc5f2,\n     ddx-15f7ee0b.\n\nWhat is in place already (checked):\n\n  - Server package cli/internal/server/ with graphql resolver module,\n    state.go / state_executions.go, workers.go, and a land_coordinator\n    — the sweep / state-classification pattern has prior art here.\n  - Frontend SvelteKit tree includes /nodes/[nodeId]/projects/[projectId]\n    with executions, workers, beads, documents, etc. No worktrees route yet.\n  - Executions detail page already exists at .../executions/[executionId].\n    Cross-link target in AC 7 is therefore implementable, not blocked on\n    ddx-726bc5f2 (which may itself be partial or separate).\n  - Two worktree path conventions confirmed at runtime:\n      .claude/worktrees/agent-<hash>/   (branch-based, older)\n      /tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-<bead>-<ts>-<hash>/ (detached)\n    This execution itself is running from the /tmp convention.\n\nWhat is blocking a single-pass completion:\n\n  - The surface area spans Go (resolver + mutations + sweep + classifier +\n    CLI subcommand + config plumbing), SvelteKit (new route, table with\n    sort/filter, two confirm dialogs, mutation wiring, Houdini type\n    regeneration), fixtures (≥100-worktree seeder), unit tests, an\n    integration test, and a Playwright e2e. Each surface has its own\n    test-green bar; shipping them all together green within one pass\n    risks red commits on the surfaces that get squeezed last.\n  - AC 5 (CLI subcommand) requires a new `ddx server state` command\n    group; the current CLI surface exposes `ddx server` but does not\n    have a `state` subcommand tree — adding one is a small but\n    independent surface that interacts with the wider command layout.\n  - AC 6 (sweep + counter + config) needs config-schema changes\n    (.ddx/config.yaml worktrees block), which touches the config loader\n    and every test that loads config. This is a cross-cutting change\n    and deserves its own attempt slot.\n  - AC 8's ≥100-worktree fixture is cheap to generate but the p95\n    claim must be measured against a real handler — per the user's\n    standing perf stance (feedback_testing_and_performance), a perf\n    claim requires baseline + boundary + harness, not just a seed and\n    a one-shot timing.\n\nRecommended breakdown (for re-queue):\n\n  A. Inventory resolver + pure classifier + unit tests.\n     (AC 1, AC 2; pure, no UI, no config changes.)\n  B. Worktrees route + list view + cross-links to executions.\n     (AC 3, AC 7; depends on A; no mutations yet.)\n  C. Remove / Force-remove mutations + row actions + Playwright e2e.\n     (AC 4, AC 9; depends on B.)\n  D. CLI worktree-prune subcommand + integration test.\n     (AC 5; can run parallel to C once A is done.)\n  E. Sweep + counter + config + opt-in auto_prune.\n     (AC 6; depends on A; config-surface change.)\n  F. ≥100-worktree fixture + perf harness with p95 measurement.\n     (AC 8; depends on A; separate because of the perf methodology bar.)\n  G. Path-convention design note + Part 4 migration plan.\n     (AC 10, AC 11 for cross-refs; docs-only.)\n\nA follow-up attempt should take A alone, or A+B together, to stay\nwithin a single pass's green-bar budget.\n\nNo files were modified in this worktree.\nresult_rev=6449424a64780692a3295a7a061db87d52f17eb8\nbase_rev=6449424a64780692a3295a7a061db87d52f17eb8","created_at":"2026-04-24T03:17:31.160062255Z","kind":"execute-bead","source":"ddx agent work","summary":"already_satisfied"}
