.ddx/attachments/ddx-ea3a7e23/events.jsonl:3:{"actor":"ddx","body":"Bead: ddx-ea3a7e23 — V6 generate principle composite (pressure-test gate)\n\nDecision: no_changes. The plan (docs/helix/02-design/plan-2026-04-29-visual-suite.md\n§\"Bead breakdown\" V6) explicitly forbids a manual prompt-file → image fallback:\n\"No manual prompt-file → image fallback; if those slip, V6 slips.\" A well-justified\nno_changes is preferable to authoring a prompt and shelling out to an image tool\noutside the FEAT-010 substrate.\n\nWhat is done\n- Verified the named blocker beads are closed: ddx-d5e71fb3 (FEAT-010 three-layer\n  substrate), ddx-5d92b873 (FEAT-007 sidecar + generated_by), ddx-64fbb1b3\n  (`ddx artifact regenerate` CLI).\n- Verified `ddx artifact regenerate` exists and dispatches into the FEAT-010\n  store via cli/cmd/artifact.go: it requires (a) the artifact present in the\n  document graph and (b) at least one execution definition that lists the\n  artifact under produces_artifact.\n- Read the six existing principle prompts under docs/helix/00-discover/visuals/\n  (principle-1-lever … principle-6-fulcrum) — V5 author-prompts work is in\n  place and can be referenced by the composite prompt.\n\nWhat is blocking\n1. Missing image-generation skill. The `nano-banana-pro-openrouter` skill is\n   referenced from `.crush/skills/` and `.pi/skills/` as symlinks pointing to\n   `.agents/skills/nano-banana-pro-openrouter/`, but that target directory does\n   not exist in this worktree (only helix-* skills and `ddx` are under\n   `.agents/skills/`). Without the skill the generator cannot run.\n2. No execution definition registered. `ddx exec list --json` returns `[]`;\n   there is no nano-banana-pro-openrouter generator definition, and no\n   definition lists `principles-composite` (or any visual artifact id) under\n   produces_artifact. `ddx artifact regenerate principles-composite` therefore\n   fails with \"artifact \\\"principles-composite\\\" not found in document graph\"\n   — the artifact is not registered, and even if it were, selectArtifactGenerator\n   in cli/cmd/artifact.go:99 would error with \"no generator definition or\n   generated_by provenance\".\n3. Sidecar metadata not authored. The plan calls for\n   `principles-composite.{prompt.md,png,png.ddx.yaml}` co-located with the V5\n   prompts, with `depends_on` and `generated_by` edges. The `.ddx.yaml` sidecar\n   for the (yet-unrendered) composite cannot be written without a real\n   `generated_by` run record, which only the substrate run produces.\n\nWhat a follow-up attempt would need (in order)\n1. A predecessor bead that installs / vendors the `nano-banana-pro-openrouter`\n   skill into `.agents/skills/` so the broken symlinks resolve. Today this\n   skill is missing from the execute-bead worktree.\n2. A predecessor bead that authors a `ddx exec define` execution definition\n   for the nano-banana-pro-openrouter generator with\n   `produces_artifact: principles-composite` (and, ideally, the six standalone\n   principle artifact IDs as well so V7 can reuse it).\n3. A predecessor bead that registers the `principles-composite` artifact in\n   the document graph (sidecar with id, depends_on .stitch/DESIGN.md and the\n   six principle prompts, media_type image/png) so `ddx artifact regenerate`\n   resolves it.\n\nOnce those three preconditions hold, V6 collapses to: author\ndocs/helix/00-discover/visuals/principles-composite.prompt.md (referencing the\nsix existing principle prompts and DESIGN.md tokens), then run\n`ddx artifact regenerate principles-composite`. The composite prompt should\nexplicitly assemble the lever metaphor — beam (P1), cyclic motion (P2),\ninterchangeable handles (P3), non-uniform load (P4), receipts trail (P5),\nfulcrum at the human-AI seam (P6) — so the pressure-test reads on the first\nrender. Budget tracking ($10 cap, $1.50/image halt) starts when the substrate\nrun actually executes.\n\nRecommendation: file three predecessor beads above (skill-install, exec-define,\nartifact-register), block ddx-ea3a7e23 on them, and re-queue. Do not escalate\nto a stronger model — model capability is not the constraint here.\nrationale: Bead: ddx-ea3a7e23 — V6 generate principle composite (pressure-test gate)\n\nDecision: no_changes. The plan (docs/helix/02-design/plan-2026-04-29-visual-suite.md\n§\"Bead breakdown\" V6) explicitly forbids a manual prompt-file → image fallback:\n\"No manual prompt-file → image fallback; if those slip, V6 slips.\" A well-justified\nno_changes is preferable to authoring a prompt and shelling out to an image tool\noutside the FEAT-010 substrate.\n\nWhat is done\n- Verified the named blocker beads are closed: ddx-d5e71fb3 (FEAT-010 three-layer\n  substrate), ddx-5d92b873 (FEAT-007 sidecar + generated_by), ddx-64fbb1b3\n  (`ddx artifact regenerate` CLI).\n- Verified `ddx artifact regenerate` exists and dispatches into the FEAT-010\n  store via cli/cmd/artifact.go: it requires (a) the artifact present in the\n  document graph and (b) at least one execution definition that lists the\n  artifact under produces_artifact.\n- Read the six existing principle prompts under docs/helix/00-discover/visuals/\n  (principle-1-lever … principle-6-fulcrum) — V5 author-prompts work is in\n  place and can be referenced by the composite prompt.\n\nWhat is blocking\n1. Missing image-generation skill. The `nano-banana-pro-openrouter` skill is\n   referenced from `.crush/skills/` and `.pi/skills/` as symlinks pointing to\n   `.agents/skills/nano-banana-pro-openrouter/`, but that target directory does\n   not exist in this worktree (only helix-* skills and `ddx` are under\n   `.agents/skills/`). Without the skill the generator cannot run.\n2. No execution definition registered. `ddx exec list --json` returns `[]`;\n   there is no nano-banana-pro-openrouter generator definition, and no\n   definition lists `principles-composite` (or any visual artifact id) under\n   produces_artifact. `ddx artifact regenerate principles-com