' AC3 covers land/reconcile audit; child 'Mark decomposed parent beads execution-ineligible before retry' AC3 covers decomposed-parent audit; child 'Classify repeated pre-claim system warnings as operator-visible worker state' AC3 covers pre-claim audit.\"},{\"parent_ac\":\"8. Existing related behavior from `ddx-2965925e`, `ddx-b2846610`, and `ddx-d67f124e` remains covered; this bead either reuses their helpers or waits for those dependencies, and does not add duplicate low-level implementations.\",\"coverage\":\"Child 'Classify land coordination failures without implementation reruns' AC4 preserves `ddx-2965925e` and `ddx-b2846610`; child 'Classify repeated pre-claim system warnings as operator-visible worker state' AC4 preserves `ddx-d67f124e`; every child description preserves all three dependency IDs and the parent non-scope constraints.\"},{\"parent_ac\":\"9. `cd cli \\u0026\\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -run 'NiflheimEvidence|EmptyReviewResult|NilReviewer|LandCoordination|DecomposedParent|RetryEscalation|CycleTraceCarriesDecisionAudit' -count=1` passes.\",\"coverage\":\"Covered as child-specific focused gates: review child AC4, land child AC5, decomposed-parent child AC5, pre-claim/escalation child AC5.\"},{\"parent_ac\":\"10. `cd cli \\u0026\\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -count=1` passes.\",\"coverage\":\"Review child AC5, land child AC6, decomposed-parent child AC6, pre-claim/escalation child AC6.\"},{\"parent_ac\":\"11. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.\",\"coverage\":\"Review child AC6, land child AC7, decomposed-parent child AC7, pre-claim/escalation child AC7.\"}],\"child_ids\":[\"ddx-cdd1a0b2\",\"ddx-bced4e39\",\"ddx-d2725150\",\"ddx-eea2dfca\"],\"rationale\":\"The parent bead mixes four independently testable failure families: review evidence gating, land coordination classification, decomposed-parent execution eligibility, and repeated pre-claim system warnings/retry escalation. Splitting on those boundaries keeps each 