.ddx/attachments/ddx-bffb23ae/events.jsonl:9:{"actor":"erik","body":"Bead ddx-bffb23ae (Story 12 B3) — no_changes rationale\n========================================================\n\nStatus: AC7 already satisfied on main; no further code change needed in\nthis attempt.\n\nWhat is done\n------------\nA prior attempt landed commit efbed403 (\"feat(agent): add prompt_sha to\nmanifest + prompt-size CI fixture [ddx-bffb23ae]\") which is an ancestor\nof HEAD/main in this worktree. Verified with `git merge-base HEAD\nefbed403` → efbed403. That commit delivers every AC7 deliverable:\n\n1. prompt_sha in manifest.json for every attempt\n   - Field defined: cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:177-181\n     (`PromptSHA string \\`json:\"prompt_sha,omitempty\"\\``)\n   - Populated on write: cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:1127\n     (`PromptSHA: promptSHA(promptContent)`)\n   - Helper: cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:1467-1470\n     (`promptSHA` returns hex sha256 of the rendered prompt bytes)\n   - Regression test: cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_artifacts_test.go\n     :230-298 asserts manifest.prompt_sha is a 64-char hex digest and\n     equals sha256 of the prompt.md bytes on disk.\n\n2. Render-size CI fixture emitting word/byte counts per (variant,\n   contextBudget)\n   - Test: cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_promptsize_test.go\n     (`TestPromptSizeReport`) renders both variants\n     (claude harness, agent harness) at contextBudget = \"\" (full) and\n     \"minimal\", logs the table to test output, writes a tab-separated\n     human report and a JSON sibling, and asserts minimal < full bytes\n     per variant to catch cheap-tier regressions.\n   - Determinism guard: `TestPromptSHA_DeterministicAcrossRenders`\n     asserts the helper is stable across renders and differs across\n     variants.\n\n3. CI surfaces the report as an artifact\n   - .github/workflows/ci.yml:201-214 runs the fixture with\n     `DDX_PROMPT_SIZE_REPORT=${{ github.workspace }}/prompt-size-report\n     .txt` and uploads `prompt-size-report.{txt,json,log}` as the\n     `prompt-size-report` artifact.\n\nVerification run in this worktree\n---------------------------------\n`cd cli && go test ./internal/agent -run\n'TestPromptSizeReport|TestPromptSHA|ExecuteBeadArtifacts' -count=1` →\nok (0.012s).\n\nWhy the bead was re-queued\n--------------------------\nThe notes section on this bead reads \"REVIEW:BLOCK — Diff contains only\nthis attempt's own execution evidence ... The shown manifest.json itself\nlacks a prompt_sha field, contradicting AC7.\" That review fired against\na *different* attempt whose diff happened to contain only the evidence\nfiles (manifest.json/result.json) for that attempt's own execution\nbundle. The actual implementation landed on a separate commit\n(efbed403) which is now on main. The recorded manifest.json the\nreviewer inspected was generated by an *earlier* execution that ran\nbefore efbed403 was merged, so it predates the field — the manifest.json\nemitted by the current binary does include prompt_sha.\n\nWhat a follow-up attempt would need\n-----------------------------------\nNothing for AC7. If the reviewer still doubts the field is being\nwritten, point them at the fresh manifest.json in this attempt's\nevidence directory (.ddx/executions/20260502T121152-24b051ff/\nmanifest.json) and the unit test\nTestExecuteBeadArtifacts_ManifestPromptSHA in execute_bead_artifacts_\ntest.go which asserts prompt_sha is present and matches sha256 of\nprompt.md.\nrationale: Bead ddx-bffb23ae (Story 12 B3) — no_changes rationale\n========================================================\n\nStatus: AC7 already satisfied on main; no further code change needed in\nthis attempt.\n\nWhat is done\n------------\nA prior attempt landed commit efbed403 (\"feat(agent): add prompt_sha to\nmanifest + prompt-size CI fixture [ddx-bffb23ae]\") which is an ancestor\nof HEAD/main in this worktree. Verified with `git merge-base HEAD\nefbed403` → efbed403. That commit delivers every AC7 deliverable:\n\n1. prompt_sha in manifest.json for every attempt\n   - Field defined: cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:177-181\n     (`PromptSHA string \\`json:\"prompt_sha,omitempty\"\\``)\n   - Populated on write: cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:1127\n     (`PromptSHA: promptSHA(promptContent)`)\n   - Helper: cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:1467-1470\n     (`promptSHA` returns hex sha256 of the rendered prompt bytes)\n   - Regression test: cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_artifacts_test.go\n     :230-298 asserts manifest.prompt_sha is a 64-char hex digest and\n     equals sha256 of the prompt.md bytes on disk.\n\n2. Render-size CI fixture emitting word/byte counts per (variant,\n   contextBudget)\n   - Test: cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_promptsize_test.go\n     (`TestPromptSizeReport`) renders both variants\n     (claude harness, agent harness) at contextBudget = \"\" (full) and\n     \"minimal\", logs the table to test output, writes a tab-separated\n     human report and a JSON sibling, and asserts minimal < full bytes\n     per variant to catch cheap-tier regressions.\n   - Determinism guard: `TestPromptSHA_DeterministicAcrossRenders`\n     asserts the helper is stable across renders and differs across\n     variants.\n\n3. CI surfaces the report as an artifact\n   - .github/workflows/ci.yml:201-214 runs the fixture with\n     `DDX_PROMPT_SIZE_REPORT=${{ github.workspace }}/prompt-size-report\n     .txt` and uploads `prompt-size-report.{txt,json,log}` as the\n     `prompt-size-report` artifact.\n\nVerification run in this worktree\n---------------------------------\n`cd cli && go test ./internal/agent -run\n'TestPromptSizeReport|TestPromptSHA|ExecuteBeadArtifacts' -count=1` →\nok (0.012s).\n\nWhy the bead was re-queued\n--------------------------\nThe notes section on this bead reads \"REVIEW:BLOCK — Diff contains only\nthis attempt's own execution evidence ... The shown manifest.json itself\nlacks a prompt_sha field, contradicting AC7.\" That review fired against\na *different* attempt whose diff happened to contain only the evidence\nfiles (manifest.json/result.json) for that attempt's own execution\nbundle. The actual implementation landed on a separate commit\n(efbed403) which is now on main. The recorded manifest.json the\nreviewer inspected was generated by an *earlier* execution that ran\nbefore efbed403 was merged, so it predates the field — the manifest.json\nemitted by the current binary does include prompt_sha.\n\nWhat a follow-up attempt would need\n-----------------------------------\nNothing for AC7. If the reviewer still doubts the field is being\nwritten, point them at the fresh manifest.json in this attempt's\nevidence directory (.ddx/executions/20260502T121152-24b051ff/\nmanifest.json) and the unit test\nTestExecuteBeadArtifacts_ManifestPromptSHA in execute_bead_artifacts_\ntest.go which asserts prompt_sha is present and matches sha256 of\nprompt.md.\nresult_rev=59065ae5723e0c45cc6c431be9ecbc75dbfdd4ad\nbase_rev=59065ae5723e0c45cc6c431be9ecbc75dbfdd4ad","created_at":"2026-05-02T12:13:20.881468118Z","kind":"execute-bead","source":"ddx agent work","summary":"already_satisfied"}
.ddx/attachments/ddx-baa1dbf2/events.jsonl:3:{"actor":"erik","body":"Bead ddx-baa1dbf2 — Story 6 B2 — no changes required.\n\nThe bead's full scope was already implemented and merged before this attempt, by\nprior bead ddx-5af9ae07 in commit d0a5dec0 (\"feat(web): artifacts sort dropdown\n+ staleness chips, cursor reset on param change\"). The base commit for this\nattempt (bb783e63) is downstream of that merge, so the worktree already\nsatisfies every acceptance criterion:\n\nAC mapping (file paths relative to repo root):\n\n1. \"Sort dropdown reorders list; URL persists sort=.\"\n   - cli/internal/server/frontend/src/routes/nodes/[nodeId]/projects/[projectId]/artifacts/+page.svelte\n     lines 261–274 (sort <select> bound to data.sort, onchange → selectSort →\n     navigateWith({ sort })).\n   - cli/internal/server/frontend/src/routes/nodes/[nodeId]/projects/[projectId]/artifacts/+page.ts\n     lines 59–74 (SORT_OPTIONS, ArtifactSort, parseSort, DEFAULT_SORT) and the\n     load() function passes sort to the GraphQL request.\n   - cli/internal/server/frontend/src/lib/urlState.ts lines 7, 36, 61–64\n     (sort key parse/serialize; cleared when null/empty).\n\n2. \"Staleness chip filters; URL persists staleness=.\"\n   - +page.svelte lines 220–245 (staleness chips with data-testid hooks,\n     selectStaleness toggle, clear button).\n   - +page.ts lines 76–82 (STALENESS_OPTIONS / parseStaleness).\n   - urlState.ts lines 7, 37, 65–68 (staleness key parse/serialize).\n\n3. \"q/mediaType/staleness/sort compose; pasting a URL with all four reproduces\n   the same view.\"\n   - load() in +page.ts (lines 84–111) is the single source of truth: it reads\n     all four params from the URL via readState and forwards them as GraphQL\n     variables, so a deep link reproduces the same query.\n   - navigateWith() in +page.svelte (lines 67–78) merges patches into the\n     current URLSearchParams and triggers goto(), so combinations compose.\n\n4. \"Clearing all filters returns URL