sonaLifecycle hits all three mutations + fork,\n    asserts `persona_is_library_read_only` on library targets, and\n    asserts CLI-created personas show up via the personas query.\n\nAC#4 — CLI parity:\n  Subcommands implemented in cli/cmd/persona.go\n    `ddx persona new <name> [--body]`    → writer.Create\n    `ddx persona edit <name> [--body]`   → writer.Update (+ $EDITOR path)\n    `ddx persona fork <lib> [--as]`      → writer.Fork\n    `ddx persona delete <name>`          → writer.Delete\n  Registered in cli/cmd/command_factory_commands.go alongside the\n  existing subcommands.\n  Tests: cli/cmd/persona_lifecycle_test.go\n    TestPersonaCLI_Lifecycle (all 4 subcommands happy/sad paths)\n    TestPersonaCLI_GraphQLParity (CLI-created persona visible to the\n      shared loader used by the GraphQL resolver)\n    TestPersonaCLI_LoadUsesProjectOverride (precedence applied in the\n      `persona load` injection path too)\n\nAC#5 — UI explainer copy:\n  cli/internal/server/frontend/src/routes/nodes/[nodeId]/projects/\n    [projectId]/personas/PersonasView.svelte\n  `data-testid=\"personas-explainer\"` carries two sentences:\n    - \"Personas are AI personality templates...\"\n    - \"Library personas are shared across projects and are read-only;\n       project personas live with this project...\"\n  Playwright: personas.e2e.ts -> \"personas page shows explainer...\"\n\nAC#6 — Source badge:\n  Each persona row renders `data-testid=\"persona-source-<name>\"` with\n  `library` or `project` text. Library badges use zinc; project badges\n  use teal so they read as the \"active/editable\" source.\n  Playwright: personas.e2e.ts same test asserts both values.\n\nAC#7 — New / Edit / Delete for project personas:\n  - Header `New persona` button opens the editor dialog.\n  - Project rows expose `persona-edit-<name>` and\n    `persona-delete-<name>` buttons; library rows expose neither.\n  - Editor dialog persists via personaCreate/personaUpdate.\n  - Delete dialog confirms and