.ddx/attachments/ddx-a9edd569/events.jsonl:9:{"actor":"erik","body":"Bead ddx-a9edd569 is already fully implemented at HEAD by commit 47b48d38\n(\"feat(web): label-aware collision and bounded convergence in doc-graph\n[ddx-a9edd569]\"), merged as 816752ef-predecessor b3da4924. No source changes\nare required in this attempt.\n\nThe prior review BLOCK note (\"Diff contains only an execution result.json\nreceipt; no changes to D3Graph.svelte or any source files\") was incorrect —\nthe reviewer appears to have inspected only an attempt's evidence directory\nrather than the merged commit. `git show 47b48d38 --stat` confirms 151 lines\nadded to cli/internal/server/frontend/src/lib/components/D3Graph.svelte and\n131 lines added to cli/internal/server/frontend/e2e/graph.spec.ts.\n\nAcceptance criteria, with evidence at HEAD:\n\nAC1 — Custom label-aware collision force lands in D3Graph.svelte.\n    cli/internal/server/frontend/src/lib/components/D3Graph.svelte:80-169\n    `labelAwareCollide<N>(padding)` builds per-node axis-aligned bounding\n    boxes covering the r=18 circle plus the trailing label (rendered at\n    x=24, truncated at 32 chars + ellipsis) and resolves overlaps in a\n    two-pass quadtree sweep with position correction. Wired in at line 284\n    via .force('collide', labelAwareCollide<SimNode>(8)), replacing the\n    earlier forceCollide(48) circle-only force.\n\nAC2 — No two node circles overlap after settle on the 128-node fixture\n    (Playwright bounding-box check).\n    cli/internal/server/frontend/e2e/graph.spec.ts:612-697 TC-043. Builds a\n    128-node ternary-tree fixture with hub cross-links, waits for the\n    bounded-convergence freeze (data-settleMs), enumerates every circle's\n    consolidated transform, and asserts dist(i,j) >= r_i + r_j - 0.5 for\n    all pairs.\n\nAC3 — Label bounding boxes do not overlap other nodes' circles after\n    settle.\n    cli/internal/server/frontend/e2e/graph.spec.ts:699-718 TC-043. For each\n    node's text bbox, computes the closest point to every foreign circle\n    centre and asserts the squared distance is >= (r - 0.5)^2.\n\nAC4 — Settle completes within 2 s (reported, not gated, per codex).\n    cli/internal/server/frontend/src/lib/components/D3Graph.svelte:391-400\n    captures performance.now() at simulation start, and on the `end` event\n    pins all nodes (fx/fy = x/y) and writes Math.round(elapsedMs) to\n    svgNode.dataset.settleMs. The Playwright test reports the value via\n    console.log at e2e/graph.spec.ts:722 and does not gate on it. Tuning\n    that drives ~2 s settle: alphaDecay(0.05), velocityDecay(0.5),\n    degree-tuned forceManyBody (-450 - 90·min(deg,10)) and forceLink\n    distance (140 + 18·min(degSrc+degTgt,10)).\n\nDrag-end semantics (from the description, not numbered AC) match codex's\nrecommendation:\n    cli/internal/server/frontend/src/lib/components/D3Graph.svelte:338-342\n    on('end') sets d.fx = null; d.fy = null (release, not re-pin).\n\nNo commit is produced because the bead contract is already satisfied at\nHEAD; producing an empty or cosmetic commit would only add noise to the\nmerge history.\nrationale: Bead ddx-a9edd569 is already fully implemented at HEAD by commit 47b48d38\n(\"feat(web): label-aware collision and bounded convergence in doc-graph\n[ddx-a9edd569]\"), merged as 816752ef-predecessor b3da4924. No source changes\nare required in this attempt.\n\nThe prior review BLOCK note (\"Diff contains only an execution result.json\nreceipt; no changes to D3Graph.svelte or any source files\") was incorrect —\nthe reviewer appears to have inspected only an attempt's evidence directory\nrather than the merged commit. `git show 47b48d38 --stat` confirms 151 lines\nadded to cli/internal/server/frontend/src/lib/components/D3Graph.svelte and\n131 lines added to cli/internal/server/frontend/e2e/graph.spec.ts.\n\nAcceptance criteria, with evidence at HEAD:\n\nAC1 — Custom label-aware collision force lands in D3Graph.svelte.\n    cli/inter