.ddx/attachments/ddx-a8eaef0a/events.jsonl:13:{"actor":"ddx","body":"## What is done\n\nThe bead's implementation work is already merged on the base branch. Commit\n`63e86ba1 refactor(agent): retire ExecuteBeadOptions and legacy ExecuteBead\n[ddx-a8eaef0a]` removed both:\n\n  - `type ExecuteBeadOptions` struct\n  - the legacy `ExecuteBead` (non-`WithConfig`) method\n\nVerification of AC item 1:\n\n    $ rg 'type ExecuteBeadOptions ' cli/\n    (no matches)\n\nThe remaining `ExecuteBeadOptions` mentions in the tree are only in source\ncomments (cli/cmd/agent_execute_bead_e2e_test.go, .../execute_bead_e2e_routing_test.go,\ncli/internal/config/types.go, cli/internal/config/testconfig.go) referencing\nthe SD-024 migration history — the type itself is gone.\n\n## What is blocking\n\nAC items 2 and 3 (`go build ./...` / `go test ./...`) cannot be demonstrated\ngreen in this pass for a reason unrelated to this bead's scope:\n\n    cli/cmd/agent_route_status.go:326:28: cand.RecentSuccessRate undefined\n        (type \"github.com/DocumentDrivenDX/agent\".RouteCandidateStatus has\n         no field or method RecentSuccessRate)\n    cli/cmd/agent_route_status.go:421:12: cand.RecentSuccessRate undefined\n\nThe same failure is present at the bead's declared base-rev\n(`7bb075002d99bf66d84a860b4364c430ba637fa9`), so it predates the\nExecuteBeadOptions removal and is not caused by this work.\n\nRoot cause: the external `github.com/DocumentDrivenDX/agent` module renamed\n`RouteCandidateStatus.RecentSuccessRate` → `ProviderReliabilityRate` (per\nADR-006 §5, in `/Users/erik/Projects/agent/service.go`). The local\n`cli/cmd/agent_route_status.go` still references the old field name. This is\na separate routing-observability migration, outside the SD-024 cleanup scope\nnamed by this bead's description (\"Removes the legacy ExecuteBeadOptions\nstruct and the legacy ExecuteBead method\").\n\nSpot check that the affected packages alone are healthy:\n\n    $ go build ./internal/agent/... ./internal/config/...\n    (exit 0)\n\n    $ go test ./internal/agent/ -run TestSynthesizeCommitMessage_InExecuteBead -count=1\n    ok  \tgithub.com/DocumentDrivenDX/ddx/internal/agent\t0.011s\n\nSo the SD-024-touched code is green; only the unrelated `cmd/agent_route_status.go`\nbreaks the whole-tree build/test commands the AC names.\n\n## What a follow-up attempt would need\n\nEither:\n\n  (a) File and complete a separate bead that updates\n      `cli/cmd/agent_route_status.go` to use\n      `RouteCandidateStatus.ProviderReliabilityRate` (two call sites:\n      lines 326 and 421), then re-queue this bead so its full-tree\n      build/test commands can be demonstrated green; or\n\n  (b) Relax this bead's AC to scope-limited build/test commands\n      (`go build ./internal/agent/...` and\n      `go test ./internal/agent/...`), since the legacy-code removal\n      itself does not touch the broken package.\n\nCommitting a route-status fix from inside this bead would violate the\n\"Do not modify files outside the scope the bead description names\"\nconstraint in the execute-bead instructions.\nrationale: ## What is done\n\nThe bead's implementation work is already merged on the base branch. Commit\n`63e86ba1 refactor(agent): retire ExecuteBeadOptions and legacy ExecuteBead\n[ddx-a8eaef0a]` removed both:\n\n  - `type ExecuteBeadOptions` struct\n  - the legacy `ExecuteBead` (non-`WithConfig`) method\n\nVerification of AC item 1:\n\n    $ rg 'type ExecuteBeadOptions ' cli/\n    (no matches)\n\nThe remaining `ExecuteBeadOptions` mentions in the tree are only in source\ncomments (cli/cmd/agent_execute_bead_e2e_test.go, .../execute_bead_e2e_routing_test.go,\ncli/internal/config/types.go, cli/internal/config/testconfig.go) referencing\nthe SD-024 migration history — the type itself is gone.\n\n## What is blocking\n\nAC items 2 and 3 (`go build ./...` / `go test ./...`) cannot be demonstrated\ngreen in this pass for a reason unrelated to this bead's scope:\n\n    cli/cmd/agent_ro