.ddx/attachments/ddx-15f7ee0b/events.jsonl:23:{"actor":"ddx","body":"No-changes rationale for ddx-15f7ee0b attempt 20260423T040113-a89a35ab\n======================================================================\n\nStatus: All acceptance criteria are already satisfied by commits already\npresent in the base branch (a101e215 and its ancestors). No additional\nchanges are required.\n\nThe previous REVIEW:BLOCK on this bead appears to have been a review-side\nmis-targeting: the reviewer's diff covered the evidence-only commit\n034fbf8f instead of the implementation commits af88d432 and 1f1b916c,\nboth of which are already merged into main and are ancestors of the\ncurrent base revision a101e215. The review notes themselves acknowledge\nthis possibility (\"the actual implementation may have been merged already\nbut is not visible in this diff\").\n\nVerification of every AC item against the working-tree state:\n\nAC §1 — Fix A: test isolation enforced by CI\n  - cli/internal/server/test_isolation_lint_test.go provides\n    TestTestsIsolateStateDir, which AST-walks every *_test.go in the\n    server package and fails if a test wires up a server constructor\n    without first isolating XDG_DATA_HOME via setupTestDir-family helpers\n    or t.Setenv(\"XDG_DATA_HOME\", ...).\n  - TestTestIsolationLintCatchesBadCase exercises both the allowed-pattern\n    (good source passes) and the disallowed-pattern (bad source flagged)\n    arms of the lint, satisfying the \"Test cases added for both ...\"\n    sub-clause of AC §1.\n  - All existing tests pass the lint (verified by `go test`).\n\nAC §2 — Fix B: sweep recognizes test-dir pollution\n  - cli/internal/server/state.go exposes IsTestDirPath, which matches\n    /tmp/, /private/tmp/, /var/folders/ prefixes and any path containing\n    a /Test[A-Z][A-Za-z0-9_]*\\d+/ segment (the goTestNameRegexp).\n  - ServerState.migrate (state.go:158-229) drops matching entries on\n    first sweep with no 24 h tombstone delay (Fix B item 1).\n  - ServerState.SweepProjects (state.go:295-330) drops matching entries\n    whether or not the path still exists on disk (Fix B item 2).\n  - Unit test TestMigrateDropsTestDirPollution (state_test.go:90-172)\n    seeds a fixture state containing one real project, one missing\n    /tmp/TestFoo123/001 entry, one *existing* /tmp/Test... entry, and a\n    /private/tmp/TestMac789/001 entry; asserts only the real project\n    survives migration. This is exactly the seeded-fixture test specified\n    in AC §2.\n\nAC §3 — Fix C: pruning CLI\n  - cli/cmd/server_state.go registers `ddx server state prune` with\n    --dry-run and --state flags. Default --state resolves to\n    server.DefaultStateFilePath() (XDG_DATA_HOME/ddx/server-state.json).\n  - server.PruneStateFile (state.go:487-535) writes\n    server-state.json.bak-<UTC YYYYMMDDTHHMMSS> beside the file before\n    rewriting, prints \"Pruned X of Y entries (Z kept)\", and skips the\n    write entirely when DryRun is true.\n  - Integration test TestServerStatePruneDropsPhantomsKeepsRealProjects\n    (cmd/server_state_test.go:22-130) seeds 10 real + 100 fake entries,\n    runs the command, asserts 10 survive and a backup containing exactly\n    110 entries was written.\n  - TestServerStatePruneDryRun additionally verifies --dry-run leaves the\n    file mtime unchanged and writes no backup.\n\nAC §4 — Perf amplifier regression test\n  - TestGetBeadSnapshotsSkipsTombstonedProjects\n    (graphql_bead_perf_skip_phantom_test.go) installs a beadStoreOpenHook\n    and asserts GetBeadSnapshots never opens a bead store for a project\n    whose Unreachable=true. The unreachable filter happens inside\n    GetProjects (state.go:335-347), which the bead path consumes before\n    delegating to beadSnapshotsForProjectEntry.\n  - The CI job \"Guard server state against test pollution\" added in\n    .github/workflows/ci.yml (commit 1f1b916c) runs the full test suite\n    under an isolated XDG_DATA_HOME, starts the server, and fails if the\n    resulting state file contains more than 20 projects or any path\n    matching the test-dir patterns.\n\nAC §5 — Backward compatibility\n  - loadServerState (state.go:113-143) emits \"ddx-server: Pruned X\n    phantom test-dir projects from state file\" when migrate drops at\n    least one entry, satisfying the upgrade-log requirement.\n  - TestLoadServerStateLogsPhantomCleanup (state_test.go:205-239) seeds\n    a state file with two phantom entries, redirects the stdlib logger,\n    invokes loadServerState, and asserts the cleanup line appears in the\n    captured output.\n  - PruneStateFile is idempotent on already-pruned files (a clean state\n    file produces Dropped=0 and no functional change beyond the backup).\n\nAC §6 — Cross-reference\n  - The bead's <notes> already contain the cross-reference paragraph\n    linking ddx-9ce6842a (beads perf) and ddx-2ceb02fa (sessions feed)\n    as the surfaces amplified by this pollution.\n  - state.go:40-43 and state_graphql.go documentation comments name the\n    same two beads in the source so future maintainers see the link.\n\nTest runs (commands executed in this worktree):\n\n  $ go test ./internal/server/ -count=1 \\\n        -run 'TestIsTestDirPath|TestMigrateDropsTestDirPollution|TestSweepProjectsDropsTestDirPollution|TestLoadServerStateLogsPhantomCleanup|TestTestsIsolateStateDir|TestTestIsolationLintCatchesBadCase|TestGetBeadSnapshotsSkipsTombstonedProjects'\n  PASS\n  ok   github.com/DocumentDrivenDX/ddx/internal/server  0.034s\n\n  $ go test ./cmd/ -count=1 -run 'TestServerStatePrune'\n  PASS\n  ok   github.com/DocumentDrivenDX/ddx/cmd  0.015s\n\n  $ go test ./internal/server/ -count=1 -timeout 120s\n  ok   github.com/DocumentDrivenDX/ddx/internal/server  22.464s\n\n  $ go build ./...\n  (clean)\n\nPre-existing unrelated failures in ./cmd: TestInstallationPerformance and\nthe TestAcceptance_US028..US034 family fail because they expect a\npre-built `cli/build/ddx` binary that is not produced by the test\nharness. These failures pre-date this bead (the test files were last\ntouched by commits 0a9c892d / d6dc8cdc / 62d1807d / d02fdea2, none of\nwhich are related to ddx-15f7ee0b).\n\nConclusion: nothing to commit. The branch already meets the contract.\nA bead-attempt commit would only add a no-op marker. Returning control\nto the orchestrator without producing one.\nrationale: No-changes rationale for ddx-15f7ee0b attempt 20260423T040113-a89a35ab\n======================================================================\n\nStatus: All acceptance criteria are already satisfied by commits already\npresent in the base branch (a101e215 and its ancestors). No additional\nchanges are required.\n\nThe previous REVIEW:BLOCK on this bead appears to have been a review-side\nmis-targeting: the reviewer's diff covered the evidence-only commit\n034fbf8f instead of the implementation commits af88d432 and 1f1b916c,\nboth of which are already merged into main and are ancestors of the\ncurrent base revision a101e215. The review notes themselves acknowledge\nthis possibility (\"the actual implementation may have been merged already\nbut is not visible in this diff\").\n\nVerification of every AC item against the working-tree state:\n\nAC §1 — Fix A: test isolation enforced by CI\n  - cli/internal/server/test_isolation_lint_test.go provides\n    TestTestsIsolateStateDir, which AST-walks every *_test.go in the\n    server package and fails if a test wires up a server constructor\n    without first isolating XDG_DATA_HOME via setupTestDir-family helpers\n    or t.Setenv(\"XDG_DATA_HOME\", ...).\n  - TestTestIsolationLintCatchesBadCase exercises both the allowed-pattern\n    (good source passes) and the disallowed-pattern (bad source flagged)\n    arms of the lint, satisfying the \"Test cases added for both ...\"\n    sub-clause of AC §1.\n  - All existing tests pass the lint (verified by `go test`).\n\nAC §2 — Fix B: sweep recognizes test-dir pollution\n  - cli/internal/server/state.go exposes