tifact path.\n  - The wiring fires from execute_bead_loop.go ~L794-810 inside the\n    ExecuteBeadStatusSuccess branch, gated on\n    candidate.IssueType == bead.IssueTypeOperatorPrompt.\n  - The events form satisfies the spec wording in\n    docs/helix/02-design/adr/ADR-021 §Bead shape: \"every artifact\n    mutated by an operator-prompt execution gets an\n    origin_operator_prompt_id event so provenance survives later edits\".\n  - Tests: TestComputeOperatorPromptAffected_DiffsBeadsAndArtifacts,\n    TestRecordOperatorPromptBacklinks_AppendsEventsOnAffectedAndOriginator,\n    TestRecordOperatorPromptBacklinks_EmptyAffectedNoEvents,\n    TestRecordOperatorPromptBacklinks_ConcurrentTargetSameBead.\n\nAC3 — \"Backlinks queryable via ddx bead show\":\n  - `ddx bead show <id> --json` calls Store.LoadEventsInline (cmd/bead.go\n    L330) which inlines events for both active and archived beads, so\n    `origin_operator_prompt_id` events are visible via the JSON shape:\n        ddx bead show <originator-or-affected-id> --json \\\n          | jq '.events[] | select(.kind == \"origin_operator_prompt_id\")'\n  - Equivalently, `ddx bead evidence list <id>` (cmd/bead.go L654-668)\n    enumerates the same events.\n\nThe verification_command above re-runs the four AC-bearing test packages\nagainst the current tree. Exit 0 ⇒ all three ACs remain satisfied, the\nbead can close as already-done.\nresult_rev=61429f5f01a91bfa793402e525ca8064186d4074\nbase_rev=61429f5f01a91bfa793402e525ca8064186d4074","created_at":"2026-05-03T19:43:52.929277629Z","kind":"execute-bead","source":"ddx agent work","summary":"already_satisfied"}
